619,Brockville General Hospital,Healthcare Experience,"Healthcare Experience. Safe, trusted, and quality healthcare; where and when patients need it.. Enhance our patient and family centered culture.: Improve access to care.: Ensure safe and effective transitions.: Implement evidence-based practices.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text focuses on quality and safety, as well as improving access to needed care for patients.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Brockville General Hospital,619
619,Brockville General Hospital,Partnerships,Partnerships. Collaborate to meet the needs of our community.. Seek opportunities to better integrate care.: Foster shared leadership with our partners.: Honour our role in sustaining a healthy community.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,The text emphasizes collaboration and integration of care to meet community needs and sustain a healthy community.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Brockville General Hospital,619
619,Brockville General Hospital,Team Well-Being,"Team Well-Being. Invest in our people to be the best at what we do.. Ensure a safe, healthy, positive, and professional work culture.: Inspire and empower our people.: Sustain a highly qualified healthcare workforce.: Create a culture of equity, diversity, inclusion, and accessibility.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on investing in employees, fostering a positive work culture, and sustaining a qualified workforce, while also creating a culture of EDI which all point to workforce and organizational themes.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Brockville General Hospital,619
619,Brockville General Hospital,Resource Sustainability And Growth,"Resource Sustainability And Growth. Delivery of safe, quality care through smart resource use.. Strengthen our current technological, physical, and equipment infrastructure.: Improve information systems to support decision-making and patient care.: Modernize and expand to meet future needs of our community.: Streamline to preserve our health human resources.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"Focuses on smart resource use and strengthening infrastructure and equipment, while also streamlining human resources to improve efficiency.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Brockville General Hospital,619
624,Campbellford Memorial Hospital,Modernizing Service Delivery To Continuously Improve Outcomes,"Modernizing Service Delivery To Continuously Improve Outcomes. We will create an integrated, high performing and agile health services model promoting a holistic approach to wellness and healthcare.. NF.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The focus on integrated health services and promoting a holistic approach to wellness aligns with integration and partnerships, as well as population and community health.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Campbellford Memorial Hospital,624
624,Campbellford Memorial Hospital,"Advancing Our Workplace Through Inclusivity, Connection, Wellbeing, And Growth","Advancing Our Workplace Through Inclusivity, Connection, Wellbeing, And Growth. We will foster a culture of belonging by inspiring and supporting each other to reach our full potential.. NF.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text emphasizes inclusivity, wellbeing, and growth within the workplace, aligning with workforce sustainability and fostering a positive organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Campbellford Memorial Hospital,624
624,Campbellford Memorial Hospital,Pushing The Boundaries Of Rural Care,Pushing The Boundaries Of Rural Care. We will set a new standard for the delivery of rural care outside the traditional hospital setting.. NF.,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,ACCESS & CAPACITY,Focus on delivering care outside the hospital in a rural setting suggests an emphasis on community-based health and improving access for rural populations.,Population & Community Health,Population & Community Health,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Campbellford Memorial Hospital,624
624,Campbellford Memorial Hospital,Building For Tomorrow,Building For Tomorrow. Innovate our space today and plan to build a new Campus of Care that will serve as a destination for integrated health services at the heart of the community.. NF.,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text discusses building a new Campus of Care, indicating infrastructure development and integrated health services suggesting partnerships.",Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Campbellford Memorial Hospital,624
592,Lennox & Addington County General Hospital,1. Exceptional Care,"1. Exceptional Care. THE_HOSPITAL will invest in a Quality Improvement transformation, annually identifying 1-2 areas or units that require special focus.. NF.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The focus on quality improvement and identifying areas needing special focus directly relates to patient care excellence, supported by organizational efforts to achieve it.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lennox & Addington County General Hospital,592
592,Lennox & Addington County General Hospital,2. Trusted Relationships,"2. Trusted Relationships. THE_HOSPITAL actively fosters inclusion and respect through a systemic anti-racism framework, including Indigenous People.. NF.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text explicitly mentions inclusion, respect, and an anti-racism framework, all aligning with health equity and a supportive organizational culture.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lennox & Addington County General Hospital,592
592,Lennox & Addington County General Hospital,3. Relentless Communications,"3. Relentless Communications. THE_HOSPITAL will pursue a robust multi-channel communications/ engagement strategy to enhance patient experiences, improve patient care, enhance teamwork, help attract staff, and maintain our strong reputation in the community.. NF.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The focus on patient experience and improved patient care aligns with patient care excellence, while attracting staff aligns with workforce sustainability.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lennox & Addington County General Hospital,592
593,MIDDLESEX HOSPITAL ALLIANCE,Collaborate For Exceptional Care And Experiences,"Collaborate For Exceptional Care And Experiences. NF. • Provide compassionate care and patient-centered experiences through communication and engagement with our patients, families and care providers with a specific focus on local Indigenous communities.: • Continue to enhance quality and safety in alignment with our quality priorities.: • Leverage technology to advance the next phase of digital care delivery.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on compassionate, patient-centered care and experience, quality and safety, and has a specific focus on local Indigenous communities.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,MIDDLESEX HOSPITAL ALLIANCE,593
593,MIDDLESEX HOSPITAL ALLIANCE,"Engage, Support And Inspire Our People","Engage, Support And Inspire Our People. NF. • Acknowledge, respect and embrace diversity, equity, inclusion and antiracism in our environments.: • Build on a culture of empowering engagement, safety, trust, belonging and purpose.: • Enhance our focus on wellness and recognition, aiming to be an organization of choice for employees, physicians and volunteers.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on employee engagement, wellness, and creating a positive and inclusive work environment, aligning with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,MIDDLESEX HOSPITAL ALLIANCE,593
593,MIDDLESEX HOSPITAL ALLIANCE,Advance How We Deliver Care,"Advance How We Deliver Care. NF. • Harness innovative ways of expanding access to high quality care for our local and rural communities.: • Invest in relationships and collaborate with partners to achieve our vision and strategic priorities, making the healthcare system more integrated for our patients.: • Advance clinical, information technology, capital infrastructure and financial opportunities to respond to the evolving and future needs of our hospitals and communities.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,The text highlights harnessing innovation for expanding access to care and collaborating with partners for a more integrated healthcare system.,Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,MIDDLESEX HOSPITAL ALLIANCE,593
596,STEVENSON MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,People,"People. Creating a work environment that values and recognizes the contribution of every staff member in creating a positive patient care experience. Creating and upholding a culture of continuous learning, focused on collaboration and teamwork.. We will: achieve our pillars by continuing to seek out and utilize innovative approaches, from cutting edge equipment to finding new ways to anticipate and meet our patients' needs, working closely with our staff to utilize every dollar available to offer excellent care, and developing new partnerships to build strong community coalitions.: We will: collaborate with our staff, our peers, our local community, Ministry and Ontario Health Team to create the highest quality comprehensive care options for everyone in our community.: We will: create communication channels to keep our patients, families, staff and local community informed about the direction at THE_HOSPITAL, what is happening and where we are going.: We will: put quality first, in every action, every day to continuously create an excellent care experience for each and every patient.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text emphasizes valuing staff contributions, fostering a culture of continuous learning, and collaboration, which directly aligns with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,STEVENSON MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,596
596,STEVENSON MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,Care,"Care. Keeping the patient at the center of every care discussion and decision. Ensuring that patient values inform every aspect of delivery.. We will: achieve our pillars by continuing to seek out and utilize innovative approaches, from cutting edge equipment to finding new ways to anticipate and meet our patients' needs, working closely with our staff to utilize every dollar available to offer excellent care, and developing new partnerships to build strong community coalitions.: We will: collaborate with our staff, our peers, our local community, Ministry and Ontario Health Team to create the highest quality comprehensive care options for everyone in our community.: We will: create communication channels to keep our patients, families, staff and local community informed about the direction at THE_HOSPITAL, what is happening and where we are going.: We will: put quality first, in every action, every day to continuously create an excellent care experience for each and every patient.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on patient-centered care and quality, while also highlighting collaboration with the community and OHT.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,STEVENSON MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,596
596,STEVENSON MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,Partnerships,"Partnerships. Working collaboratively with local and community health care providers to continue to develop our care network and availability to offer a seamless care experience for our patients.. We will: achieve our pillars by continuing to seek out and utilize innovative approaches, from cutting edge equipment to finding new ways to anticipate and meet our patients' needs, working closely with our staff to utilize every dollar available to offer excellent care, and developing new partnerships to build strong community coalitions.: We will: collaborate with our staff, our peers, our local community, Ministry and Ontario Health Team to create the highest quality comprehensive care options for everyone in our community.: We will: create communication channels to keep our patients, families, staff and local community informed about the direction at THE_HOSPITAL, what is happening and where we are going.: We will: put quality first, in every action, every day to continuously create an excellent care experience for each and every patient.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on developing partnerships with local providers to improve the care network and patient experience, as well as working with OHTs to build comprehensive care options.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,STEVENSON MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,596
596,STEVENSON MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,Investments,"Investments. Operating appropriately within fiscal constraints to maximize investments in staff, equipment, infrastructure and improvement to provide high quality care for present and future patients.. We will: achieve our pillars by continuing to seek out and utilize innovative approaches, from cutting edge equipment to finding new ways to anticipate and meet our patients' needs, working closely with our staff to utilize every dollar available to offer excellent care, and developing new partnerships to build strong community coalitions.: We will: collaborate with our staff, our peers, our local community, Ministry and Ontario Health Team to create the highest quality comprehensive care options for everyone in our community.: We will: create communication channels to keep our patients, families, staff and local community informed about the direction at THE_HOSPITAL, what is happening and where we are going.: We will: put quality first, in every action, every day to continuously create an excellent care experience for each and every patient.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,The text focuses on operating within fiscal constraints to maximize investments for high-quality patient care and seeking innovative approaches for efficiency.,Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,STEVENSON MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,596
597,Mississippi River Health,Your Care Experience,"Your Care Experience. NF. • Ensure patients & residents experience high-quality, compassionate care: • Coordinate seamless care within and amongst our facilities: • Continue care experience improvement through implementation of clinical services plan.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The focus is on improving the patient experience through high-quality, compassionate, and coordinated care.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Mississippi River Health,597
597,Mississippi River Health,Our Great People,"Our Great People. NF. • Empower people to provide excellent, personalized and innovative care: • Ensure a strong and sustainable team of health professionals: • Be the place people choose to work.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text emphasizes empowering staff and ensuring a sustainable team, pointing to workforce sustainability, while also aiming for excellent, personalized and innovative care, which connects to patient care excellence.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Mississippi River Health,597
597,Mississippi River Health,Our Partners In Care,Our Partners In Care. NF. • Reimagine and engage in partnerships that strengthen the network of care: • Better serve community mental health and post hospital care needs with our partners: • Work with Ontario Health Team partners to advance community health priorities and interests.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The text focuses on strengthening partnerships and networks of care, especially with the Ontario Health Team, and mentions community health priorities.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Mississippi River Health,597
597,Mississippi River Health,Our Places & Spaces,"Our Places & Spaces. NF. • Develope a vision for redevelopment of Carleton Place hospital facility: • Integrate information, financial and EMR systems: • Function seamlessly together.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,This involves redevelopment of a hospital facility and integration of systems across locations.,Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Mississippi River Health,597
599,Arnprior Regional Health,Person Centred Care,"Person Centred Care. Emphasizing our existing areas of exceptional clinical care today and continually advancing our care for tomorrow.. Foster relationships to enhance patient, resident, client and family partnerships, improving the overall experience.. Explore collaborative opportunities for quality of care and service excellence within our community.. Expand our reach by leveraging innovative care delivery models, emphasizing, accessibility, quality, and efficiency of care for our community.. Proactively respond to our community's evolving needs through designing optimal care pathways for persons through OHT partnerships and alignment of service integration.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The focus is on improving patient experience and quality of care, with mention of OHT partnerships for service integration.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Arnprior Regional Health,599
599,Arnprior Regional Health,Our People,"Our People. Our investment in, and the development of our people, so our healthcare team can grow and thrive, and encompassing a network of support for staff, volunteers, and services providers.. Recruit and retain skilled and passionate healthcare team members who live our values and demonstrate a commitment to the people we serve across THE_HOSPITAL.. Build our people's capacity through targeted opportunities for professional and leadership development.. Link our people strategy to maintain a culture of mutual respect, compassion, recognition, and support our team's safety, mental health, and wellness.. Develop a culture founded in diversity, equity and inclusion that drives decision making, service delivery, leadership, and partnerships.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"Focus on recruitment, retention, development, wellness, and culture clearly aligns with workforce sustainability, while also touching on organizational culture through values and DEI initiatives.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Arnprior Regional Health,599
599,Arnprior Regional Health,Our Infrastructure,"Our Infrastructure. Developing a future oriented plan and the development of our infrastructure to advance our journey as a health hub that provides the next generation care within our community.. Continue maximizing the use of digital health technology to improve the quality of care our providers can deliver, and the seamlessness of our patient, resident, and client experience across our neighbouring healthcare organizations.. Co-design our physical infrastructure by engaging patients, resident, clients, and providers to maximize the experience we provide while efficiently addressing the future clinical, environmental and community needs.. Provide a master planning process to ensure we are meeting the current and future needs of our community with regards to capital infrastructure investment.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,The text primarily discusses the development of infrastructure and maximizing the use of digital health technology to improve care.,Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Arnprior Regional Health,599
599,Arnprior Regional Health,Our Partners,"Our Partners. Fostering productive relationships to create an integrated health care system within our community and surrounding region.. Strengthen linkages with the Ottawa West Four Rivers OHT, improving the overall population health with a focus on person centred care through enhanced experiences, reinvesting in care, and improving provider engagement.. Enhance two-way engagement with our community, promoting responsiveness, mutual understanding, and collaboration.. Invigorate our community participation and volunteerism, adopting differentiating approaches to attract, foster, and acknowledge community support.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,The text focuses on fostering relationships to create an integrated healthcare system and improving population health with community engagement.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Arnprior Regional Health,599
599,Arnprior Regional Health,Financial Stewardship,"Financial Stewardship. Ensuring THE_HOSPITAL has the requisite resources to enable continued service excellence, enhance experiences and build upon the strategic priority for the community.. Creatively engage with the broader system to ensure we have the resourcing required to deliver on our ambitious plan.. Seek innovative funding mechanisms, identifying unique areas of operational excellence, and opportunities for industry partnerships.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on ensuring the hospital has necessary resources through funding, efficiency, and partnerships.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Arnprior Regional Health,599
606,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,Drive Clinical And Academic Excellence,"Drive Clinical And Academic Excellence. We’ll be a regional academic health sciences centre. As a full-scale teaching hospital and research institute, we’ll offer the latest in complex, specialized care at scope and scale that meets our region’s needs. Using state-of-the-art tools, we’ll teach the next generation of practitioners to be clinically exceptional and compassionate. As a national leader in research at the bedside, we’ll improve care now, not years in the future. The cornerstone of our work will always be collaborative partnerships, to give you the care you need – at THE_HOSPITAL or elsewhere in our regional system of care.. • Continuously improving performance indicators for quality: • Increased number of collaborations with academic institutions and research partners: • Increased number and effectiveness of our partnerships with care providers that support the right care, at the right place and time.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"This text focuses on academic excellence, research institute development, and collaborative partnerships to improve care.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,606
606,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,"Cultivate Fulfilled, High-Performing Teams","Cultivate Fulfilled, High-Performing Teams. The drive for excellence fuels Team THE_HOSPITAL. We’re a workforce equipped for today and primed for the challenges of tomorrow. Driven by our shared purpose, as we live our values, each member of Team THE_HOSPITAL is powered by the impact they have on the people they care for. Top talent, regardless of specialization or career stage, will aspire to join THE_HOSPITAL, knowing it is an important career achievement. Through a culture of continuous learning, our people will grow in their roles, supported by the best tools and resources to unlock their potential. We attract and retain an engaged and talented team that feels cared for and valued. Our diverse perspectives and unique experiences will continue to ignite innovation and foster belonging. Diversity is critical to our collective success.. • Increased number of qualified candidates: • Increased Team THE_HOSPITAL engagement: • Improved retention of diverse staff, physicians and volunteers.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on attracting, retaining, and supporting a high-performing workforce through culture, learning, and engagement, aligning with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,606
606,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,Make Exceptional Patient And Family Experiences,"Make Exceptional Patient And Family Experiences. Offering culturally informed care, Team THE_HOSPITAL will continue to understand and honour diverse perspectives and needs. We will eliminate disparities and promote equity to ensure fair access to care for all. We will recognize and act on the unique needs of Indigenous Peoples. Our patients and families will feel comfortable and safe. We’ll offer as many care options as makes sense for your needs, with patients and families remaining active participants in that process. They’ll also be able to easily navigate the connections between THE_HOSPITAL and our community care partners. Our patient and family experience will not only help people heal; it will ensure they feel respected, informed and empowered.. • Improved patient satisfaction: • Improved evidence of equitable access.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The focus is on improving patient and family experiences through culturally informed care, eliminating disparities, promoting equity, and addressing the needs of Indigenous Peoples.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,606
606,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,Sustainable Investment,"Sustainable Investment. We’ll wisely use our resources for lasting improvements and growth, ensuring THE_HOSPITAL and our regional healthcare system stay strong, effective, and accessible now and in the future. Our essential investment in research and advanced medical technologies will make precise, minimally invasive care – the gold standard for complex care – possible. We’ll expand and upgrade our facilities to meet state-of-the-art standards for our rapidly growing community to eliminate hallway medicine and reduce wait times. By safeguarding our reputation, we’ll build community trust, attract top talent and partners, and inspire funding – all vital for sustainable, quality care. We’ll make smart choices and adapt our plans as the healthcare landscape changes.. NF.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text discusses using resources wisely for lasting improvements, facility upgrades, and attracting funding for quality care, indicating a focus on financial sustainability and infrastructure.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,606
606,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,Health Technology,"Health Technology. Technology is crucial to providing care that’s not just smarter, but also kinder and more efficient. We’ll simplify how everyone – our team, patients, and partners – accesses information and care. We’ll continually introduce and upgrade digital tools that improve how we share and use data, ensuring everyone benefits from more connected services. Team THE_HOSPITAL will be equipped with advanced medical technologies and systems designed to deliver seamless, integrated care. By leveraging advanced analytics and securing easy access to crucial information, we’ll make informed decisions a routine part of care while safeguarding personal privacy with strict security protocols.. NF.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on improving care through technology and equipping the team with advanced systems, also highlighting the efficiency aspect.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,606
606,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,Strategic Partnerships,"Strategic Partnerships. We’ll continue to forge powerful alliances to meet our patients’ diverse needs and enhance community well-being. As a partner in the Barrie and Area Ontario Health Team and with Simcoe Muskoka hospitals, we’ll support regional collaboration to improve the overall health of our region. We’ll partner with local organizations to fill gaps in care and help people heal at home as much as possible; we’ll work to each other’s strengths and share resources to reach our common goals. We aim to build a regional system of care that is responsive, resourceful, and united in its mission to nurture a healthier community.. NF.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The text emphasizes forging alliances, OHT partnerships, and regional collaboration to improve overall health and fill gaps in care within the community.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre,606
611,North Shore Health Network,Clarify,"Clarify. Getting clear about who we are is an important part of this plan, with renewed mission and vision statements, as well as values.. - Communicate this strategic plan to THE_HOSPITAL community, including partners, First Nations, and municipality. Use public townhall, Chief and Council, and municipal council meetings to spread awareness of the plan.: - Embed the THE_HOSPITAL C.A.R.E.S. values. Invest in branded items to distribute to staff; displace values and acronym in prominent places through THE_HOSPITAL sites; embed values in on-boarding; tie values to annual performance appraisals; integrate into external communications and social media presence.: - Ensure capacity and capability of the Board, Senior Leadership, and the broader Leadership Team to execute the Hospital/Performance Improvement Plan. Provide Board training and regular education sessions as part of the annual work plan; invest in target skills development for Senior Leaders; support in-service learning, invest in target skills development (like financial management for non-financial managers), and support medium to long-term education planning at the manager level.: - Conclude a Hospital/Performance Improvement Plan with Ontario Health. Continue to work through the Hospital Services Accountability Agreement process with Ontario Health.: - Identify and articulate THE_HOSPITAL’s role in the Algoma Ontario Health Team. Continue to participate at the Governance Committee and Leadership Committee to ensure a rural voice.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The focus is on clarifying the hospital's mission, vision, and values, along with engaging with First Nations and the municipality, indicating a strong emphasis on organizational culture and social responsibility.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,North Shore Health Network,611
611,North Shore Health Network,Stabilize,"Stabilize. Making sure our tank is full, so we can continue to serve our communities.. - Establish a sustainable multilevel provider hospitalist program. Work with the local physician group and staff nurse practitioners to establish a sustainable rotation given local resources.: - Fully establish the Geriatric Program. Continue recruitment for vacant positions and apply for reallocations of funding where needed for recruitable positions that fit the program and patient needs.: - Continue to build flexibility into practices. Ensure cross training and succession planning for key positions.: - Identify gaps in care in our service area. Work collaboratively with Trefry Centre and Dr. McLeod’s program for western catchment.: - Move to a truly participatory budget process within the Leadership Team. In addition to the annual budget refreshers, Finance will work directly with the department manager and their senior manager to establish a realistic budget to be held accountable to through an iterative process.: - Implement the Performance Improvement Plan (PIP). Working with the Implementation Committee, Senior Leadership, and the Board, we will make the changes identified and committed to in the PIP, working towards a financially sustainable THE_HOSPITAL that has a balanced budget: - Renew/build partnerships. Sign the partnership agreement with Maamwesying; sign the protocol agreement with Nogdawindamin; formalize service level agreements for support of Huron Shores Family Health Team; engage with First Nations leaders and communities to be an ally in reconciliation; and engage municipal leaders to support local health advocacy.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text emphasizes establishing sustainable programs, participatory budgeting, implementing a performance improvement plan for financial stability, and building flexibility into practices through cross-training and succession planning, indicating a focus on both financial and workforce aspects.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,North Shore Health Network,611
611,North Shore Health Network,Improve,"Improve. Building on our foundation of safe, quality care to do better for those we serve.. - Create cultural safety throughout THE_HOSPITAL. Invest in multimodal cultural safety training; commit to action on #22 of the Calls to Action of the Truth and Reconciliation Commission of Canada (and other Calls that are reasonably actionable by THE_HOSPITAL); develop better pathway for culturally competent community based care post-discharge; develop partnership for in-patient/LTC culturally appropriate care; identify and create a space for multi-use spiritual care; explore and if appropriate implement tri-lingual wayfinding signage; tie cultural learning to National Indigenous Peoples Day and National Truth and Reconciliation Day; work towards “economic reconciliation” by procuring items from Indigenous businesses; identify other diverse communities and work collaboratively on strategies to create cultural safety.: - Collaborate with Maamwesying Ontario Health Team. Establish relationship envisioned in Partnership Agreement; collaborate on shared areas of importance such as community-based care and mental health and addictions.: - Be a full participant in the Algoma Ontario Health Team. Continue to contribute to Leadership Council and Governance Committees; leverage OHT for local integration and service extensions/improvements.: - Implement ONE/Meditech Expanse digital health transformation. Allocate sufficient resources for smooth go-live; optimize post go-live environment to maximize patient benefit.: - Become better environmental stewards. Identify and eliminate single use plastics; substitute single use plastics for single use sustainable materials; reduce packaging waste; where feasible transition to reusable products; reduce energy consumption; use environmentally sustainable products.: - Reach for a unified culture of one team at multiple sites. Encourage regular leadership (especially Senior Leadership Team) presence at all three sites; common staff events (when and where safe and appropriate); align non-clinical services along service rather than by site; standardization across sites for services, products, and practice.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"This focuses on creating cultural safety for Indigenous populations and collaborating with Ontario Health Teams, addressing equity and system integration.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,North Shore Health Network,611
640,COLLINGWOOD G&M HOSPITAL,Elevate Quality,Elevate Quality. NF. • Enhance the patient and family experience: • Advance patient safety and access to care.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text focuses on improving the patient experience, safety, and access to care.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,COLLINGWOOD G&M HOSPITAL,640
640,COLLINGWOOD G&M HOSPITAL,Develop Team,Develop Team. NF. • Strengthen THE_HOSPITAL's culture: • Invest in THE_HOSPITAL team members: • Scale up our workforce.,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The focus on strengthening culture, investing in team members, and scaling up the workforce directly addresses workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,COLLINGWOOD G&M HOSPITAL,640
