644,Cornwall Community Hospital,Recovery,Recovery. NF. * Enhancing access to care: * Committing to operational excellence: * Advancing innovation: * Maintaining a culture of quality and safety: * Establishing physical capacity.,ACCESS & CAPACITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"This focuses on enhancing access to care, operational excellence, quality and safety, and establishing physical capacity.",Access & Capacity,Access & Capacity,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Cornwall Community Hospital,644
644,Cornwall Community Hospital,People,"People. NF. * Inspired by patients and care partners: * Supporting the wellbeing of our people: * Engaging and cultivating a high performing team: * Building a culture of equity, diversity and inclusion, and embracing reconciliation: * Stewarding our environmental and social responsibilities.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on employee wellbeing, team performance, equity, and social responsibilities, indicating workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Cornwall Community Hospital,644
644,Cornwall Community Hospital,Integration,Integration. NF. * Creating sustainable models of care: * Supporting transitions in care: * Advancing collaborative partnerships: * Promoting health system integration.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,None,"The text explicitly focuses on integration, partnerships, and transitions in care, all of which fall under the Integration & Partnerships theme.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Cornwall Community Hospital,644
646,DEEP RIVER & DISTRICT HEALTH,People,"People. We will retain, recruit and grow our team to provide care for today and tomorrow.. ► Fostering a culture where our THE_HOSPITAL team feels valued and safe.: ► Retaining and recruiting team members to operate our current and future services.: ► Providing opportunities for learning, growth and development.: ► Nurturing an inclusive environment where people want to work, learn and grow.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on retaining, recruiting, and growing the team, as well as fostering a positive and inclusive work environment.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,DEEP RIVER & DISTRICT HEALTH,646
646,DEEP RIVER & DISTRICT HEALTH,Growth,"Growth. We will responsibly build and advance our capabilities to provide safe, quality care and services.. ► Partnering with patients, residents and family to provide quality, person-centered care and services.: ► Managing growth and operations responsibly.: ► Enhancing our physical space to meet community, patient, resident and team member needs.: ► Leveraging and embedding existing and emerging technology into operations to connect people to care.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text emphasizes providing quality care, enhancing physical space and leveraging technology to improve operations.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,DEEP RIVER & DISTRICT HEALTH,646
646,DEEP RIVER & DISTRICT HEALTH,Community,"Community. We will foster partnerships and opportunities for engagement to improve the health of our community.. ► Engaging with our community to understand their needs, including seniors and equity-deserving* populations.: ► Exploring existing and new ways to provide access to care and services.: ► Leveraging evidence and data to help shape services.: ► Establishing THE_HOSPITAL as an inclusive and safe place where everyone can access care.",POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on improving community health through engagement and understanding the needs of diverse populations, including seniors and equity-deserving groups.",Population & Community Health,Population & Community Health,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,DEEP RIVER & DISTRICT HEALTH,646
647,Dryden Regional Health Centre,Be A Great Place To Work,"Be A Great Place To Work. “Empowering Exceptional People to Provide Exceptional Care”<br><br>Our people – THE_HOSPITAL staff, professional staff, physicians and volunteers- are our greatest asset. We need enough staff, with the right kinds of skills, who are highly engaged and energized to continue to offer our patients the type and scope of quality service THE_HOSPITAL wants to provide.<br><br>THE_HOSPITAL has always had strong HR strategies that have enabled us to be creative in attracting and retaining the best people. Now more than ever we need to be here for the staff and physicians we have invested in, ensuring they feel appreciated and are enabled to give their best every day. We know that if we are an exceptional place to work, THE_HOSPITAL will be successful at retaining our staff and at attracting new talent, even in this very competitive labour market.. • Focus on adopting evidence-based practices, strategies, and behaviours that we know will have positive impacts on staff, performance, fulfillment, and engagement.: • Use innovative best practices so our people can care, work, grow, and thrive, and be an exceptional place for existing and new staff to deliver quality patient care.: • Provide our people with access to the leadership, resources, and supports needed to thrive in a physically and emotionally safe environment;: • Implement and provide training that allow us to actively demonstrate our commitment to cultural diversity, anti-racism and inclusion in our daily work.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This initiative focuses on attracting, retaining, and supporting staff, aligning with workforce sustainability, and emphasizes cultural diversity, anti-racism and inclusion, thus relating to organizational culture and governance.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Dryden Regional Health Centre,647
647,Dryden Regional Health Centre,Ensure Strong Foundations,"Ensure Strong Foundations. “Progressive Care for Changing Times”<br><br>We have learned a lot from the pandemic and know that stability is needed to get through difficult times. In order to continue to offer high quality services to our community, THE_HOSPITAL needs to ensure it is operating with strong foundations.<br><br>This means optimizing our financial resources, ensuring we are accessing funding effectively, and using the funds we have in the best way we can.<br><br>It also means ensuring strong service delivery foundations: knowing we are set up to deliver best quality services to our patients. We also need to ensure that our actions continue to be aligned with our core values, ensuring we demonstrate our respect and understanding for the unique needs of the populations that rely on us.. • Ensure we are optimizing how we access funding to support our work: • Identify and implement innovative ways to generate/increase our revenues: • Execute on strategies that will create clinical and/or operational efficiencies, so that we can do more with the resources that we have.: • Act on opportunities to improve service delivery approaches to ensure we are maximizing our use of resources and providing care aligned with best practice.: • Plan for and continue to invest in making capital upgrades that will enhance our ability to deliver quality services: • Ensure effective emergency planning: • Invest to ensure our actions at THE_HOSPITAL promote culturally safe experiences and advance health equity for Indigenous peoples: • Develop mechanisms for engaging the voices of groups we may not have heard from in the past.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,The text focuses on optimizing financial resources and promoting culturally safe experiences and health equity for Indigenous peoples.,Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Dryden Regional Health Centre,647
647,Dryden Regional Health Centre,Lead New Solutions,"Lead New Solutions. “Innovative Care through Collaboration”<br><br>It is clear that new solutions are needed to address the many pressures our community and our hospital is facing. Our ability to continue to serve our patients depends greatly on decisions being made outside our walls.<br><br>THE_HOSPITAL needs to take an active role in determining the future as the system changes and new ways of serving patients are being developed in our community. We need to ensure there is clarity about what THE_HOSPITAL will provide as it works together with others in new ways. We commit to being a catalyst for change.<br><br>We will dedicate resources and share our experience and expertise, providing leadership in pursuit of a system that provides better access to the types of care our communities needs.. • Create short- to medium-term development plans for key leaders with the goal of increasing THE_HOSPITAL's capacity and competency to lead internal and system change;: • Support and enable THE_HOSPITAL leaders to actively advocate for and support the development and improvement of community-based services that will improve the health of our communities;: • Build on our capacity and capabilities of leader roles at THE_HOSPITAL to ensure external accountabilities are assigned, understood, and accounted for.: • Ensure a sustainable future by understanding our mandate, advancing partnerships, and using best practices to guide how we are using our valuable and limited resources;: • Provide strong leadership to help our communities and system find solutions to increasingly difficult challenges, advance partnerships, and advocate for positive system change.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on leading change through collaboration and partnerships within the broader healthcare system, while also emphasizing leadership development and organizational capacity to drive this change.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Dryden Regional Health Centre,647
648,HWMH; EG,Deliver A Staff And Clinician Experience That Retains And Recruits Top Talent.,"Deliver A Staff And Clinician Experience That Retains And Recruits Top Talent.. NF. 1.1 Develop a comprehensive strategy to help attract and retain staff.: 1.2 Define clear performance measurements that promote accountability.: 1.3 Ensure that our staff have the skills and training to provide high-quality care to meet the increasingly-complex care needs of our community.: 1.4 Focus on diversity, equity and inclusion to inform decision making, service delivery, leadership, and partnerships.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The focus is on attracting and retaining staff, with elements of accountability, skills/training, and DEI woven into the strategy.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,HWMH; EG,648
648,HWMH; EG,Meet The Growing And Changing Needs Of Our Community.,Meet The Growing And Changing Needs Of Our Community.. NF. 2.1 Conduct a needs assessment based on the demographic changes in the community to align upon the core clinical services that meet the needs of our growing population moving forward.: 2.2 Refine pathways to referral programs.: 2.3 Explore and prioritize current and prospective healthcare partnerships that allow us to meet the needs of our community.: 2.4 Share resources with partner organizations to optimize efficiencies and improve patient and resident care.: 2.5 Build and grow our leadership visibility and presence within the community.: 2.6 Explore innovative models of care that support our rural community.,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"This focuses on community needs assessment, referral pathways, and partnerships, aligning with population health and integration.",Population & Community Health,Population & Community Health,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,HWMH; EG,648
648,HWMH; EG,Invest In Our Long-Term Sustainability.,Invest In Our Long-Term Sustainability.. NF. 3.1 Renew our Health Information System to optimize patient and resident care.: 3.2 Double the capacity of Edgewater Gardens.: 3.3 Build rigorous financial sustainability and risk management plans.,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text discusses financial sustainability plans, renewing the health information system, and doubling capacity which implies financial planning.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,HWMH; EG,648
650,ST. JOSEPH'S GENERAL HOSPITAL ELLIOT LAKE,The Patient Experience,"The Patient Experience. NF. - Treated like family: - Quality, safe, compassionate, patient and senior-centred care: - Access and Equity for all.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The title and text highlight patient-centered care, quality, safety, and access & equity, all aligning with patient experience.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,ST. JOSEPH'S GENERAL HOSPITAL ELLIOT LAKE,650
650,ST. JOSEPH'S GENERAL HOSPITAL ELLIOT LAKE,Inspired Employees,Inspired Employees. NF. - Ensuring employee safety in a just culture with a focus on Health Human Resources (HHR) challenges and opportunities: - Setting the standard of Civility and promoting cultural diversity: - Creating an environment of staff appreciation.,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on employee safety, HR challenges, cultural diversity, and staff appreciation, which all relate to workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,ST. JOSEPH'S GENERAL HOSPITAL ELLIOT LAKE,650
650,ST. JOSEPH'S GENERAL HOSPITAL ELLIOT LAKE,Unity,"Unity. NF. - Fostering collaboration and partnership: - Coordination with Regional services: - Transformation of service delivery- ""One stop shop"".",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,None,"The text emphasizes collaboration, partnership, and coordination of services, aligning with integration efforts.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,ST. JOSEPH'S GENERAL HOSPITAL ELLIOT LAKE,650
650,ST. JOSEPH'S GENERAL HOSPITAL ELLIOT LAKE,Demonstrated Leadership,Demonstrated Leadership. NF. - Upholding the legacy of Catholic Health Care Services: - Through all communications: - To provide First Class Services as a Centre of Excellence.,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The statement emphasizes upholding the legacy and providing first-class services, which relates to organizational values and a commitment to excellence in patient care.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,ST. JOSEPH'S GENERAL HOSPITAL ELLIOT LAKE,650
651,The Le Royal,Sustainability,"Sustainability. Build our successful future on a solid foundation.. Maximize revenue and funding: The THE_HOSPITAL will advocate for increased government funding, while also strengthening fundraising initiatives and diversifying sources of support.. Be a responsible steward of limited resources: The THE_HOSPITAL is committed to strong financial accountability, effective cost management and optimizing resource use to ensure that every dollar advances our mission and serves our community.. Improve our approach to risk management and governance: The THE_HOSPITAL will enhance its approach to risk management by strengthening accountability and oversight and ensuring that governance practices align with the standards set by the Ontario Hospital Association.. Reduce our impact on the environment: The THE_HOSPITAL will identify and implement ways to reduce waste, protect the environment and contribute to the fight against climate change. Through sustainable practices, we will support the health and well-being of both our community and the planet.. Use technology to increase efficiency and effectiveness: The THE_HOSPITAL will develop a digital strategy that guides investments in modern tools such as the Regional Epic medical records system and Microsoft 365. Together with our staff and partners, we’ll create a framework for introducing artificial intelligence with the goal of improving productivity and easing administrative burdens.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on revenue, funding, cost management, risk management, governance, and environmental impact, aligning with financial sustainability and organizational governance.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,The Le Royal,651
651,The Le Royal,People,"People. Cultivate a positive work environment through transparency, collaboration and engagement.. Strengthen engagement by building a culture of respect, trust and open communication that provides safety and wellness: At The THE_HOSPITAL, we are committed to creating a workplace where every voice is valued and matters. We will develop an internal communications strategy and introduce modern channels, including a new intranet. We will continue to enhance our wellness and safety initiatives, employing a whole-of-organization approach that empowers employees, prioritizes engagement, fosters open communication and focuses on practical solutions. We’ll also amplify recognition programs and promote a values-driven culture that celebrates and supports everyone.. Foster a culture of accountability: Accountability means showing up for each other, keeping our word and standing behind our commitments. It starts with our leaders and extends to every member of our team. It also means supporting our people by providing the tools, skills and training they need to deliver exceptional patient care.. Expand opportunities for learning and growth: At The THE_HOSPITAL, we know that our employees want and need the opportunity for learning and growth. The SPARQ strategic plan includes activities to enhance learning, training and professional development at all levels, such as expanding leadership competencies.. Modernize people programs and systems: The programs and systems in place for our people will be renewed, refreshed and reimagined as part of the strategic plan. This includes many aspects of the employee experience, from optimizing our approach to scheduling and implementing new HR systems to reviewing benefits and wellness offerings.. Strengthen belonging, diversity and EDIIA initiatives: The SPARQ strategic plan prioritizes action, including training and investment in the Equity, Diversity, Indigeneity, Inclusion and Accessibility (EDIIA) committees. Establish an Indigenous, First Nations and Inuit advisory circle to develop an action plan in response to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission of Canada.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses primarily on improving the work environment, employee wellness, and learning opportunities, reflecting workforce sustainability, and it also touches on fostering a culture of accountability and belonging, aligning with organizational culture and governance.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,The Le Royal,651
651,The Le Royal,Access,"Access. Break down the barriers to mental illness and addiction care and provide the highest quality and timely treatment for more patients.. Define our place in the system: The THE_HOSPITAL will clarify care pathways. Working with our clinical leaders, we’ll balance specialized care with broad access to mental illness and addiction services. Data will inform these decisions, enabling us to understand today’s needs and anticipate future demand.. Implement patient-centred services: We will increase meaningful partnerships and programs within the community, including strengthening communication and coordination for inpatient, outpatient and transitioning patient care. This will include leveraging our size and scope to provide leadership and act as a catalyst for system development.. Increase community partnerships and programs: The THE_HOSPITAL will strengthen communication and coordination across inpatient, outpatient and transitional care to better support patients at every stage of their journey. This includes being a strong presence at key planning tables, including those focused on housing, emergency services and mental illness and addiction services in community settings, to build on the strengths of each partner, foster collaboration and avoid duplication of efforts.. Focus on timely access and seamless flow: The THE_HOSPITAL will use access indicators to become more responsive to patient needs. We will also leverage digital solutions, such as virtual care, to make it easier for people to connect with the support they need. In addition, we will streamline referral management processes to improve the flow of patients into the right services, reducing wait times and enhancing the overall patient experience. This includes introducing an on-site pharmacy to provide easier and faster access to medications and better coordination of care between pharmacists and other healthcare professionals.. Meet the needs of diverse and marginalized people: The THE_HOSPITAL will use data to identify disparities in care and inform our resourcing decisions. Working collaboratively with community partners, we will co-design solutions that improve access and support for marginalized and underserved groups.",ACCESS & CAPACITY,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on breaking down barriers to access, improving timely treatment, and addressing the needs of diverse and marginalized populations.",Access & Capacity,Access & Capacity,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,The Le Royal,651
651,The Le Royal,Research,"Research. Integrate data-driven learning into care and accelerate the translation of discoveries into practice.. Focus on distinct research and specialty areas: The THE_HOSPITAL will build strength in research areas like depression, anxiety, addiction and trauma. This means investing in recruiting and developing researchers with deep expertise to fuel innovation and improve patient outcomes.. Become a rapid learning health system: The THE_HOSPITAL will build a learning culture where evidence drives improvements in care. Through training, career pathways, academic partnerships and learning events, we will create more opportunities for our research teams to learn, grow and apply new knowledge, ensuring that research and innovation translate quickly into better outcomes. We’ll also combine data interoperability with artificial intelligence to accelerate clinical insights and decision-making.. Reduce the gap between discovery and impact: The THE_HOSPITAL will strengthen research capacity and expand clinical trials while improving how we mobilize knowledge into practice. We will increase the involvement of patients, families and our community in the research process and build our ability to develop evidence-based policies that shape all aspects of mental health. These efforts will help ensure that what we learn translates into real-world improvements faster.. Become a globally renowned academic hospital for research: The THE_HOSPITAL will strengthen its reputation as a leader in mental illness and addiction research by increasing awareness of our work and expanding research partnerships. We will become a first-line validation site and early adopter of new tools and methodologies for diagnosis and treatment, helping to shape the future of mental illness and addiction care, here and around the world.. Redesign academic portfolio to strengthen internal oversight and external partnerships: The THE_HOSPITAL will renew its focus on training and professional development by addressing gaps and ensuring that learning can be applied in practice. We will establish an internal academic committee to provide stronger oversight and coordination, while also deepening partnerships with academic institutions in postgraduate medical education, nursing and graduate studies. These efforts will support a more connected and supportive academic environment that fuels continuous learning and innovation.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text heavily focuses on research activities, integrating research into care, and academic partnerships, with a mention of using AI to accelerate clinical insights.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,The Le Royal,651
651,The Le Royal,Quality,"Quality. Integrate evidence-based care and innovation to promote and enhance client and patient experience and outcomes at both the individual and system levels.. Modernize our medical leadership model: The THE_HOSPITAL will adopt the medical leadership model recommended by a 2025 review, which will include a Chief of Staff, a Senior Medical Officer, and additional senior medical leadership roles to support and strengthen this structure.. Foster a person, family and community-centred approach to care: The THE_HOSPITAL is committed to improving how we listen, communicate and learn from those we serve. By strengthening communication at every stage of care, we aim to ensure patients and their families feel heard, respected and included in decisions that affect them. These patient-centred best practices will be standardized across The THE_HOSPITAL to ensure a consistent, high-quality experience for everyone.: We will also support staff in deepening their understanding of the patient experience and why it matters — strengthening our culture of empathy, partnership and respect. This approach will be grounded in the principles of Equity, Diversity, Inclusion, Indigeneity and Accessibility — not as add-ons, but as essential elements in creating a care experience where everyone feels safe, seen and supported.. Encourage interdisciplinary collaboration: Mental illness and addiction outcomes improve when we work together. The THE_HOSPITAL will strengthen collaboration across roles and teams at every stage of the patient journey — from clinical staff and front-line managers to inpatient and community care providers. By breaking down silos and building stronger connections, we can deliver more coordinated, compassionate care that truly supports the whole person.. Implement a comprehensive framework for patient safety and person-centred care: The THE_HOSPITAL will draw on key frameworks to strengthen patient safety and person-centred care, and also adopt relevant national and provincial standards. These frameworks will inspire our practices, helping us create safer, more responsive and more compassionate care environments for everyone we serve.. Measure outcomes and improve evaluation: The THE_HOSPITAL will develop reports and dashboards to track progress toward our goals, from hospital operations and patient outcomes to the employee experience. By measuring what matters, we can make informed decisions, identify areas for improvement and ensure accountability as we work toward lasting, meaningful change.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on enhancing patient experience, outcomes, safety, and person-centered care, while also addressing organizational structure and leadership to support these goals.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,The Le Royal,651
653,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,System Integration,"System Integration. THE_HOSPITAL believes that each organization has strength and capacity to provide excellent services and by working together, actively removing barriers, we can respond to people's holistic needs timely, we can prevent people needing help falling through the cracks, and we can uphold a world-class healthcare system for all.. * Policies, processes, procurement, equipment, supplies are reviewed and streamlined for both sites.: * Appropriate committees are formed and sustained to support standardization (eg. product evaluation, signage).: * Forum that gets partners together (eg. Health huddle) are supported / co-established.: * Common platforms such as policies, Meditech Expanse, bulk purchasing, bulk subscriptions are explored with partners.: * Explore ways to collaborate meaningfully, creating seamless pathways in providing care.: * Team members are actively supported in representing THE_HOSPITAL at regional committees and leading the creation of such committees if not existing (eg. environmental, maintenance).: * An up to date resource map that can support recruitment and retention is made available.: * Representation at meetings and events are active and consistent.: * TAOHT / CDOHT maturation is fully supported through sharing of THE_HOSPITAL resources.: * Opportunities toward service integration that can better serve our communities are actively pursued.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,Focus is on collaboration and removing barriers to improve efficiency and create seamless care pathways within the healthcare system.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,NA,TRUE,2,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE; BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH,653
653,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,People Centered-Care,"People Centered-Care. THE_HOSPITAL believes that the system should work for the people and not the people trying to figure out how to navigate the complex system. We see individuals as a whole person, with worth and dignity, and are deserving of the best care possible at the right place, the right time, the right provider, and as close to home as possible.. * Assessment for baseline SWOT is completed and an EDI work plan is established.: * EDI training made accessible to all staff and physicians.: * Strengthened services for Francophone, Indigenous citizens, and other marginalized groups.: * Integrated principles in THE_HOSPITAL culture.: * Baseline data and comprehensive indicators are collected and utilized for QI.: * Improved access and wait time, data regularly monitored to gauge strategies that effectively advance targets.: * Incidents and feedback are used to make improvements: * Patient safety is prioritized by tracking data and creating system improvements to eliminate risks involving medication, falls, hospital acquired infections, and other preventable safety incidents.: * A system of innovation is established where everyone has a chance to share ideas, participate, learn, and lead innovative practices / programs.: * Strategic Planning with PEP conducted to identify strategies that fully incorporate patients and families' voices in THE_HOSPITAL processes.: * Patients' and families' voices are integrated in THE_HOSPITAL processes and feedback is actively solicited.: * Committees / Groups / Meetings are streamlined across the organization for efficiency and strategic use of time towards accomplishing organizational goals: * Improved access to Mental Health, spiritual and cultural support including language services: * Improved access to follow-up care post-discharge and systems navigation for: * Relentless pursuit of best practices and out of the box thinking to improve care and access.: * Embed partnership-based culture when determining support for individuals and families: * Gaps are identified and programs evaluated for continuous effectiveness: * Implement quality improvement systems such as mapping out patients' journeys to identify barriers, quality case reviews, and creating comprehensive scorecards.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"This focuses on providing excellent and equitable patient care by integrating patient voices, improving access for marginalized groups, and implementing quality improvement systems.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,NA,TRUE,2,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE; BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH,653
653,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,Infrastructure,"Infrastructure. In order to provide the best care possible, THE_HOSPITAL believes in having the right infrastructure to support the work that we do - physical, technological, data, equipment, and processes. We believe in proactive maintenance and advocacy to maintain the resources that are needed to provide the best care possible. Continuous quality improvement is embedded in everything that we do.. * Average satisfaction rating or higher from staff and physician regarding their transition to Expanse experience.: * Staff supported 24/7 during Go Live date and at least 6 months post Go Live.: * Workflow optimization post Go-Live: * Electronic Scheduling system implemented in 2025: * Other opportunities to automate are explored, existing systems merged and optimized: * ED/ICU: Ministry-funded application submitted, project completed up to pre-tender stage.: * Fund-Raising expertise leveraged and fund-raising plan implemented.: * Projects are prioritized and advanced through for Ministry and public support: * Strengthened Foundation support and optimization: * Policies / frameworks are created: communication, partner engagement, decision-making, capital project approval, procurement.: * Regular operations review, data access: * CNIB Guidelines incorporated in all documents and electronic sites.: * Accessibility Framework reviewed and approved.: * Accessibility assessment completed and projects based on risks and resources are prioritized.: * Accessibility committee established with strong patient and frontline participation.: * Ongoing assessments to measure progress and ensure responsiveness to people's needs.: * Evidence in people culture, resource management, adaptive processes, strong leadership and partnership.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on physical infrastructure, technological infrastructure (Expanse, Electronic Scheduling), and improvements to processes and accessibility.",Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,NA,TRUE,2,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE; BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH,653
653,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,Health And Human Resources,"Health And Human Resources. The backbone of our services is our people. Our employees, our leaders, our physicians, our partners, our volunteers. Our people's welfare is our priority. THE_HOSPITAL believes in fair and equitable treatment, in providing a safe and welcoming work environment where people thrive and pursue continuous growth, and where people are valued.. * HR Strategy launched and reviewed annually or as needed. The strategy includes recruitment and retention strategies, talent management, succession,: * A formal Professional Development Program including promotion of leadership competencies and mentorship, and regular performance appraisals are developed and sustained: * Scopes of practice are optimized: * Robust recognition system for contributions and stellar value-based attributes is implemented: * Employee and physician mental health are supported timely.: * Wellness initiatives and safety are prioritized.: * Critical Incident Stress Debriefing available 24/7: * Ergonomics assessment and equipment are available to all staff: * Incidents and near misses are addressed with risks identified mitigated and safety groups / committees established.: * Policies and expectations are established and clearly communicated.: * Fair procedural processes are adhered to as per collective agreements and organizational policies: * Volunteer Program is created / implemented with clearly outlined contributions and recognitions: * Physicians / NPs have access to tools and training that enhance clinical leadership, excellent people-centered care, and ground-breaking initiatives specifically responding to the needs in the North.: * Standard processes are established that support consistency, fairness, and equitability: * Recognition and incentive programs are implemented.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on employee welfare, recruitment, retention, development, recognition, and a safe/welcoming work environment, reflecting both workforce sustainability and organizational culture/governance.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,NA,TRUE,2,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE; BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH,653
653,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,Communication,"Communication. The heart of what we do is dependent on the quality of our communication, THE_HOSPITAL believes in timely, responsive, transparent, and clear communication as the vehicle to get our work done and to serve effectively. THE_HOSPITAL is committed to ongoing improvement and to ensuring that our people, our community members, our partners, are well-informed and proactively engaged with our organization.. * The communication framework established include principles, strategies, processes, and THE_HOSPITAL tools that are being utilized to communicate: * Multiple ways of communicating internally are utilized (Town halls, newsletters, mass messaging for emergency and non-emergency announcements, huddle boards, feedback boards, emails): * Intranet and a document management system are set-up and well-utilized: * Effective communication is gauged based on feedback, surveys, and interpersonal connections: * Accomplishments / milestones are celebrated: * An operational “macro agenda” calendar is created and shared: * TAOHT and CDOHT are fully supported to maturity: * Regular participation in forums with partners that promote dialogue, focusing on improving the health of the communities we serve: * A variety of media is used to communicate and reach out to the general public (radio, newsprints, social media): * Regular community updates are shared: * Feedback / incident management policies and processes are re-established: * Employees, physicians, partners have a well-established system where they can provide ideas / feedback and are recognized for their contributions: * Patient / family communications are established for clear service navigation, expectations before, during, and after receiving services, understanding of resources available and opportunities for advocacy.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text emphasizes communication principles, strategies, and processes within the organization and with external partners, highlighting a focus on organizational culture and integration with OHTs and community members.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,NA,TRUE,2,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE; BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH,653
653,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,Fiscal Accountability,"Fiscal Accountability. THE_HOSPITAL believes in managing our resources effectively so we can continue to provide excellent services, we can continue to think outside the box, and we can continue to invest in the future of healthcare in our communities.. * Revenue generation streams are regularly identified and fully optimized (OH, federal, municipal, for profit): * Regular reconciliation of staffing / budget / resources / changes: * Contracts are actively managed and updated to ensure THE_HOSPITAL receives market value or better deals: * Revive fiscal advisory committee with representation as per legislation / by-laws, focusing on budget processes, transparent processes: * Product evaluation, Process committee, space committee, and other groups that can promote transparency, efficiency, and active staff participation are established: * Scorecard enhanced and shared appropriately: * Staff, physician, partners have opportunities to contribute to processes towards quality and efficiency: * Clear processes with clear accountabilities are established (requesting capital equipment, renovations, changes): * Clear reporting structures and accountabilities are adhered to.: * Processes that create bottlenecks are identified and actively eliminated: * Close partnerships between the governance and foundation boards are supported towards common gaols: * Streamline foundation goals and strategies with the organization's: * THE_HOSPITAL Foundation's presence in the community is reinforced: * Stronger connection with external sources of support (mines, private citizens, factories, rails) are nurtured: * THE_HOSPITAL has a balanced budget by 2029: * THE_HOSPITAL has a healthy capital reserve and funding application processes that allow for active maintenance and preservation of buildings and resources: * THE_HOSPITAL healthy cash flow ensures timely payments and ability to cover operational needs.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on managing resources effectively, optimizing revenue, budget reconciliation, and establishing clear processes for fiscal accountability, indicating a focus on financial sustainability and organizational governance.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,NA,TRUE,2,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE; BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH,653
951,William Osler Health System,Quality Excellence,"Quality Excellence. Relentlessly pursuing world-class, high-quality health care. • Deliver excellent care through an elevated patient experience that is co-designed to cultivate trust and confidence: • Embody evidence-based models of care to advance exemplary quality: • Exemplify Osler as an industry leader in providing safe and reliable health care.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on delivering excellent, evidence-based care and patient experience, reflecting a commitment to quality and the organization's values.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,William Osler Health System,951
951,William Osler Health System,Organizational Effectiveness,Organizational Effectiveness. Optimizing resources to provide effective health care for the communities we serve. • Enable capacity and transformation of health services aligned to population growth and patient needs: • Leverage technology and analytics capabilities to enhance operational efficiencies and advance patient care: • Drive value-based improvement and decision-making through strategic use of data and evidence.,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on optimizing resources and enhancing operational efficiencies, directly aligning with financial sustainability while also mentioning the advancement of patient care.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,William Osler Health System,951
951,William Osler Health System,People & Culture,"People & Culture. Inspiring a sense of belonging that supports people to be their best and do their best. • Advance our organizational culture to elevate a sense of belonging, pride, and trust: • Foster a learning culture that encourages curiosity, discovery and innovation: • Attract and retain the best talent for the organization and communities we serve.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on improving organizational culture, fostering a learning environment, and attracting/retaining talent.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,William Osler Health System,951
951,William Osler Health System,Health System Leadership,Health System Leadership. Leading and partnering to transform the health system for Osler’s communities and beyond. • Lead and advance integrated care through partnerships to ensure seamless care experiences: • Evolve and innovate models of care inspired by our communities' needs: • Advocate to ensure required resources to build capacity and advance integrated health care in collaboration with partners.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on leading and partnering to transform the health system and advance integrated care, also touching on evolving models of care which reflects organizational leadership.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,William Osler Health System,951
951,William Osler Health System,Research & Academics,"Research & Academics. Developing the health care providers and researchers of tomorrow. • Transform to an academic health centre, and expand research and teaching while further strengthening our connection with the communities we serve: • Pursue research that advances translation of discovery into practice to improve patient care, health outcomes and system performance: • Develop an exemplary clinical interprofessional educational experience for the future health care workforce.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text explicitly focuses on research and academic development, with an aim to improve patient care through translation of discovery into practice.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,William Osler Health System,951
952,Lakeridge Health,Improve Population Health,"Improve Population Health. Partner with primary care and other providers to promote prevention, health and wellness strategies that foster healthier communities.. • Develop a deep understanding of our diverse community needs to address disparities, promote equity and enrich quality of life: • Co-commit with our community and partners to a set of health measures to improve, to focus our collective efforts: • Each of our clinical programs will have population health measures which they will drive to improve – these will undoubtedly include secondary prevention measures for various chronic illnesses: • Strengthen community partnerships across the continuum of care to tailor a delivery network that supports optimal health: • Leverage innovative and cost-effective options to improve patient care including virtual care, digital engagement and technology innovation: • Collaborate with primary care and community partners to support people at home or in their community.",POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on improving population health through partnerships, addressing community needs and disparities, and implementing preventative measures, with a secondary emphasis on health equity.",Population & Community Health,Population & Community Health,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Lakeridge Health,952
952,Lakeridge Health,Commitment To Individual Health Care,"Commitment To Individual Health Care. Continuously improve delivery of high quality care and services in acute, home and community settings.. • Evolve as a leading provider of acute health services, focused on the best outcomes for people in our communities: • Establish new services and models of care that are responsive to emerging patient needs: • Encourage, empower and enable patients and their families to be true partners in their care: • Invest in innovative health care models and virtual care opportunities to support people to safely and effectively manage disease and chronic conditions at home or in their community: • Improve the overall experience of care (quality and patient satisfaction).",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The focus is on improving quality of care, patient experience, and managing chronic conditions in the community.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Lakeridge Health,952
952,Lakeridge Health,Create An Integrated System Of Care,"Create An Integrated System Of Care. Lead the transformation to a connected and integrated system of care in Durham Region.. • Use data, evidence and best practices to understand the needs of the community and to support decision-making, health equity and cost reduction: • Excel as an economic engine that drives prosperity in our region through expanded academic, research and post-secondary relationships: • Pursue non-traditional partnerships within and beyond the health care sector to extend service to more people at a better value: • Enhance supports for sustainable transitions across the system through strong linkages with community partners: • Continue to plan and deliver services close to patients’ homes through the power of our strong regional network and our focus on rural health: • Ensure we are delivering our core services in a responsible and fiscally sustainable way.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on building an integrated system of care and highlights the importance of data, community needs, health equity, partnerships, and system transitions.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Lakeridge Health,952
952,Lakeridge Health,Be A Workplace Of Choice,"Be A Workplace Of Choice. Through a dedicated focus on team health, wellness, safety and wellbeing that supports a high-performing, adaptable and enjoyable workplace environment.. • Create a culture that inspires exploration, innovation and excellence in everything we do: • Foster an inclusive, healthy work environment where people feel safe, valued and recognized for their individual and shared achievements: • Enable interprofessional teams where people work to their full scope to deliver high quality care, meaningful outcomes and continuous improvement: • Become an workplace of choice that attracts, appreciates and retains highly dedicated, accountable people who reflect our community, deliver care with kindness, and execute with passion, professionalism and integrity.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on creating a positive and supportive workplace environment that attracts, retains, and values employees, which falls under workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Lakeridge Health,952
953,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,Personalized & Precise Treatments,"Personalized & Precise Treatments. Drive innovation in personalized and precise treatments by leveraging cutting-edge technology, advanced techniques, and novel therapies to improve patient outcomes, reduce side effects, and minimize hospital visits.. • Expand capacity to expedite innovations from 'idea' to 'adoption', collaborating with partners to drive commercialization: • Strengthen leadership in molecular and image-guided diagnostics and therapeutics: • Build capacity to support and advance clinical trials: • Enhance the profile of clinical trials and improve accessibility to patients, families and caregivers.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS","The focus is on driving innovation in treatments through technology and expanding capacity for clinical trials, indicating a blend of digital health and research.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,953
953,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,Integrated Care,"Integrated Care. Lead system transformation with partners to improve access in the areas of primary, community and specialized care.. • Lead transformative system-wide efforts to shape the future of health care across Ontario: • Drive excellence in care through strategic joint ventures and partnerships: • Evolve care models using integrated, patient-centered approaches: • Lead innovative and proactive approaches to optimize capacity and flow.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The focus is on system transformation through partnerships to improve access to care, indicating integration and a proactive approach to optimize capacity and flow.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,953
953,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,Quality & Patient Experience,"Quality & Patient Experience. Exceed care expectations by delivering compassionate patient experiences and achieving the best care outcomes.. • Measure and improve care, using quality frameworks and system comparators, to drive local excellence: • Leverage digital tools and processes to achieve the highest quality and safety standards: • Incorporate patient and family feedback to elevate compassion and high quality care: • Engage and empower patients and families to co-design personalized experiences.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on improving care quality and patient experience through compassionate care and achieving best outcomes, supported by digital tools and patient feedback.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,953
953,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,Thriving People And Teams,"Thriving People And Teams. Strengthen Team THE_HOSPITAL by cultivating leadership that drives care, improves outcomes, and advances innovations to turn challenges into opportunities.. • Support growth through professional and leadership development opportunities: • Lead innovative workforce models and team-based approaches to drive system impact: • Lead in leveraging Augmented Reality (AR) and Virtual Reality (VR) technologies to accelerate learning and advance skill development: • Strengthen and expand partnerships to drive new education and training models.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on strengthening the team through leadership, professional development, innovative workforce models, and leveraging AR/VR for learning and skill development, aligning with workforce sustainability and digital innovation.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,953
953,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,Social Responsibility,"Social Responsibility. Drive positive change that promotes equitable access to care that improves health outcomes, fosters an inclusive patient experience and workplace, and reduces environmental impact.. • Pursue the eradication of health inequity for the patients and families we serve: • Nurture a culture of inclusion and belonging, and increase diversity in leadership and health professionals: • Adopt environmentally sustainable infrastructure practices: • Strengthen environmental stewardship by optimizing resource use and reducing waste.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This text emphasizes equitable access, inclusion, diversity, and environmental stewardship, which align with health equity, organizational culture, and social responsibility.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,953
953,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,Digital Health & Artificial Intelligence,"Digital Health & Artificial Intelligence. Enabled by THE_HOSPITAL’s new Health Information System (HIS), use digital technologies and analytics to enhance care for Ontarians.. • Integrate and expand the HIS and digital tools to enhance care delivery and seamless information sharing across the health system: • Advance the development and adoption of AI to create a technologically advanced health system: • Enhance data and analytic capabilities to foster a data-driven, and accelerate research: • Leverage interconnected data to provide safer care.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The focus is on using digital tools, AI, and the HIS system to improve care and integrate information sharing across the health system.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,953
953,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,Growth & Investment,Growth & Investment. Grow and diversify our revenue streams to ensure sustainable operations to advance health care innovation and to enable infrastructure development for THE_HOSPITAL to achieve its vision to invent the future of health care.. • Expand capacity of partnership with the THE_HOSPITAL Foundation to grow philanthropic funds: • Business development and commercialization: • Unlock our master plan with the development of the new Critical Care Centre: • Continue to renew our aged infrastructure to continue to deliver exceptional care.,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text discusses growing revenue streams for sustainable operations, infrastructure development, and renewing aged infrastructure.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sunnybrook HEALTH SCIENCES CENTRE,953
955,Grey Bruce Health Services,Excellence In Care,Excellence In Care. Delivering patient-centred care that advances the health of our communities.. • We will earn and maintain trust with our patients and their families: • We will provide excellent customer service: • We will understand and meet the needs of our diverse and evolving communities: • We will align service delivery with best practices in healthcare.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on patient-centered care, customer service, and aligning service delivery with best practices, suggesting a focus on quality and organizational values.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Grey Bruce Health Services,955
955,Grey Bruce Health Services,A Great Place To Work,"A Great Place To Work. Recognition as a place where people want to work and build their careers.. • We will promote our culture of continuous improvement: • We will invest in our staff, physicians, and volunteers by providing opportunities for continuing education and growth: • We will facilitate a learning environment to attract new talent: • We will apply inclusivity, diversity and equity principles to organizational standards and practices.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"Focuses on attracting, retaining, and investing in staff while fostering a culture of continuous improvement and inclusivity.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Grey Bruce Health Services,955
955,Grey Bruce Health Services,Innovation And System Leadership,"Innovation And System Leadership. Turning ideas into patient-centred solutions through investment, creativity and empowering partners.. • We will be courageous in our approach and demonstrate a willingness to take smart risks: • We will celebrate our wins and encourage eachother to improve: • We will leverage technology to serve our patients better: • We will co-design patient-centred care models with our patients, families, and partners.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text emphasizes leveraging technology for patient care and co-designing care models with partners, highlighting both digital innovation and system integration.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Grey Bruce Health Services,955
955,Grey Bruce Health Services,Intentional Partnerships,"Intentional Partnerships. Taking ownership of our role as a regional network that can be trusted to engage, listen and partner.. • We will improve communication to support patients in navigating the healthcare system: • We will acknowledge, respect and collaborate with with our diverse communities to learn and grow together: • We will value and collaborate with our academic partners in the development of future healthcare talent: • We will prioritize partnerships that already exist and be purposeful with our engagement.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text emphasizes building partnerships within the healthcare system and with diverse communities, highlighting both integration and a commitment to equitable collaboration.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Grey Bruce Health Services,955
958,The Ottawa Hospital,Enrich The Quality Of Care For Patients,Enrich The Quality Of Care For Patients. We will help grow a healthy system based on integrated care for patients across our network of health and social partners.. 1. Strategic priority – Enhance our culture of patient partnered-care and meaningful engagement – Empower patients and their care partners as active participants in the care that we provide and entrust everyone working at THE_HOSPITAL with providing the best possible patient experience.: 2. Strategic priority – Improve access to care for all patients – Spearhead the development of new and innovative approaches to the delivery of care and leverage local partnerships to ensure our patients have access to the care they need when they need it.: 3. Strategic priority - Expand partnerships across the care continuum – Build a strong integrated system for regional health care delivery in collaboration with a wide range of partners to address the needs of the communities we serve.: 4. Strategic priority – Drive the digital evolution in healthcare- Enhance health outcomes for the populations we serve through safe automation of care and business processes.: 5. Strategic priority – Expand infrastructure development and modernization – Develop and maintain world class infrastructure to support the needs of our community and advance health care delivery.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,The text focuses on enhancing the quality of care for patients through patient engagement and improving access through partnerships and integrated care.,Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,The Ottawa Hospital,958
958,The Ottawa Hospital,Ignite The Power Of People,"Ignite The Power Of People. Foster an environment that inspires people, so they are filled with pride, affinity, and accomplishment at work.. 6. Strategic priority – Create leaders of tomorrow – Develop human-centered leaders that live THE_HOSPITAL values and vision by actively engaging staff, physicians and volunteers in development and supporting them through continuing education, learning and mentorship.: 7. Strategic priority – Advance workforce planning and sustainability – Drive the future of healthcare delivery through innovative models that support high functioning team members to work to their full potential.: 8. Strategic priority – Support engagement and well-being to maintain a healthy workforce– Build an inspiring, engaging, and safe environment where all team members can connect to the purpose and meaning of their work aligned to THE_HOSPITAL vision of caring for people like you would for a loved one.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on creating a positive work environment, developing leaders, and supporting workforce planning and well-being.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,The Ottawa Hospital,958
958,The Ottawa Hospital,Nurture Our Social Responsibility,"Nurture Our Social Responsibility. Everything we do in healthcare is engrained in a profound social responsibility to our community. We will provide leadership in navigating a complex health system to improve the health of our diverse population and contribute to a healthier planet for all.. 9. Strategic priority – Advance Indigenous engagement – Continue on our journey to reconciliation to address the systemic racism, discrimination, and inequities pervasive in the healthcare system and advance a culture of belonging so everyone has equitable access, without discrimination, to safe healthcare that respects Indigenous People's traditional and living knowledge in all aspects of their health.: 10. Strategic priority – Advance Equity, Diversity, Inclusion and Accessibility – Address the systemic racism, discrimination, and inequities pervasive in the health care system and advance a culture of belonging for everyone where we foster accessibility, equity, diversity and inclusion that reflects the people we serve.: 11. Strategic priority – Lead environmental stewardship in healthcare- Become a leader in sustainable healthcare, applying principles of planetary health to improve the well-being of our patients, our community and contribute positively to a healthier planet.: 12. Strategic priority – Ensure financially responsible stewardship and sustainability – Preserve financial strength and flexibility to enable world class care through strategic financial planning and partnerships that support economic opportunities.: 13. Strategic priority – Harness community support – Acknowledge the trust and endorsement of a generous community and together with TOHF, build on this spirit of philanthropy and voluntarism to ensure that our community continues to have access to world-class care.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The text focuses on addressing systemic racism, discrimination, inequities, improving the health of a diverse population, Indigenous engagement, environmental stewardship, and community support.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,The Ottawa Hospital,958
958,The Ottawa Hospital,Accelerate Discovery,"Accelerate Discovery. Pursue impactful, cutting-edge research to pioneer new treatments and tools that benefit patients and elevate further our leadership role in research and education globally.. 14. Strategic priority – Create hope for patients through a commitment to leading edge research – Give our patients and their loved ones new hope through research that is making tomorrow's health care possible today by focusing on breakthroughs by design and practice-changing research.: 15. Strategic priority- Advance multidisciplinary education – Train the next generation of health professionals through excellence in multidisciplinary team-based learning, learner experience and knowledge dissemination in collaboration with our educational partners.: 16. Strategic priority – Lead the innovation platform – Lead innovation in health care while advancing Ottawa as a thriving innovation ecosystem.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on research, education, and leading innovation in healthcare, which aligns with both the Research and Digital Health themes.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,The Ottawa Hospital,958
959,Health Sciences North,Providing Quality People-Centred Care,"Providing Quality People-Centred Care. Putting patients and families at the centre of all we do and working together to provide exceptional care.. - Advance hospital expansion plans to improve access to acute, emergency, pediatric, mental health and addictions care.: - Design models of care that improve healthcare experiences for patients and families to meet their goals. We will make the healthcare system easier to navigate and promote seamless care transitions by working closely with community partners.: - Be leaders in making healthcare safer for everyone with a focus on continuous quality improvement.: - Transform surgical care in Northeastern Ontario by investing in state-of-the-art tools, including a robotics program and hybrid operating room.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text emphasizes patient-centered care, improved healthcare experiences, and expansion plans to improve access to various types of care.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Health Sciences North,959
959,Health Sciences North,Empowering Human Potential,"Empowering Human Potential. Creating an environment where the talented and dedicated people of Team THE_HOSPITAL can thrive and be celebrated.. - Proactively attract, recruit, retain and invest in a skilled workforce that reflects and meets the needs of the diverse communities we serve to address workforce shortages.: - Build a unified culture focused on wellness, collaboration and breaking down silos to prioritize strategic objectives.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on attracting, retaining, and investing in a skilled workforce while also building a unified and collaborative culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Health Sciences North,959
959,Health Sciences North,Advancing Equity Through Social Accountability,"Advancing Equity Through Social Accountability. Addressing health equity gaps by promoting an inclusive environment free of racism, discrimination and all forms of bias.. - Continuously engage with Indigenous communities and Indigenous health organizations to strengthen relationships and develop pathways that increase availability and access to culturally safe and wholistic care. The Indigenous Health Advisory Council and the Calls to Action of the Truth and Reconciliation Commission Report will guide this work.: - Build cultural competency and humility to strengthen our ability to provide exceptional care that is safe, equitable, and free of racism and discrimination for all.: - Enhance our active offer of French language services to provide people with communication and services in their preferred official language.: - Improve access to mental health services across the region, including emergency mental health and addictions care.: - Meet the growing needs of the older adult population by expanding services focused on best practices and dignified care to support aging in the right place.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The text focuses on addressing health equity gaps, engaging with Indigenous communities, and improving access to mental health services and elder care, aligning with both health equity and population health.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Health Sciences North,959
959,Health Sciences North,Achieving Healthcare Excellence Through Education And Research,"Achieving Healthcare Excellence Through Education And Research. Impactful research and education enables us to develop collaborative healthcare solutions, paving the way for a healthier North.. - Collaborate with academic, healthcare, and community organizations to establish an Academic Health Sciences Network. These partnerships will unlock ground-breaking research and transformative educational opportunities, driving healthcare innovation for the North and making a lasting impact on the global stage.: - Invest in the integration of research activities throughout THE_HOSPITAL to create a thriving environment for research opportunities that helps us understand people's health needs and improves health outcomes.: - Develop a culture of education to provide learning and teaching experiences that are inclusive, accessible, safe, and welcoming to promote professional development, recruitment and retention.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on research and education, collaboration with academic and community organizations, and creating a research-friendly environment.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Health Sciences North,959
959,Health Sciences North,Strengthening Organizational Sustainability,"Strengthening Organizational Sustainability. A focus on sustainability will enable us to be here when people need us the most – now and into the future.. - Achieve financial strength by driving efficiency, instilling a culture of long-term planning and advocating for equitable funding.: - Improve health outcomes and healthcare worker experiences by expanding Information Technology infrastructure and enabling the safe and ethical use of emerging technologies including Artificial Intelligence.: - Identify eco-friendly practices and opportunities to reduce our carbon footprint.: - Cultivate a culture of philanthropy throughout THE_HOSPITAL and the communities we serve, to inspire giving that fuels advancements in care and research, transforming the lives of those who depend on us.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on achieving financial strength through efficiency and equitable funding, while also highlighting the expansion of IT infrastructure and the use of AI, aligning with financial sustainability and digital health respectively.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Health Sciences North,959
961,UNIVERSITY OF OTTAWA HEART INSTITUTE / INSTITUT DE CARDIOLOGIE DE L'UNIVERSITÉ D'OTTAWA,Goal One,"Goal One. Catalyze impactful research by creating and supporting unique Innovation Hubs of interdisciplinary research teams. **ATHEROSCLEROSIS AND CARDIOMETABOLIC DISEASES**: • Understanding triggers of atherosclerosis and cardiometabolic diseases including diabetes: • Biomarkers for risk prediction and personalized pharmacogenomics: • Personalizing intervention strategies and innovative devices and tools (including imaging). **ARRHYTHMIAS**: • Causes of atrial fibrillation and reversibility: • Early detection and proper classification: • Risk prediction rules/devices and personalizing treatment strategies e.g., 4D molecular imaging: • Prevention strategies including the impact of obesity and lifestyle interventions. **HEART FAILURE**: • Improved classification and understanding of major forms of heart failure (HF): • Novel biomarkers and treatment targets: • Personalized medicine through innovative treatment strategies and molecular imaging: • Early detection and treatment of HF, including indigenous populations and new tools: • Cardiac transplant vasculopathy. **VALVULAR HEART DISEASE**: • How valvular diseases develop: • Screening for familial cases: • Personalized risk stratification for best disease management and outcomes: • Innovative surgical and transcatheter therapies. **BRAIN AND HEART**: • Impact of mental illness on CV Disease: • Brain and heart axis in drug use/abuse: • Microvascular disease in stroke, dementia and cognitive impairment: • Rhythm synchrony and dyssynchrony bewteen brain and heart: • Psychological and behavioural interventions to improve mental and CV health. **DISCOVERY TO TRANSLATIONAL INNOVATIONS**: • Innovative imaging ligands and ultra high-resolution molecular imaging: • Genome editing to interrogate impact of a gene target: • Reprogrammed human stem cells and 3D organoid models of human disease: • Biomaterials, nanobiofilms and smart delivery vehicles for novel diagnostics and therapeutics. **PRECISION MEDICINE**: • Next generation ‘omics’ technologies to validate novel biomarkers: • Integrated datasets and tailored decision algorithms: • Imaging technology to improve patient outcomes: • Incorporation of precision medicine into existing frameworks of care. **BIG DATA AND ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE**: • Linked clinical databases, through the THE_HOSPITAL CardioCore platform and electronic medical records: • Linkage to external administrative databases such as the Institute of Clinical Evaluative Sciences. **HEALTHY DIVERSE POPULATIONS**: • Incorporating sex- and gender effects in all research activities: • Incentivizing and promoting research on indigenous populations.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"This goal focuses on impactful research through Innovation Hubs, covering areas like atherosclerosis, arrhythmias, heart failure, valvular heart disease, and brain-heart connections, incorporating precision medicine, big data, AI, and initiatives for healthy diverse populations, which indicates the combination of both research and digital health.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNIVERSITY OF OTTAWA HEART INSTITUTE / INSTITUT DE CARDIOLOGIE DE L'UNIVERSITÉ D'OTTAWA,961
961,UNIVERSITY OF OTTAWA HEART INSTITUTE / INSTITUT DE CARDIOLOGIE DE L'UNIVERSITÉ D'OTTAWA,Goal Two,Goal Two. Support and enhance our fundamental and translational research enterprise. • Increase Peer Reviewed Funding: • Sustain Equipment & Infrastructure: • Recruit High Caliber Trainees: • Maintain Fundamental Science Capacity.,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"This goal focuses on increasing research funding, sustaining research equipment/infrastructure, and recruiting trainees, all pointing to research and academic endeavors, with a secondary consideration for the physical resources needed for research.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNIVERSITY OF OTTAWA HEART INSTITUTE / INSTITUT DE CARDIOLOGIE DE L'UNIVERSITÉ D'OTTAWA,961
961,UNIVERSITY OF OTTAWA HEART INSTITUTE / INSTITUT DE CARDIOLOGIE DE L'UNIVERSITÉ D'OTTAWA,Goal Three,Goal Three. Catalyse innovation and excellence in clinical research. • Recognition of the value of clinical research: • Innovative research to address clinical problems: • Enhance infrastructure to facilitate clinical research: • Patient Engagement.,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"This goal focuses on promoting clinical research, enhancing research infrastructure, and fostering innovation in addressing clinical problems, pointing towards research and potential use of technology for innovation.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNIVERSITY OF OTTAWA HEART INSTITUTE / INSTITUT DE CARDIOLOGIE DE L'UNIVERSITÉ D'OTTAWA,961
961,UNIVERSITY OF OTTAWA HEART INSTITUTE / INSTITUT DE CARDIOLOGIE DE L'UNIVERSITÉ D'OTTAWA,Goal Four,Goal Four. Build cross-cutting initiatives to facilitate research. • Regional Partnership: • Research Promotion and Communications: • Recruit High Caliber Trainees: • Grant Application Support: • Research Integrity: • Industry Engagement: • Patient Engagement.,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"This goal explicitly focuses on building research capacity through partnerships, recruitment, and support, indicating research and integration are the primary areas.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNIVERSITY OF OTTAWA HEART INSTITUTE / INSTITUT DE CARDIOLOGIE DE L'UNIVERSITÉ D'OTTAWA,961
962,Niagara Health,Putting People First,"Putting People First. People are the basis of everything we do at the hospital — both patients and our team members. Caring for patients is the reason the hospital exists. Connecting with our community and building partnerships with other organizations serving our patients help us deliver better care. Nothing can happen without our team.. Strengthening our patient-centred culture: Decisions will be made to optimize patient experience and patient care with initiatives across all levels of the organization being co-designed with patient partners. We will also work with specific patient populations, beginning with Indigenous partners, to improve care.. Building an inclusive and collaborative workplace: Every team member should feel supported, valued and engaged, understanding how their individual role contributes to the broader vision and culture of the hospital. Programs, policies and decisions at the hospital will be designed to reflect and enhance diversity, equity and inclusion using the Ontario Health Equity, Inclusion, Diversity and Anti-Racism Framework.. Equipping our team members with the tools for success: Programs will be implemented to support the mental health and wellness of all team members. We will provide greater access to education and training opportunities for growth and development.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text emphasizes patient-centered care, experience, and the importance of a supportive and inclusive environment for healthcare workers, addressing both patient care quality and workforce well-being.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Niagara Health,962
962,Niagara Health,Delivering Safe And Quality Care,"Delivering Safe And Quality Care. Our purpose is clear that every person who comes to the hospital should receive the best care, every time. We must use all resources available to us to ensure people can access hospital services when they need them, that these services and experiences are consistent, and that we are always striving to do better.. Improving how patients move across the hospital: Drawing on sector best practices, we will improve our ability to serve people when they need it and enhance how patients access services. We will also focus on creating seamless care for patients as they move in and out of our hospitals.. Integrating data and research: As we implement our new hospital information system, we will apply the data and analytics generated to help us make better decisions. We will embed research into our work, using the outcomes to enhance the care we provide.. Embedding continuous quality improvement: the hospital will build continuous quality improvement capacity and capability across the organization. We will standardize our care and empower our team to deliver the best care to our patients.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text focuses on delivering the best and safest care to patients, improving patient flow, and enhancing access to services, all of which fall under patient care excellence and access & capacity.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Niagara Health,962
962,Niagara Health,Transforming How We Work,"Transforming How We Work. As the needs of the hospital’s patients, community and team members change, we must transform how we work. We will become one truly regional system, functioning seamlessly across sites. We are updating our physical structures, including building a new hospital, but we are also changing how we organize ourselves and how we use technology to work together and to serve our patients.. Refining our regional model: As we open the new South Niagara Site, we will shift how and where we work to function as one team serving the entire Niagara region. Patients will know they will get the same standard of care across all of the hospital.. Implementing interprofessional team best practices: To best use the capacity of our team members and deliver care as efficiently as possible, we will implement best practices for how we set up our teams and how each team member performs in their scope of practice.. Enhancing and leveraging technology: We will use technology to enhance how we communicate across teams and with our patients, offering new options for how we provide care virtually.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The focus is on becoming one regional system, leveraging technology for communication and virtual care, and implementing interprofessional teams.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Niagara Health,962
963,Wellington Health Care Alliance,"Together, Empowering A Meaningful Patient Journey","Together, Empowering A Meaningful Patient Journey. NF. • Growing relationships with our patients and families, involving them in care and operational decision-making: • Cultivating quality, yielding excellent care: • Transforming how we collect and use information to drive quality and support the patient journey.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on patient and family involvement in care decisions, quality improvement, and using data to improve the patient journey, indicating patient care excellence and a focus on organizational values.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Wellington Health Care Alliance,963
963,Wellington Health Care Alliance,"Together, Advancing A Culture Of Team Wellness","Together, Advancing A Culture Of Team Wellness. NF. • Fostering a team engaged in quality care: • Promoting and supporting continuous growth, empowering problem-solvers in developing creative solutions: • Cultivating the leaders of the future.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on fostering team wellness, promoting growth, and cultivating future leaders, indicating workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Wellington Health Care Alliance,963
963,Wellington Health Care Alliance,"Together, Nurturing Our Alliance Ecosystem","Together, Nurturing Our Alliance Ecosystem. NF. • Maintaining sustainable finances: • Strengthening the Alliance: • Nurturing corporate social responsibility: • Sustaining and growing clinical services.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,"The text discusses strengthening the Alliance and maintaining sustainable finances, indicating integration and financial aspects.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Wellington Health Care Alliance,963
963,Wellington Health Care Alliance,"Together, Enriching Partnerships And Growing Community Relationships","Together, Enriching Partnerships And Growing Community Relationships. NF. • Committing to active participation as a member of the Guelph Wellington Ontario Health Team (GW OHT): • Collaborating with partners to support quality patient care: • Planning for the impact of future community growth.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on OHT participation and collaboration to support patient care, along with planning for future community growth within partnerships.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Wellington Health Care Alliance,963
963,Wellington Health Care Alliance,"Champion Diversity, Equity And Inclusion In Everything We Do","Champion Diversity, Equity And Inclusion In Everything We Do. NF. • Including DEI as the foundational enabler of each strategic pillar: • Committing to co-design and advance a health equity plan in alignment with our communities and people we serve.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on DEI, a key aspect of health equity, and integrating it into the organization's strategic pillars and planning.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Wellington Health Care Alliance,963
969,Ontario Shores Centre for Mental Health Sciences,We Care.,"We Care.. We will provide personalized care, using the latest innovations and real-time data, in partnership with patients and family caregivers. Ontario Shores has developed a reputation as a leader and trusted provider of high-quality evidence based mental health care. Over the next four years, Ontario Shores will tailor evidence-based care through utilizing near real-time patient data to provide personalized care for patients, leveraging innovative tools and technologies.. Strategic Goal 1: Develop tools and approaches that embed patient characteristics into their care.. Strategic Goal 2: Leverage technology that collects and utilizes near real-time data to personalize care.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The focus on personalized care, utilizing evidence-based practices and real-time patient data through technology, aligns with patient care excellence and digital health innovation.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Ontario Shores Centre for Mental Health Sciences,969
969,Ontario Shores Centre for Mental Health Sciences,We Lead.,"We Lead.. We will design an evidence-based, integrated continuum of care that enhances equitable access, improves outcomes and promotes recovery. Ontario Shores will leverage its strength and lead the development of future standards to advance systems of care. Over the next four years, Ontario Shores will engage targeted partners to co-design an integrated stepped care model that prioritizes keeping patients in their communities, improving access and efficiency of care delivery.. Strategic Goal 1: Engage in purposeful partnerships to achieve equitable access to care across the continuum.. Strategic Goal 2: Implement bundled care models and integrated population health strategies to improve patient outcomes.. Strategic Goal 3: Empower patients and families as partners in Recovery.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on partnerships to achieve equitable access to care, continuum of care and integrated care models.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Ontario Shores Centre for Mental Health Sciences,969
969,Ontario Shores Centre for Mental Health Sciences,We Unite.,"We Unite.. We will create a diverse and inclusive workplace that champions, empowers and supports our people and teams. Ontario Shores will build upon its highly skilled and engaged workforce to create a dynamic workforce of the future. Mental Health professionals will learn and practice in diverse and inclusive interprofessional teams in partnership with patients, families and caregivers.. Strategic Goal 1: Optimize team-based care that enables clinicians to work at the top of their professional scope.. Strategic Goal 2: Build knowledge and capacity to elevate mental health care across the continuum.. Strategic Goal 3: Be an employer of choice that focuses on the wellbeing, engagement and resilience of our people.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on creating a diverse and inclusive workplace, supporting employees, and optimizing team-based care, all of which contribute to workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Ontario Shores Centre for Mental Health Sciences,969
964,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,"Equity, Diversity & Inclusion (Edi)","Equity, Diversity & Inclusion (Edi). NF. • Anti-racism Campaign: • Truth and Reconciliation Commission of Canada Review Committee: • United Nations Declaration on the Rights of Indigenous Peoples Act (UNDRIP): • Sustainable Indigenous Recruitment and Retention: • Trauma Informed Care Training: • EDI Hospital-Wide Policy Review Process.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on EDI initiatives, anti-racism, indigenous rights, and indigenous recruitment/retention, all falling under health equity and workforce sustainability.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,964
964,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,Mental Health & Addictions,Mental Health & Addictions. NF. • Schedule 1 Steering Committee: • Expansion of Rapid Access Addictions Medicine Clinic: • Urgent Psychiatry Services: • Investigate In-Patient Addiction Treatment Facility: • Discussion re: Partnering with Established Treatment Centres: • Dedicated Mental Health Counsellor in Emergency Department (ED).,ACCESS & CAPACITY,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The focus is on expanding access to mental health and addiction services, with a strong emphasis on partnerships with established treatment centres.",Access & Capacity,Access & Capacity,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,964
964,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,"Future Planning, Infrastructure & Growth","Future Planning, Infrastructure & Growth. NF. • Infrastructure & Growth: - Long-Term Care Beds: - Schedule 1 Beds: - Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI): - Expand Specialist Services: - Intensive Care Unit Beds: - Phase 2 of ED Renovations: • Sustainability: - Staffing, Health Human Resources: - Financial Stability: - Physicians.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"Focus on infrastructure development (beds, MRI, renovations) and staffing/financial stability.",Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,964
964,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,Investing In Our People,Investing In Our People. NF. • Staff Experience: • Health Human Resources: • Financial Incentives / Taxation Exempt: • Leadership Development for Staff / Succession Planning: • Promote Positive Work Environment and Culture: • Indigenous Midwifery Supports.,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on improving staff experience, HR, leadership development, and creating a positive work environment, all of which fall under workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,964
964,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,High Quality Patient Experience & Care,"High Quality Patient Experience & Care. NF. • Patient Experience: • Best Practices - Quality of Care, Patient-Centered, Patient Safety: • Patient Navigator: • Indigenous Transitions Facilitator: • Accreditation for Indigenous Services in Healthcare: • Best Practice Spotlight Organization: • Patient and Family Advisor: • Communications Strategy: - Podcast: - Newsletter: • Clinical Scholar.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"Focuses on patient experience, quality of care, and specific initiatives related to Indigenous healthcare and patient navigation.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,964
964,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,Innovation / Technology - Digital Transformation,Innovation / Technology - Digital Transformation. NF. • Ontario Health Team Digital Project: • Meditech Expansion: • Ocean E-Referral Expansion: • Innovative Models of Radiology Services: • Artificial Intelligence Exploratory Options: - Self-Registration Kiosk: • Innovative Interpreter Services.,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"This project focuses on digital technologies like Meditech expansion, e-referral systems, AI, and self-registration kiosks within the context of an Ontario Health Team digital project.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,964
964,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,External Partnerships,"External Partnerships. NF. • Advocacy - Affordable / Equitable Housing: • Social Determinants of Health: • Relationship / Partnerships: • Tribal Councils, Sioux Lookout First Nation Health Authority (SLFNHA), Municipality, Non-Insured Health Benefits (NIHB), Northern Ontario School of Medicine (NOSM) University, Nourish, High School, Ontario Health Team's, Seven Generations, Social Justice & Leadership, Police Services, etc.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text explicitly mentions partnerships with various external organizations and addresses social determinants of health, indicating a focus on integration and equity.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,SIOUX LOOKOUT Meno Ya Win HEALTH CENTRE,964
965,Sault Area Hospital,Compassionate Person-Centred Care,"Compassionate Person-Centred Care. We will ensure our patients and their families feel heard and empowered to be active participants in their care.. DIVERSITY, EQUITY & INCLUSION - We will provide inclusive and culturally safe care to all, beginning with a focus on Indigenous health and continuing to improve overall access, equity and respect for diversity.. INTEGRATED HEALTH CARE - We will meet the health and care needs of those we serve through continued collaboration with community and regional partners.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text emphasizes patient empowerment, culturally safe care, and improvements in access and equity, pointing towards both patient care quality and health equity themes.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Sault Area Hospital,965
965,Sault Area Hospital,Healthy And Supportive Organization,"Healthy And Supportive Organization. Our leaders will enable their teams to do their best and ensure staff, physicians, and volunteers are healthy, well and safe at work.. SUPPORTIVE ENVIRONMENT - We will enable good health and attendance and invest in the development of people focused leaders.. SAFE WORKPLACE - We will ensure a healthy and safe environment by working together to reduce incidents of workplace violence and worker injury.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on creating a healthy, safe, and supportive work environment, investing in leadership development and reducing workplace incidents, which aligns with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Sault Area Hospital,965
965,Sault Area Hospital,Strengthening Our Operations,"Strengthening Our Operations. We will ensure that our organization can best meet the health and care needs of the population we serve.. HIGH QUALITY CARE - We will continue our commitment to quality, research, innovation and digital solutions.. FINANCIAL HEALTH - We will drive financial sustainability.. PANDEMIC RECOVERY - We will stabilize, transform, sustain and restore health and care services for those in our communities.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,"The text emphasizes high quality care, research, innovation, digital solutions, financial sustainability, and pandemic recovery.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Sault Area Hospital,965
