967,Cornwall Community Hospital Hôpital communautaire de Cornwall,People,"People. NF. - Inspired by patients and care partners: - Supporting the wellbeing of our people: - Engaging and cultivating a high performing team: - Building a culture of equity, diversity and inclusion, and embracing reconciliation: - Stewarding our environmental and social responsibilities.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on organizational culture, team engagement, EDI, and employee wellbeing.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Cornwall Community Hospital Hôpital communautaire de Cornwall,967
967,Cornwall Community Hospital Hôpital communautaire de Cornwall,Integration,Integration. NF. - Creating sustainable models of care: - Supporting transitions in care: - Advancing collaborative partnerships: - Promoting health system integration.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,None,"The text focuses on creating care models, supporting transitions, and advancing partnerships, all related to health system integration.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Cornwall Community Hospital Hôpital communautaire de Cornwall,967
970,Brant Community Healthcare System,Patients,"Patients. We will prioritize high-quality, person-centered care and improving patient outcomes.. Adopting leading evidence-based standards and practices for patient safety and quality while continuously maintaining the highest level of accreditation.. Engaging patients and families to co-design the best possible care experience through the growth and empowerment of our Patient and Family Advisory Program.. Providing a culturally safe healthcare experience for First Nations, Inuit and Métis people through the advancement of the Indigenous Health Service and the development of an Indigenous Health Strategy.. Understanding our community's health and equity data to respond to diverse needs and ensure culturally safe care for all.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on high-quality, person-centered care, patient safety, patient engagement, and culturally safe care for Indigenous peoples and diverse communities.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Brant Community Healthcare System,970
970,Brant Community Healthcare System,People,"People. We will focus on the recruitment, retention, well-being, development, and engagement of TeamBCHS.. Leveraging the talents of our diverse workforce to foster a culture of excellence, while creating opportunities for both career growth and recruitment.. Supporting the psychological safety, well-being, and resilience of our people to promote a thriving work environment across TeamBCHS.. Fostering a culture of recognition and joy that inspires employees by connecting them to the purpose of their work, while upholding the highest standards of professionalism, respect, and accountability.. Inspiring a culture of inclusion and belonging by advancing our Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Belonging (DEI-B) roadmap, aligned with our Indigenous Health Strategy and the Ontario Health Equity, Inclusion, Diversity, and Anti-Racism framework.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on recruitment, retention, well-being, and engagement of staff (Workforce), while also emphasizing diversity, equity, inclusion, and belonging (Health Equity).",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Brant Community Healthcare System,970
970,Brant Community Healthcare System,Partners,"Partners. We will lead collaborations within our hospital and with community partners to drive innovation, elevate healthcare quality, and improve health outcomes.. Strengthening and formalizing partnerships with other healthcare organizations, particularly primary care providers, to improve access to and continuity of care.. Leading collaborations with community organizations to implement innovative solutions to provide the right care at the right place.. Growing our partnerships with academic institutions to enhance our academic mission, providing students with opportunities to learn and develop their careers.. Participating in research opportunities to improve patient care.. Strengthening outreach and partnerships with diverse community groups to enhance patient and TeamBCHS experiences to reflect the communities we serve.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text emphasizes collaborations within the hospital and with community partners to improve healthcare quality and outcomes, along with strengthening partnerships with other healthcare organizations and community groups.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Brant Community Healthcare System,970
970,Brant Community Healthcare System,Progress,"Progress. We will advance the redevelopment of our facilities, services, and systems to meet the evolving needs of our communities, ensuring sustainable, environmentally responsible, high-quality, and accessible care for years to come.. Reimagining our care facilities by advancing the redevelopment of the the hospital.. Ensuring effective care delivery within our current facilities while also completing infrastructure renewal projects.. Implementing a Digital Health Strategy that integrates innovative technologies—including the implementation of a new Health Information System—to enhance patient and provider experiences while streamlining operations.. Creating a multi-year financial plan that focuses on financial sustainability and exploring non-ministry and new revenue streams to enhance our fiscal health.. Advancing environmental sustainability by reducing waste, optimizing energy use, and incorporating green practices into hospital operations.. Implementing a Clinical Services Plan that addresses the evolving needs of the diverse communities we serve, incorporating new programs and services to enhance access to high-quality and equitable care.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on facility redevelopment, digital health strategy implementation, and environmental sustainability efforts within the hospital, alongside financial planning and clinical services.",Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Brant Community Healthcare System,970
971,St. Joseph's Health Centre Of Sudbury,Care With Purpose And Compassion,"Care With Purpose And Compassion. NF. • Embrace our Mission by championing compassionate care and service for all.: • Enhance and broaden our Equity, Diversity, and Inclusion (EDI), Anti-Racism, and Indigenous reconciliation initiatives to cultivate a welcoming, respectful, and inclusive environment.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on EDI initiatives, anti-racism, Indigenous reconciliation, and aligning actions with the organization's mission of compassionate care.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's Health Centre Of Sudbury,971
971,St. Joseph's Health Centre Of Sudbury,Cultivate A Thriving Workforce,"Cultivate A Thriving Workforce. NF. • Become the leading workplace by prioritizing effective retention strategies and enhancing recruitment efforts.: • Nurture a supportive atmosphere that ensures staff psychological health & safety, promotes well-being, and increases job satisfaction.: • Embrace a distributed leadership approach and offer training, development, and mentorship programs for staff members.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text emphasizes retention, recruitment, staff well-being, and leadership development, aligning with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's Health Centre Of Sudbury,971
971,St. Joseph's Health Centre Of Sudbury,Advance Our Excellence In Care,Advance Our Excellence In Care. NF. • Enhance person-centred care and health outcomes by implementing new models of care.: • Identify gaps and unmet needs within our community and implement targeted solutions to support our most vulnerable populations.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on person-centered care and improving outcomes, while also addressing the needs of vulnerable populations.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's Health Centre Of Sudbury,971
971,St. Joseph's Health Centre Of Sudbury,Amplify Our Impact Across The Sector,"Amplify Our Impact Across The Sector. NF. • Solidify our leadership role in care excellence and in championing the Catholic Mission in healthcare.: • Share our transformative strategies, initiatives, and results to elevate care in the sector.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"Focuses on solidifying leadership and elevating care in the sector, highlighting both organizational influence and care quality.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's Health Centre Of Sudbury,971
972,Waypoint CENTRE for MENTAL HEALTH CARE,Serve,"Serve. We will apply our expertise in mental health, addiction, and geriatric care for patients/clients and families, to support their best possible health experiences and outcomes.. Deliver high quality and safe care driven by data and evidence.: Grow specialized services in areas aligned with our unique capabilities and strengths.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The focus is on delivering high-quality, safe care and improving health outcomes, supported by the organization's expertise.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Waypoint CENTRE for MENTAL HEALTH CARE,972
972,Waypoint CENTRE for MENTAL HEALTH CARE,Discover,"Discover. We will advance research and embrace education, mobilizing diverse forms of knowledge and sharing our expertise to ignite possibilities and create a brighter future.. Build and strengthen partnerships to expand as a hub for advanced training in mental health, addictions, and geriatric care.: Evaluate innovative models of care and disseminate insights to shape a better health system.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text explicitly mentions advancing research and education, strengthening partnerships, and evaluating innovative models of care.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Waypoint CENTRE for MENTAL HEALTH CARE,972
972,Waypoint CENTRE for MENTAL HEALTH CARE,Lead,"Lead. We will be a trusted partner, driving innovation, advocacy, and integrated care to strengthen the system and support healthier communities. Provide leadership, expertise, and enabling functions to design and deliver innovative integrated care models with partners.: Support and advocate for one system and help build capacity for community - and primary care-based mental health, substance use health and geriatric services.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The focus is on integrated care models with partners and driving innovation, indicating integration and digital health themes.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Waypoint CENTRE for MENTAL HEALTH CARE,972
972,Waypoint CENTRE for MENTAL HEALTH CARE,Inspire,"Inspire. We will create a culture where people learn, grow and thrive, and feel pride, empowerment and belonging to a community that is having a remarkable impact.. Create continuous opportunities for workforce training, learning and growth.: Cultivate an inclusive and empowering culture that prioritizes staff well-being.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on creating a positive work environment, opportunities for growth and inclusion, which all relate to workforce and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Waypoint CENTRE for MENTAL HEALTH CARE,972
973,Weeneebayko Area Health Authority,Strategy 1: Excellent Quality Service,"Strategy 1: Excellent Quality Service. We will provide service that is patient and family centred and is respectful of mind, body and spiritual needs.. - Deliver a cultural competency training program, to staff and referral partners and evaluate effectiveness: - Measure and monitor patient satisfaction rates for THE_HOSPITAL programs and services on an annualized basis: - Expand the geriatric speciality clinic model, for outreach to all communities within the James and Hudson Bay Region: - Develop a strategy for the THE_HOSPITAL website to increase public access to information and data collection.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"This strategy focuses on patient-centered care, cultural competency, and expanding services to underserved communities, aligning with both patient care excellence and health equity.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Weeneebayko Area Health Authority,973
973,Weeneebayko Area Health Authority,Strategy 2: Quality Infrastructure,"Strategy 2: Quality Infrastructure. We will sustain financial health and optimize growth to achieve our mission and vision.. - Support the implementation of the stage 2 provincial capital planning process for the development of new regional facilities: - Engage in an objective analysis of governance, management and medical staff structures, decision-making and communication processes at THE_HOSPITAL to identify recommendations for strengthening these systems: - Optimize the Hospital Information System in order to support information and data collection systems; leverage off NE LHIN's IT initiatives: - Develop a process to identify and eliminate accessibility barriers to ensure compliance with provincial legislation: - Optimize geographic logistics in order to promote cost-saving initiatives.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This strategy focuses on facility development, governance structure analysis, accessibility barrier removal, and optimization of geographic logistics, encompassing both infrastructure and organizational elements.",Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Weeneebayko Area Health Authority,973
973,Weeneebayko Area Health Authority,Strategy 3: Safety First,Strategy 3: Safety First. We will ensure optimal safety in all aspects of care for the patient and staff.. - Provide introductory and refresher training to staff on THE_HOSPITAL's incident management program: - Promote wellness and mental wellbeing through cultural and traditional activities: - Provide timely access to appropriate health care services and optimize patient flow: - Implement quality improvement projects for key areas of need throughout the health system.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The strategy focuses on safety in patient care, incident management training for staff, and promoting staff wellness.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Weeneebayko Area Health Authority,973
973,Weeneebayko Area Health Authority,Strategy 4: Build Organizational Capability & Capacity,"Strategy 4: Build Organizational Capability & Capacity. We will hire, retain and inspire the best in our people.. - Support the development and roll out of a comprehensive staff orientation program: - Support the roll out of a staff recognition program that is consistent among all THE_HOSPITAL sites: - Support the roll out of staff satisfaction surveys every two years to help benchmark performance: - Create and deliver a training program that supports the roll out of the new performance management system: - Work with department heads to establish a recruitment and retention strategy that is targeted towards physicians, nurses and skilled tradespeople.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This strategy focuses on hiring, retaining, and inspiring staff through programs, recognition, surveys, training, and recruitment strategies.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Weeneebayko Area Health Authority,973
973,Weeneebayko Area Health Authority,Strategy 5: Financial Health,"Strategy 5: Financial Health. Generation of operating surpluses to re-invest in technology, equipment & infrastructure. - Optimize financial, physical infrastructure, and human resources through implementation of the hospital improvement plan: - Take advantage of funding opportunities by applying to funding programs and non-government sources: - Assess our progress and improve value through standardized performance measures: - Identify opportunities for cost control that support productivity improvements and financial accountability: - Implement a comprehensive fundraising strategy for THE_HOSPITAL that increases our donations.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The strategy focuses on generating surpluses, optimizing resources, controlling costs, and fundraising, all of which relate to financial health, with a secondary focus on physical infrastructure.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Weeneebayko Area Health Authority,973
