974,North Bay Regional Health Centre,Innovation & Digital Enablement,Innovation & Digital Enablement. NF. NF.,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,None,"The title explicitly mentions ""Innovation & Digital Enablement,"" which clearly falls under the Digital Health & Innovation theme.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,North Bay Regional Health Centre,974
975,Trillium Health Partners,Inspire And Invest In A Diverse Team Thp,"Inspire And Invest In A Diverse Team THE_HOSPITAL. Strengthen our people-centred culture where Team THE_HOSPITAL reflects the community, and every person feels respected, connected, and supported to deliver better care every day.. Well-Being: Prioritizing the holistic well-being of Team THE_HOSPITAL to ensure everyone feels supported and able to thrive.. Equity, Diversity, and Inclusion: Cultivating an environment where everyone can do their best work, and where diversity is reflected in leadership, decision-making, and opportunity.. Growth and Development: Fostering meaningful opportunities for every person to learn, grow, and contribute, supported by consistent and connected ways of working together.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on investing in a diverse team, their well-being, and fostering growth, all related to workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Trillium Health Partners,975
975,Trillium Health Partners,Deliver The Highest Quality Care,"Deliver The Highest Quality Care. Deliver equitable, whole-person care that is personalized and strengthened by evidence, digital innovation, and continuous improvement to achieve better outcomes and experiences.. People-Centred Care: Delivering equitable, whole-person care by working with patients, families, caregivers, and the community to shape experiences that reflect each person's values and health goals.. Quality and Evidence-Based Care: Advancing evidence-based practices, treatments, and equipment, while accelerating change through quality improvement and learning health system methods.. Digitally Enabled Care: Using community insight, advanced analytics, and the power of responsible, ethical, and human-centred Al for better health.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on delivering high-quality, equitable, and personalized care, while also emphasizing the use of digital innovation to improve outcomes and experiences.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Trillium Health Partners,975
975,Trillium Health Partners,Partner For A Seamless Health System,"Partner For A Seamless Health System. Partner to build a seamless, digitally-enabled health system that wraps around people and communities, connecting care, tools, and partnerships for better access, outcomes, and experiences.. Digitally-Connected Seamless Care: Creating a fully integrated system where care is coordinated and enhanced through digital innovation and AI-powered solutions to wrap around each person.. Community Partnerships for Better Health: Working with partners to support prevention, early detection, and chronic disease management.. Trillium HealthWorks and Health Hubs: Expanding access through modern facilities and community-based hubs that act as anchors of seamless, digitally-connected care.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on building a seamless, integrated health system through partnerships and digital enablement.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Trillium Health Partners,975
975,Trillium Health Partners,Shape A Healthier Community For All,"Shape A Healthier Community For All. Embed research, innovation, and education into every aspect of care, translating discovery into real-world impact to shape better health for all.. Research: Generate and apply data, evidence, and knowledge - supported by our clinical researchers and science community at the hospital' Institute for Better Health - to understand, anticipate, and respond to the evolving needs of the community and drive health system excellence.. Innovation: Rapidly design, implement, evaluate, and scale new human-centred, evidence informed solutions for better health, harnessing AI, emerging technologies, and novel ideas, enabling our strategy.. Education: Building on our strong foundation as a top destination for learners, we will foster a culture of education and continuous learning across our organization where every team member contributes to better care and healthier communities.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on embedding research and education into care, alongside the implementation of innovative, technology-driven solutions.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Trillium Health Partners,975
976,Sinai Health,Enhance Excellence And Integration In Care And Service,"Enhance Excellence And Integration In Care And Service. Invest in people, practice, partnerships, and technology to enable our patients and their essential care partners to access the highest quality care, based on the latest knowledge, within the hospital and across the health care system.. - Advance our Quality Aims to underscore our commitment to continuously improving care and service. Use the Quality Aims to develop a multi-year quality improvement roadmap as well as annual plans.: - Accelerate our efforts to enhance integrated care for our patients with specialized and complex care needs. Our focus will be on operationalizing our Cancer strategy, enhancing Inflammatory Bowel Disease service delivery, growing our capacity to deliver Mental Health and Addictions and Psychiatric Emergency Services, enhancing capacity to deliver High Acuity Obstetrics and implementing our future Ambulatory Care Model.: - Advance the use of Patient Reported Outcome Measures (PROMs) and Patient Reported Experience Measures (PREMs) in core populations to meaningfully partner with patients in the evaluation and improvement of care and service.: - Collaborate with our system partners, including the Mid-West Toronto Ontario Health Team, to evolve and strengthen care delivery in our community and across the continuum of care.: - Set the course for purposeful investments in our digital assets and health care analytic capability to improve clinical decision making, patient safety, Person-Centered Care, operational efficiency and to accelerate research.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on improving care quality, patient experience, and integrating services with partners, particularly the OHT.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sinai Health,976
976,Sinai Health,Build A Caring And Inclusive Culture And Environment,"Build A Caring And Inclusive Culture And Environment. Create welcoming environments where everyone feels they matter and belong.. - Activate the hospital's People Plan to support and equip our people so they can thrive and regain purpose in a world changed by the COVID-19 pandemic.: - Ensure the safety of our patients and our people.: - Implement 'Look and Feel' standards to ensure sustainable, safe healing spaces that allow people to thrive and create the best patient outcomes and experience.: - Set a 10 year vision for our campuses by completing a long-term master plan to prepare for the next phase of Renew Sinai and envision the best use of all owned real estate.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text focuses on creating a caring and inclusive culture, safety for patients and staff, and implementing standards for healing spaces, with a long-term master plan for campuses.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sinai Health,976
976,Sinai Health,Optimize Care And Performance,"Optimize Care And Performance. Fully utilize all of our resources (people, funds, processes) to enhance our sustainability and inspire investment in our future.. - Build capacity for performance excellence to improve the safety, reliability and effectiveness of care by enhancing organizational culture, and building a learning system anchored in safety and improvement science.: - Develop multi-year plans for financial sustainability, capital, long-term cash flow and effective talent and workforce management as well as a Post Construction Operation Plan (PCOP).: - Every year, target new areas for strategic business case development to invest in clinical and operational renewal.: - Achieve the Finance Integration and Transformation project goals including procurement redesign.: - Sustain and optimize expanded capacity to enhance access to patient care.: - Grow our commercial businesses to enable reinvestment in care and academic endeavours.: - Develop a five-year workforce sustainability strategy, including innovative care delivery models, to support care and service continuity and our people's wellness.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on utilizing resources to enhance sustainability and inspire investment, develops multi-year plans for financial sustainability, workforce management, and optimizes capacity to enhance access to patient care.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sinai Health,976
976,Sinai Health,"Advance Discovery, Education, And The Science Of Care","Advance Discovery, Education, And The Science Of Care. Prioritize our nine key areas of specialization, bringing our leadership to the next level, and invest in research and teaching to create better treatments and outcomes here and around the world.. - Advance and launch the Institute for the Science of Care and Innovation at the hospital and the Centre for Nursing Excellence.: - Extend the Magnet® Recognition Program to Hennick Bridgepoint Hospital and continue to excel by outperforming national and international benchmarks related to nurse satisfaction, patient satisfaction and clinical indicators.: - Renew and sustain our clinical research enterprise and the Lunenfeld-Tanenbaum Research Institute.: - Create opportunities for improving transitions to practice, life-long learning, professional advancement and teaching.: - Intensify our global impact in Women's and Infants' Health.: - Advance academic priorities in our key areas of specialization: Women's and Infants' Health, Diabetes, Emergency Medicine, Palliative Care, Cancer, Inflammatory Bowel Disease, Arthritis and Autoimmune Disease, Geriatrics, and Complex Medicine & Complex Orthopaedics.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on advancing research, education, and the science of care, alongside improving patient and nurse satisfaction and clinical outcomes, which aligns with research and patient care themes.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Sinai Health,976
977,NORTH OF SUPERIOR HEALTHCARE GROUP,People,"People. Dedicate our efforts and resources to the provision of care to our patients, residents, tenants, clients and their families, that is respectful of their preferences, needs and values.. • Ensure culturally safe care for Indigenous, Francophone and our diverse populations: • Promote Patient Family Resident Advisory Council engagement: • Improve seniors' care in the community.: • Improve mental health and addiction services: • Focus on social determinants of health (food, housing, employment security, and transportation): • Increase services provided by specialists: • Provide solution-focused customer service training: • Support quality with a focus on improved Accreditation standing.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text emphasizes patient-centered care, cultural safety for diverse populations, and addressing social determinants of health, aligning with patient care excellence and health equity themes.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,NORTH OF SUPERIOR HEALTHCARE GROUP,977
977,NORTH OF SUPERIOR HEALTHCARE GROUP,Providers,"Providers. Ensure a supportive work environment that attracts and retains the highest quality staff, physician, student and volunteer care team.. • Secure a sustainable and committed team of clinical, services and administrative staff, physicians and volunteers: • Promote diversity which reflects our communities: • Grow our own providers: • Improve recruitment and retention initiatives: • Create succession and full human resources plans: • Participate in local, regional and Provincial health human resources advocacy: • Provide short and long term accommodation support: • Support and expand volunteer involvement: • Facilitate family supports: • Strengthen governance: • Ensure provider safety.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on attracting, retaining, and supporting healthcare providers, as well as strengthening governance and ensuring safety.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,NORTH OF SUPERIOR HEALTHCARE GROUP,977
977,NORTH OF SUPERIOR HEALTHCARE GROUP,Partners,"Partners. Offer leadership and active participation in the collaborative efforts of our local and regional health and services partners, with a focus on developing solutions that improve the health of our communities.. • Develop and maintain relationships and capitalize on the resources and expertise of our local, district, and regional providers.: • Promote Ontario Health Team (OHT) development: • Enhance external communication: • Facilitate local health hubs: • Think outside traditional hospital roles: • Excel at care transitions: • Enhance the provision of community support services.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,The text focuses on collaborative efforts with local and regional health partners to improve community health and develop solutions through OHTs and local health hubs.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,NORTH OF SUPERIOR HEALTHCARE GROUP,977
977,NORTH OF SUPERIOR HEALTHCARE GROUP,Place,"Place. Continually enhance our buildings, equipment and technology infrastructure to assure ongoing organizational sustainability.. • Ensure the sustainability and continual improvement of our physical infrastructure, including buildings, equipment and technology: • Pursue long-term care home development at the Wilson Memorial General Hospital in Marathon: • Advance with rejuvenation of The McCausland Hospital in Terrace Bay: • Expand our information technology services including electronic medical records: • Advocate for appropriate financial resources.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,"Focuses on enhancing buildings, equipment, and technology infrastructure for organizational sustainability, with mention of financial resources.",Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,NORTH OF SUPERIOR HEALTHCARE GROUP,977
978,Kingston Health Sciences Centre,1. Ensure Quality In Every Patient Experience,"1. Ensure Quality In Every Patient Experience. NF. • Successfully adopt new Lumeo processes across THE_HOSPITAL: • Be accreditation-ready for April 2026 site survey: • Develop and implement plans to manage approved budget and improve deficit towards a break-even operating position: • THE_HOSPITAL, as the lead agency and health service provider, will continue partnering with FLA OHT and Ontario Health at Home to implement the FLA Home Care Modernization Leading Project, enhancing care coordination, and expanding in-home services: • Patients discharged from the ED with suspected exacerbations of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) or congestive heart failure (CHF) are prioritized for rapid access to receive evidence-based specialist care within a clinic closest to home: • Advance the principles of people-centred care by sharing peoples' care experiences at all levels of the organization: • Finalize and launch plans for addressing short-term urgent patient-care facility needs within and outside of existing hospital buildings (Bridging Projects).",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"Focus on quality patient experience, care coordination with OHT, and rapid access to specialist care, highlighting patient-centeredness.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Kingston Health Sciences Centre,978
978,Kingston Health Sciences Centre,"2. Nurture Our Passion For Caring, Leading And Learning","2. Nurture Our Passion For Caring, Leading And Learning. NF. • Implement a framework and strategy for enhancing Psychological Health & Safety in the workplace: • Continue to cross-train staff across clinical areas: • Enhance learning for new and emerging leaders.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on staff well-being (psychological safety), training, and leadership development, which are key aspects of workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Kingston Health Sciences Centre,978
978,Kingston Health Sciences Centre,3. Improve The Health Of Our Communities Through Partnership And Innovation,"3. Improve The Health Of Our Communities Through Partnership And Innovation. NF. • Contribute to the development of the FLA OHT by participating in Ministry-directed Initiatives: • Stabilize and optimize Lumeo at THE_HOSPITAL by proactively identifying, advocating for, and escalating priority issues through regional processes to support clinical operations: • Establish a THE_HOSPITAL clinical informatics team and local Lumeo operations governance structure to work with local stakeholders and the regional Lumeo team to stabilize, optimize, and evolve the system: • Solidify plans for a new area of excellence for CAR T-cell therapy.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text mentions contributing to the OHT, optimizing Lumeo (an EMR system), and establishing a clinical informatics team, indicating integration, digital health and community focus.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Kingston Health Sciences Centre,978
978,Kingston Health Sciences Centre,4. Launch Khsc As A Leading Centre For Research And Education,"4. Launch THE_HOSPITAL As A Leading Centre For Research And Education. NF. • Work with education partners to create capacity for all requested nursing, allied, medical and post-grad student placements: • Implement a strategic plan that enhances research activities and visibility at THE_HOSPITAL.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The title and text clearly focus on enhancing research and education activities, while also mentioning the creation of capacity for student placements, which relates to workforce development.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Kingston Health Sciences Centre,978
978,Kingston Health Sciences Centre,"5. Advance Equity, Inclusion And Diversity And Address Racism To Achieve Better Out Comes For Patients, Families, Providers And Staff","5. Advance Equity, Inclusion And Diversity And Address Racism To Achieve Better Out Comes For Patients, Families, Providers And Staff. NF. • Implement an integrated inclusion framework.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This directly addresses equity, inclusion, and diversity, which falls under the Health Equity theme, and implementing a framework implies organizational culture.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Kingston Health Sciences Centre,978
979,SCARBOROUGH HEALTH NETWORK,System Integration & Transformation,System Integration & Transformation. Work with partners to bring care closer to home with fewer handoffs.. NF.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ACCESS & CAPACITY,The text describes working with partners for system integration and aims to improve care accessibility by reducing handoffs.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,SCARBOROUGH HEALTH NETWORK,979
979,SCARBOROUGH HEALTH NETWORK,People & Culture,"People & Culture. Recruit, retain, and support our exceptional people and cultivate a culture of inclusion.. NF.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on attracting and keeping staff, as well as creating an inclusive environment.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,SCARBOROUGH HEALTH NETWORK,979
979,SCARBOROUGH HEALTH NETWORK,Population Health & Equity,Population Health & Equity. Champion improved health outcomes by matching our services to Scarborough communities' needs.. NF.,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The title and text clearly indicate a focus on population health outcomes and addressing the specific needs of communities, highlighting both population health and equity.",Population & Community Health,Population & Community Health,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,SCARBOROUGH HEALTH NETWORK,979
979,SCARBOROUGH HEALTH NETWORK,Research & Education,Research & Education. Uncover and pursue innovative new ways to address Scarborough's most critical health needs.. NF.,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text explicitly mentions research and education, with the intention of uncovering innovative new ways, which can be seen as related to digital health innovation.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,SCARBOROUGH HEALTH NETWORK,979
979,SCARBOROUGH HEALTH NETWORK,Quality & Patient Safety,Quality & Patient Safety. Keep quality care and patient safety at the core of everything we do.. NF.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text explicitly focuses on quality and patient safety, which aligns with patient care excellence, but also emphasizes it as a core value, connecting to organizational culture.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,SCARBOROUGH HEALTH NETWORK,979
980,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,Integrated Care For Urban Communities,"Integrated Care For Urban Communities. THE_HOSPITAL Health is proud to deliver a comprehensive spectrum of health care across the full breadth of Toronto. With St. Joseph’s in the west, St. Michael’s in the downtown core and Providence in the east, THE_HOSPITAL Health’s sites have been an integral part of our city’s communities for generations. Every person who turns to us for care brings with them their personal history, needs and experiences. Every person’s health care journey is different. We will work closely with our patients and partners to seamlessly integrate each person’s journey across the spectrum of care. Through the use of technology, research and data, we will make sure people receive the right care, at the right time, in the right place.. - Be the leader in integrated care for diverse urban communities.: - Provide integrated care that encompasses enhanced 24/7 access, seamless transitions, innovative options for provider/patient interaction including virtual care, increased patient autonomy and choice in care.: - Continue to be a trusted and valued partner that collaborates well with all providers in the health system.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on integrated care across different sites and seamless transitions, enhanced by technology and innovative interactions.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,980
980,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,Providing Leadership In Health Equity,"Providing Leadership In Health Equity. Health starts where people live, work and play. Social and economic factors can have lasting impacts and create stigma for those who need care. For more than 160 years, we have been here for people when they need us most, no matter their circumstances. We will work with our teams and our partners to make sure everyone can access the care they need with respect and compassion. We are committed to learning from those who have experienced disadvantage and to adapting our care, processes and language to better meet their needs. Health care is a basic human right and we will continue to be known as a leader in making care welcoming, effective, safe and accessible to all in our communities.. - Have fostered a culture of equity and made measurable and significant strides in transforming the care experience for those experiencing disadvantage in the communities we serve.: - Be a respected advocate for vulnerable populations, using research to advance policy change that truly transforms the system and impacts the social determinants of health.: - Be leaders in using evidence to advance practice change in how we care for people experiencing disadvantage.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on leadership in health equity, addressing social determinants of health and fostering a culture of equity within the organization to transform care for disadvantaged communities.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,980
980,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,Leading In World-Class Specialty Care,"Leading In World-Class Specialty Care. Being diagnosed with a disease or chronic condition can be frightening; it can suddenly change a person’s life. At these times, people trust THE_HOSPITAL Health to provide the best medical treatments and care available for themselves and for the people they love. As an academic health sciences leader with world-class specialty care programs and teams, THE_HOSPITAL Health is at the forefront of treatment for some of the world’s most complex diseases and conditions. We will work together to create care experiences that support and empower our patients throughout their care journey. Patients will feel confident knowing they are receiving the best – and often first and only – treatment available.. - Personalize the delivery of care by providing leading-edge evidence-based care for some of the most complex diseases and also the best care experience which considers the patient’s needs first.: - Be the regional and national hub for education, training and mentorship for our world-class specialty care programs that will attract globally leading talent into our specialty programs.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS","The text focuses on providing the best medical treatments and care, along with being a hub for education and training in specialty care programs.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,980
980,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,Joy In Work For Our People,"Joy In Work For Our People. People choose to work in health care to make a positive difference in their communities and in the lives of others. Joy in work is about helping make a connection to the meaning and purpose in our work. It is about creating a culture that recognizes each person’s contributions. It exists when we are all ambassadors for what we do. Joy becomes contagious. People who experience joy at work are more resilient and better equipped to support those we serve. We will continue to build our diverse workplace and make joy in work a shared responsibility. We will foster a culture that empowers our people to realize meaning and purpose in their work. THE_HOSPITAL Health will be known for its positive environment and be a sought after place to learn, work and volunteer.. - Have created an environment where all of our people can realize meaning and purpose in the work they do every day and where joy in work is reflected in the care provided to our patients.: - Be a sought after employer known for supporting healthy, productive people and teams.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on creating a positive work environment, fostering a culture of meaning and purpose, and being a sought-after employer, all related to workforce well-being and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,980
980,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,Impactful Research And Innovation,"Impactful Research And Innovation. Great innovations start with curiosity and a question. Research is essential to improving lives and communities. the hospital’s research teams relentlessly pursue some of the world’s toughest health care challenges. Their findings regularly improve the lives of people in Toronto and around the globe. From identifying new therapies to combat disease, to the development of artificial intelligence tools to improve health care delivery, THE_HOSPITAL Health is a global leader in health research and innovation. We will create a seamless bridge between research findings and patient care delivery. We will reinforce our culture of curiosity by supporting our researchers through every stage of their career and ensure our work remains at the frontier of quality and innovation.. - Have promoted a culture of discovery across our network that serves as a model for research that improves patient care and health care delivery.: - Lead in the way we partner and engage stakeholders to advance research and innovation locally, nationally and globally.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on research, discovery, and improving patient care through research findings and a culture of curiosity.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,980
980,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,Reimagining Teaching And Learning,"Reimagining Teaching And Learning. As an academic health sciences organization, education is woven into every aspect of how we work and learn together. THE_HOSPITAL Health knows that rigorous, ongoing professional development is an essential part of providing the best care to patients. We value collaborative learning and instill this by teaching our current and future health care teams together. We will be leaders in integrated health education, driving system change. We will learn from our patients and their families by including them in our teaching teams. We will be renowned as a teaching organization where people thrive, grow and achieve performance excellence.. - Drive system transformation by leading in integrated health systems education for everyone.: - Recognize patients, residents and families as teachers and learners within our teams.: - Be known as a learning organization where our teams thrive, grow and achieve performance excellence.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on education, professional development, and collaborative learning within the healthcare system, highlighting the hospital's role as a teaching organization where people thrive and grow.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,980
980,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,Achieving Quality Together,"Achieving Quality Together. Delivering an exceptional care experience is the promise we make to our patients and those that care for them every day. We believe that everyone has the right to safe, high quality care. To get there, we need a relentless focus on all the dimensions of quality, which include care that is: effective, safe, timely, patient and family partnered, efficient, equitable, integrated and supportive of provider wellness. THE_HOSPITAL Health, in partnership with our patients and their families, will design new systems and pathways of care that make navigating our health care system easier. We will build a culture of safety through systems that are reliable, ensuring care is safe. We will pursue a culture of continuous improvement, always seeking to find opportunities to learn and change and grow. Propelling our quality work will be our advanced analytics infrastructure that will uncover new insights in care and treatments, design predictive capabilities and build intuitive surveillance for safer care and improved outcomes. All of this will only be possible through genuine partnerships with our patients, their families and our community.. - Achieve excellence in all dimensions of quality.: - Be recognized as a health care organization with an unwavering commitment to safety for patients, families, staff and physicians with outcomes that prove it.: - Deliver care delivery models that actively engage the patient in enabling their health through all phases of life.: - Be known as a global leader in developing innovative approaches to partnered care.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on providing safe, high-quality care and improving patient experience, while also emphasizing a culture of safety and continuous improvement within the organization.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,980
980,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,Revolutionizing Care Through Digital Transformation And Artificial Intelligence,"Revolutionizing Care Through Digital Transformation And Artificial Intelligence. Imagine the convenience of connecting with your doctor from your own home and sharing health information from your smart device as part of that conversation. Now imagine your doctor having real-time access to evidence on how to best care for you – that is the power of artificial intelligence (AI). Through computer-enabled learning, we can use patterns of evidence and machine problem solving to take patients’ personalized information and couple that with the best evidence to improve their outcomes. Predictive models can be used to identify patients at risk, what outcomes may be expected and how to improve their care. We will harness the power of information and advanced digital solutions to positively impact quality care, experience and operational excellence. Together with our patients, we will co-design technology solutions which focus on patient convenience and a more personalized experience. We will connect care using smart technologies to create a seamless health care journey for everyone in our care. And we will lead in the use of advanced analytics and AI to ensure evidence guides our decisions.. - Have a network-wide electronic patient record.: - Have co-developed solutions to enhance access, quality and experience for our patients and providers.: - Be a real-time health system, actively using data to inform clinical and management decisions.: - Use digital tools to support our workforce, internal planning and to integrate to the broader health system.: - Be known as a leading organization that demonstrates how data and digital can revolutionize the quality and experience of care, education and research through deep integration of analytics with operations.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The focus is on using AI and digital solutions to improve healthcare, with a strong emphasis on enhancing patient convenience, experience, and quality of care.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,980
980,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,Investing In Our Future,"Investing In Our Future. Being good stewards of public resources is a hallmark left to us by our founders, the Sisters of St. Joseph of Toronto. Coming together as THE_HOSPITAL Health allows us to be more efficient in our work and to create opportunities for collaboration across our sites. We will continue to make thoughtful and prudent choices that drive maximum value from existing funding, support excellent patient care and drive our strategic plan. We will empower our teams to develop innovative ways of creating organizational value. We will work together with our Foundations to create innovative and inspirational solutions to improve patient care. We will be respected for our environmental stewardship. And we will be known as a leader in shaping new integrated funding and care models that maximize public resources – all in a time of transformative change in Ontario.. - Build a nimble culture that makes decisions through a value lens.: - Be stewards of the environment by reducing the impact we make on the planet.: - Be a leader in shaping new funding and care models as well as maximize existing funding envelopes.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on being good stewards of resources, driving value from funding, and making decisions through a value lens, indicating financial sustainability and organizational culture.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,UNITY HEALTH TORONTO,980
983,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,People Engaging With Passion,"People Engaging With Passion. We are guided by a simple but powerful principle: “Nothing for you, without you.” This applies to everyone—patients, families, caregivers, staff, physicians, and volunteers. By centering people in our work, we build meaningful partnerships in both care delivery and service design. Our highest priority is providing a safe and healthy workplace. In addition to delivering compassionate, high-quality care, THE_HOSPITAL is committed to environmental sustainability by reducing our operational impact. To those who live and work in the communities we serve, we commit to being transparent, engaged, and bold advocates for the changes needed to support both a healthier population, and high-quality care—now and in the future.. • Advance Social Accountability: Focus health priorities on marginalized or underserved populations.: • Drive Exceptional Experiences: Deliver timely, equitable, culturally safe, and collaborative person-centered care.: • Foster Proactive Engagement: Engage patients, caregivers, staff, partners, and communities in health promotion, illness prevention, and service design.: • Kindness First: Empathy and kindness will guide our actions in a culture that values equity, inclusion, diversity, and anti-racism.: • Values-Based: Compassion, Accountability, and Integrity will be evident in all that we do.: • Listening Intently: Feedback from patients, families, caregivers, volunteers, staff, partners, and community members will drive continuous improvement.: • Developing All: Staff and volunteers will be supported through ongoing learning and development.: • Communicate Clearly: We will promote transparency and ensure all voices help shape the organization’s direction and tone.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text emphasizes values, social accountability, equity, inclusion, and engagement, pointing to a focus on organizational culture and addressing the needs of marginalized populations.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,983
983,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,Partnership Collaborating With Purpose,"Partnership Collaborating With Purpose. Partnerships are central to transforming healthcare into a truly person-centered system. THE_HOSPITAL recognizes that we are stronger together. Many of the most significant improvements occur when providers collaborate across traditional boundaries. This ensures care is delivered at the right time, in the right place, and by the right provider. Whether in primary care, public health, long-term care, home and community care, hospital services, mental health, or emergency response—our collective impact is greatest when we work together, united in service to those we care for.. • Foster Collaborative Relationships: Build trusted partnerships grounded in mutual respect and shared accountability.: • Advance Integrated Care: Improve coordination across the care continuum to enhance access, quality, and experience.: • Drive System Transformation: Serve as a catalyst for innovation and alignment across the healthcare system.: • Population Health-Centered Decisions: Focus on improving community health outcomes.: • Inclusive Governance: Engage all stakeholders in decisions that impact them.: • Shared Capability: Contribute THE_HOSPITAL’s knowledge and expertise to build system-wide capacity.: • Barrier Reduction: Identify and eliminate obstacles to accessing high-quality care.: • System Alignment: Align goals, processes, and protocols with partners to enable seamless care.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The text emphasizes collaboration and partnerships across the healthcare system to improve care and community health outcomes, aligning with integration and population health focuses.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,983
983,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,Performance Exceeding Expectations,"Performance Exceeding Expectations. Strong performance is critical—not only for THE_HOSPITAL but for the entire health system. Healthcare is a vital public service and one of Canada’s largest sectors. It must be grounded in responsible business practices that protect financial sustainability and ensure timely, appropriate care. Above all, healthcare must be accountable. At THE_HOSPITAL, we evaluate our work through this lens—ensuring services are grounded in engagement, innovation, evidence, and best practice, and are delivered in the most efficient and effective setting.. • Foster Responsible Resource Management: Use human, financial, physical, and technological resources ethically, efficiently, and effectively.: • Advance Digital Innovation: Use technology to enhance care delivery and system performance.: • Drive Exceptional Quality Care: Provide care that is person-centered, safe, timely, equitable, and continuously improved.: • Clear, Transparent Priorities: Align resource allocation with organizational and system goals.: • Aligned Performance Indicators: Set annual goals that support strategic objectives.: • Timely Access: Place priority on investments that improve access to appropriate care.: • Leading Practices: Apply evidence-based standards and best practices.: • Exceptional Performance: Equip staff with tools and information to meet high standards.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text emphasizes responsible resource management, digital innovation, and aligning resource allocation with organizational goals, highlighting financial sustainability and the use of technology.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,983
654,"Espanola & Area Family Health Team, espanola regional hospital and health centre",Build Upon Patient-Centred Care Through Quality And Safety,"Build Upon Patient-Centred Care Through Quality And Safety. In recognition of the important core of providing patient-centred care, and understanding the growing focus on safety and quality in all aspects within our operations, we will use this Pillar to focus our efforts. In addition, patients and their experiences are a wealth of knowledge to tap into. When we bring the voice of patients to the planning table, through engaging with Patient Advisors, we learn, improve and grow in our abilities to fulfil our caring Mission.. ✓ Bring the Patient's Voice to the Forefront, through Growing Roles for Patient Advisors: ✓ Collaborate with Partners to Streamline Care Pathways: ✓ Partner with First Nations to Strengthen Cultural Safety & Competency: ✓ Participate in Major eHealth Strategies.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on patient-centered care, quality, safety, involving patient advisors, partnering with First Nations, and participating in eHealth strategies.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,"Espanola & Area Family Health Team, espanola regional hospital and health centre",654
654,"Espanola & Area Family Health Team, espanola regional hospital and health centre",Enhance Care Coordination And Capacity,"Enhance Care Coordination And Capacity. We know how important it is to work towards a more seamless health journey for our patients, because the system itself is so complex and specialized. In addition, providing a comprehensive basket of services close-to-home is also important. This forms the basis for Pillar Number 2.. ✓ Focus on Care Transitions: ✓ Explore Home and Community Care Enhancements: ✓ Grow Access to Priority Programs (Mental Health & Addictions, Chronic Diseases, End-of-Life Care, Patient Transportation).",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text focuses on seamless health journeys and comprehensive services, indicating integration, while also addressing access to priority programs.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,"Espanola & Area Family Health Team, espanola regional hospital and health centre",654
654,"Espanola & Area Family Health Team, espanola regional hospital and health centre","Embrace System Change, Grow Through Collaboration","Embrace System Change, Grow Through Collaboration. With the number of fundamentally transformative changes that are occurring within the health care system, we know that to continue to be successful as an organization, we must evolve and adapt to best take advantage of these changes. In addition, we know that the voice of small, rural, health care providers and patients must reach the ears of government, so as to influence policy and program changes. This Pillar strongly articulates this need.. ✓ Take an Active Leadership Role to Influence New Policy Directions: ✓ Advocate for Rural Care Models that Grow Equity of Access and are Respectful of Cultural Diversity: ✓ Collaborate with Partners towards a Local Ontario Health Team.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text emphasizes collaboration within the healthcare system, advocating for rural care models, and partnering towards a Local Ontario Health Team, while also focusing on equity of access and cultural diversity.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,"Espanola & Area Family Health Team, espanola regional hospital and health centre",654
654,"Espanola & Area Family Health Team, espanola regional hospital and health centre",Invest In Our People,"Invest In Our People. Healthcare is a people-oriented service; we work for patients, through the hands, minds, and hearts of our care-givers. All staff and clinicians have an important role to play in this. Every function within our Organization, whether it is direct hands-on care, or in various supportive roles, ultimately impacts upon our patients. Thus, we have selected Pillar Number 4 as key to our future efforts over the next 5 years.. ✓ Enhance our Patient-Focus: ✓ Grow our Just Culture across the Organization: ✓ Utilize Focused Training Opportunities to Grow Expertise & Competencies throughout the Continuum of Care.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The focus is on investing in staff, training, and growing expertise, which are all key elements of workforce sustainability, further enhanced by a just culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,"Espanola & Area Family Health Team, espanola regional hospital and health centre",654
655,Huron Health System,Partnering With Patients & Families,Partnering With Patients & Families. We will partner with patients and families in the provision of quality person-centred care. Improve patient care through timely access to an array of health services offered through a collaborative care approach. Enhance coordinated care and care transitions by working together with our health care partners across our region. Help patients and families to make informed decisions and be more active in their care through two-way communication and improved access to information and education. Tailor our services to ensure that resources are matched to the requirements of the individuals we serve and that we are responding to the needs of our community.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on improving patient care through collaboration, access, and information, with an emphasis on partnering with patients and families and healthcare partners.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Huron Health System,655
655,Huron Health System,Empowering Our People,"Empowering Our People. We are passionate about our people and work hard to support an empowered and engaged team.. Create a high trust organization where all members of our care community feel supported, appreciated, and inspired to share their ideas and expertise. Provide relevant development opportunities and training aligned with the goals and learning needs of our team members including volunteers, students, staff, physicians, and governors. Establish processes to create, retain and actively transfer knowledge throughout our organization to enable continuous improvement.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on supporting, developing, and retaining staff, creating a positive work environment, and knowledge transfer within the organization.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Huron Health System,655
655,Huron Health System,Ensuring Operational Excellence,"Ensuring Operational Excellence. We will optimize our processes and align operational efforts to make the best use of our resources.. Strengthen our use of data and technology to ensure efficiencies and to effectively articulate our resource requirements. Complete clinical services planning to clearly define the services to be provided at each site and the required ongoing investment to ensure our programs are sustainable. Modernize our infrastructure and capital assets in alignment with our clinical services plan. Reduce unnecessary duplication and standardize our processes, tools, and technology across our sites to optimize the resources available for direct patient care.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text focuses on optimizing resources, improving efficiencies, and modernizing infrastructure to ensure financial sustainability.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Huron Health System,655
655,Huron Health System,Innovating Through Partnership,Innovating Through Partnership. We will work with our partners to find innovative approaches that meet the needs of the communities we serve.. Provide leadership as partners in the development of our regional health system and the establishment of integrated care strategies that span the health care continuum. Contribute to the strengthening of upstream and community-based resources so that our hospitals can focus on the necessary care that we provide as part of our regional health care community. Identify and advance cross-system opportunities for cost saving initiatives that will enable re-investment in community care.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,The text focuses on working with partners to develop integrated care strategies and identifying cost-saving initiatives across the system.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Huron Health System,655
656,Wellington Health Care Alliance,"Champion Diversity, Equity, And Inclusion In Everything We Do.","Champion Diversity, Equity, And Inclusion In Everything We Do.. NF. • Including DEI as the foundational enabler of each strategic pillar: • Committing to co-design and advance a health equity plan in alignment with our communities and people we serve.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text explicitly mentions Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion as a foundational enabler and commitment to a health equity plan, aligning with both health equity and the organization's values.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Wellington Health Care Alliance,656
661,Cambridge Memorial Hospital,Advance Health Equity,"Advance Health Equity. Advance Health Equity promotes the need for diversity, equity, and inclusion to increase equitable access to healthcare and support a work culture where every individual can reach their full potential.. * Make meaningful change to our culture to establish THE_HOSPITAL as a safe space where all individuals can access the care they need and team members are empowered to perform to the best of their ability. (Diversity, Equity and Inclusion Plan): * Advance the Truth and Reconciliation Commission of Canada's Call to Action 22: ""Recognize the value of Aboriginal healing practices and use them in the treatment of Aboriginal patients in collaboration with Aboriginal healers and Elders where requested by Aboriginal patients."" (Indigenous Reconciliation Action Plan): * Promote, provide and maintain an environment where respect, independence, and dignity are demonstrated at all times to everyone. (Accessibility Plan): * Create inclusive and integrated care experiences that support the well-being and independence of older adults and care partners. (Seniors Health Plan).",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on diversity, equity, and inclusion initiatives, addressing both patient access and workforce culture, with specific mentions of Indigenous reconciliation and accessibility.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Cambridge Memorial Hospital,661
661,Cambridge Memorial Hospital,Elevate Partnerships In Care,"Elevate Partnerships In Care. Elevate Partnerships in Care highlights the importance of collaboration across all levels to ensure the highest quality and safest care experience.. * Improve access to care by reducing wait times, establishing community partnerships, creating new and innovative opportunities to become a leading community hospital in our region. (Clinical Services Growth Plan): * Strive to be a leader in consistently partnering with patients by respecting them as individuals, and valuing the role of their support system. (Patient Experience Plan): * Maintain exemplary standing with Accreditation Canada. (Quality and Safety Plan): * Establish a Site Master Plan to address clinical and non-clinical growth opportunities and a Building Systems Requirements Plan for renewals and upgrades required to meet current and future needs of THE_HOSPITAL. (Capital Redevelopment Plan).",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text emphasizes collaboration and partnerships across all levels to improve care quality and access, alongside a focus on patient experience and maintaining accreditation standards.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Cambridge Memorial Hospital,661
661,Cambridge Memorial Hospital,Reimagine Community Health,"Reimagine Community Health. Reimagine Community health demonstrates how we will use innovation and embrace transformation to improve the way we deliver healthcare.. * Transform the healthcare journey. (Cambridge North Dumfries Ontario Health Team Plan): * Create a digital infrastructure which supports THE_HOSPITAL's vision for the future as evidenced by increasing the abilities of our electronic medical record as well as implementation of organizational support systems. (Digital Health Plan): * Advance projects that make a practical difference to our community and establish a stronger identity in research and innovation. (Research and Innovation Plan): * Increase organizational capabilities to gain insight from analytics for operational and strategic decision making by making performance data more accessible, strengthening data quality and increasing knowledge and understanding performance data. (Operational Excellence Plan).",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on digital infrastructure and innovation within the OHT framework to improve healthcare delivery, emphasizing both technology and integration.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Cambridge Memorial Hospital,661
661,Cambridge Memorial Hospital,Increase Joy In Work,"Increase Joy In Work. Increase Joy in Work reflects our commitment to improving the well-being of our team by creating meaningful and enabling work environments.. * Provide the resources and expertise to support a healthy and engaged workforce that holds a positive attitude toward the organization and the patients we serve. Together, we will create an inclusive work community where people are valued and experience joy in work which is foundational to creating an exceptional healthcare organization. (Human Resources Plan, Employee and Physician Engagement Plan, Wellness and Well-Being Plan): * Support, highlight and breathe life into the stories that anchors the hospital's vision, mission and values. (Corporate Communications and Engagement Plan).",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The primary focus is on improving employee well-being and engagement, which aligns with workforce sustainability, while also highlighting the importance of the organization's mission and values, falling under organizational culture and governance.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Cambridge Memorial Hospital,661
661,Cambridge Memorial Hospital,Sustain Financial Health,"Sustain Financial Health. Sustain Financial Health shows our dedication to not only keeping a balanced budget but also building a strong foundation for investment and growth.. * Have funds available for strategic investments to implement the Clinical Services Growth plan, complete the Capital Redevelopment Project and implement new systems to support hospital operations. (Multi-year Financial Plan): * Make investments to complete the Capital Redevelopment Project, modernize information systems, make ongoing facility improvements, and purchase required medical equipment. (Multi-year Capital Plan).",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text focuses on maintaining financial stability, strategic investments, capital redevelopment projects, facility improvements, and equipment purchases.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Cambridge Memorial Hospital,661
662,L'HÔPITAL DU DISTRICT DE GERALDTON DISTRICT HOSPITAL GERALDTON OODENA AAKOZIIWIGAMIG,Invest In Care,"Invest In Care. Building for our Future. * Reduce the need to travel outside of Geraldton for health services: * Modernize the facilities at THE_HOSPITAL: * Invest in medical imaging and diagnostic equipment (i.e., CT scanner): * Focus on clinical integration opportunities (i.e., Hospital Information System upgrade): * Redevelop the first floor of the hospital: * Invest in health services to accommodate the growing seniors' population.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on modernizing facilities, investing in equipment, and redevelopment, which are all infrastructure-related, while also mentioning clinical integration opportunities.",Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,L'HÔPITAL DU DISTRICT DE GERALDTON DISTRICT HOSPITAL GERALDTON OODENA AAKOZIIWIGAMIG,662
662,L'HÔPITAL DU DISTRICT DE GERALDTON DISTRICT HOSPITAL GERALDTON OODENA AAKOZIIWIGAMIG,Unleash Our Potential,Unleash Our Potential. Innovation & Creativity to Empower our People. * Seek opportunities for healthcare workforce innovation: * Aim to fully staff the hospital; no more agency staffing: * Focus on succession planning and leadership development: * Develop creative recruitment and retention strategies: * Recruit families and communities: * Work with Municipalities and Townships.,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on strategies to improve workforce issues such as staffing, recruitment, retention, and leadership development.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,L'HÔPITAL DU DISTRICT DE GERALDTON DISTRICT HOSPITAL GERALDTON OODENA AAKOZIIWIGAMIG,662
662,L'HÔPITAL DU DISTRICT DE GERALDTON DISTRICT HOSPITAL GERALDTON OODENA AAKOZIIWIGAMIG,Collaborate With Partners,Collaborate With Partners. Better Care through Collaboration. * Strengthen our relationships with Greenstone health service providers: * Work with area First Nations communities: * Look for ways to work with partners.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,The text focuses on collaborating with external health service providers and First Nations communities to improve care.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,L'HÔPITAL DU DISTRICT DE GERALDTON DISTRICT HOSPITAL GERALDTON OODENA AAKOZIIWIGAMIG,662
663,Huron Health System,Partnering With Patients & Families,Partnering With Patients & Families. We will partner with patients and families in the provision of quality person-centred care. * Improve patient care through timely access to an array of health services offered through a collaborative care approach: * Enhance coordinated care and care transitions by working together with our health care partners across our region: * Help patients and families to make informed decisions and be more active in their care through two-way communication and improved access to information and education: * Tailor our services to ensure that resources are matched to the requirements of the individuals we serve and that we are responding to the needs of our community.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,The focus is on improving patient care through collaborative and coordinated approaches with healthcare partners.,Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Huron Health System,663
663,Huron Health System,Empowering Our People,"Empowering Our People. We are passionate about our people and work hard to support an empowered and engaged team.. * Create a high trust organization where all members of our care community feel supported, appreciated, and inspired to share their ideas and expertise: * Provide relevant development opportunities and training aligned with the goals and learning needs of our team members including volunteers, students, staff, physicians, and governors: * Establish processes to create, retain and actively transfer knowledge throughout our organization to enable continuous improvement.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on supporting and empowering the workforce through development, training, and creating a high-trust environment, which aligns with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Huron Health System,663
663,Huron Health System,Ensuring Operational Excellence,"Ensuring Operational Excellence. We will optimize our processes and align operational efforts to make the best use of our resources.. * Strengthen our use of data and technology to ensure efficiencies and to effectively articulate our resource requirements: * Complete clinical services planning to clearly define the services to be provided at each site and the required ongoing investment to ensure our programs are sustainable: * Modernize our infrastructure and capital assets in alignment with our clinical services plan: * Reduce unnecessary duplication and standardize our processes, tools, and technology across our sites to optimize the resources available for direct patient care.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text focuses on optimizing processes, resource utilization, and reducing duplication to ensure efficiencies and sustainability, while also mentioning infrastructure modernization.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Huron Health System,663
663,Huron Health System,Innovating Through Partnership,Innovating Through Partnership. We will work with our partners to find innovative approaches that meet the needs of the communities we serve.. * Provide leadership as partners in the development of our regional health system and the establishment of integrated care strategies that span the health care continuum: * Contribute to the strengthening of upstream and community-based resources so that our hospitals can focus on the necessary care that we provide as part of our regional health care community: * Identify and advance cross-system opportunities for cost saving initiatives that will enable re-investment in community care.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,The text focuses on working with partners to develop integrated care strategies and identify cost-saving opportunities across the system.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Huron Health System,663
665,GUELPH GENERAL HOSPITAL,Welcome Patients And Care Partners As Team Members,Welcome Patients And Care Partners As Team Members. NF. NF.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on improving patient experience by integrating patients and care partners into the care team, which also reflects a shift in organizational culture.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,GUELPH GENERAL HOSPITAL,665
665,GUELPH GENERAL HOSPITAL,Invest In Our Team,Invest In Our Team. NF. NF.,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,"The title ""Invest In Our Team"" implies a focus on workforce (likely recruitment, retention, or wellness) which often involves financial considerations.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,GUELPH GENERAL HOSPITAL,665
665,GUELPH GENERAL HOSPITAL,Collaborate To Provide Integrated Patient Care,Collaborate To Provide Integrated Patient Care. NF. NF.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The focus is on integrated care, implying collaboration and aiming for better patient outcomes.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,GUELPH GENERAL HOSPITAL,665
665,GUELPH GENERAL HOSPITAL,"Use Technology To Enhance Quality, Efficiency, And Safety","Use Technology To Enhance Quality, Efficiency, And Safety. NF. NF.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The title emphasizes technology use (digital health) to improve quality and safety (patient care excellence), along with efficiency gains (financial sustainability aspect, but less emphasized).",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,GUELPH GENERAL HOSPITAL,665
665,GUELPH GENERAL HOSPITAL,Design And Plan For The Future,Design And Plan For The Future. NF. NF.,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,None,"This title suggests a focus on strategic planning and organizational direction, aligning with themes of leadership and governance.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,GUELPH GENERAL HOSPITAL,665
666,St. Joseph's HEALTH CENTRE GUELPH,Leading,"Leading. We will have explored, designed, and developed an integrated care delivery system with our Guelph and Area partners to improve health outcomes and integrated care in our community.. * With our partners, develop a local plan to deliver integrated health services as a core member of an early adopter Ontario Health Team: * Co-design and implement a model of care based around the needs of people: * Lead the enhancement of the elder care experience across the St. Joseph's Health System: * Optimize outpatient services.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,The text focuses on developing an integrated care delivery system with partners to improve health outcomes and enhance the elder care experience.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's HEALTH CENTRE GUELPH,666
666,St. Joseph's HEALTH CENTRE GUELPH,Learning,"Learning. Through our commitment to learning, we will have optimized resources and ensured financial stability. To achieve this, we will have successfully explored, designed, and implemented systems, processes, and technologies for integration.. * Continue to raise the bar around client experience and quality standards: * Create program, change management, and communications functions to enable strategic goals: * Support an initiative consistent with our mission in the Guelph community: * Improve access to care in our Geriatric clinic: * Implement a 5-Year IT Strategic Plan, with supporting cross-functional capital planning.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text emphasizes optimized resources and financial stability through integrated systems and technologies, alongside strategic goals and IT planning.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's HEALTH CENTRE GUELPH,666
666,St. Joseph's HEALTH CENTRE GUELPH,Building,Building. We will have continued to build an integrated Campus of Care that will provide options and services for seniors in our community.. * Build a shared vision for the future of the property: * Complete the Silver Maple Seniors Townhomes Community Project: * Increase our renewable energy consumption: * Expand long-term care and priority acuity beds.,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on building an integrated campus of care for seniors, expanding long-term care beds, and increasing renewable energy consumption, indicating a focus on physical infrastructure and integrating services for seniors.",Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's HEALTH CENTRE GUELPH,666
666,St. Joseph's HEALTH CENTRE GUELPH,Caring,"Caring. We will have an inspired, motivated, and integrated community of care; where safety and wellness are prioritized.. * Create an integrated people strategy: * Attract, hire, and retain values-driven, high-performing staff: * Ensure a ready pipeline of volunteers: * Increase leadership bench strength.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on attracting, retaining, and integrating staff, along with prioritizing wellness and leadership development, which aligns with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's HEALTH CENTRE GUELPH,666
674,St. Joseph's Health System,Advance Health Beyond Boundaries,Advance Health Beyond Boundaries. NF. • Reimagine integrated care to empower individuals as they live and thrive in our communities: • Address health inequities and remove barriers to care for priority population groups across THE_HOSPITAL.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,The text focuses on integrated care and addressing health inequities for priority populations.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's Health System,674
674,St. Joseph's Health System,Amplify Our Collective Impact,Amplify Our Collective Impact. NF. • Leverage THE_HOSPITAL scope and scale to support shared priorities and optimize care delivery: • Live the legacy of the Sisters of St. Joseph through THE_HOSPITAL-wide collaboration and partnership.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text emphasizes collaboration, partnership, and leveraging the hospital's scope to optimize care, aligning with integration and partnership, while also highlighting the hospital's legacy and values, connecting to organizational culture.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's Health System,674
674,St. Joseph's Health System,Invest In Teams Of Today And Tomorrow,"Invest In Teams Of Today And Tomorrow. NF. • Attract and retain the next generation of health leaders, clinicians and researchers: • Build common learning ecosystems across THE_HOSPITAL to support the teams of today and train the teams of tomorrow.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS","The text focuses on attracting, retaining, and training healthcare professionals, aligning with workforce sustainability, and mentions building learning ecosystems, indicating a research and education component.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,St. Joseph's Health System,674
676,HANOVER & DISTRICT HOSPITAL,Caring For Our Patients,"Caring For Our Patients. We will provide high quality patient and family-centred care.. • Provide exceptional care for all who come through our doors.: • Monitor and measure our performance using quality metrics.: • Be laser-focused about caring for our patients, their families and our community.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"Focus on providing high-quality patient care and aligning the organization's focus on patient well-being, suggesting both quality improvement and a culture that prioritizes patients.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,HANOVER & DISTRICT HOSPITAL,676
676,HANOVER & DISTRICT HOSPITAL,Valuing Our People & Teams,"Valuing Our People & Teams. We will continue to value, invest in and recognize our teams.. • Continue to value, invest in and recognize our people and teams.: • Prioritize the growth and well-being of our people and teams.: • Strategically use our resources to achieve our goals.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on valuing, investing in, and recognizing the workforce, as well as prioritizing their growth and well-being, aligning with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,HANOVER & DISTRICT HOSPITAL,676
676,HANOVER & DISTRICT HOSPITAL,Innovating For A Sustainable Future,Innovating For A Sustainable Future. We will advance a forward-thinking culture into our operations to ensure our sustainability.. • Ensure fiscal responsibility and financial stability.: • Identify innovative solutions to ensure our sustainability.: • Advocate for enhanced resources to strengthen our ability to care for our patients and community.,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on fiscal responsibility and innovative solutions for sustainability, indicating financial concerns and a forward-thinking organizational culture.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,HANOVER & DISTRICT HOSPITAL,676
676,HANOVER & DISTRICT HOSPITAL,Anticipating & Responding,Anticipating & Responding. We will actively engage with our community and partners to understand and address community needs.. • Lead with purpose.: • Align our efforts with those of Ontario Health and our local health care partners.: • Anticipate and respond to the needs of our community through active engagement and partnerships.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,The text emphasizes engaging with the community and partners to address community needs and align efforts with Ontario Health.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,HANOVER & DISTRICT HOSPITAL,676
684,Rural Roads Health Services,Our Strategic Priorities,"Our Strategic Priorities. NF. - Together, pursue fulsome organizational integration toward better patient care and best use of our resources: - Proud of our rural roots, as small and unique hospitals, advance our service delivery model: - With our partners, serve our communities exceptionally well by creating an integrated system: - We are powered by our people, and commit to supporting them to be at their best.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The priorities focus on organizational integration for better patient care and working with partners to create an integrated system, with a secondary emphasis on excellent patient experience.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Rural Roads Health Services,684
686,Lady Dunn Health Centre,Strategic Goal #1 Focus On Quality In Delivering Our Services,"Strategic Goal #1 Focus On Quality In Delivering Our Services. In focusing on quality we hold ourselves to the highest standards by ensuring that we deliver care based on evidence based best practices and by always putting clients first.. • Continuously improve and resource processes to ensure quality results.: • Implement and consistently apply quality standards and checks in delivering care while focusing on environmental stewardship.: • Deliver services to meet the linguistic and cultural needs of Francophones and Indigenous People as well as other diverse groups.: • Implement the ONE Project, partnering with regional health service providers to share a common health information system.: • Advance the scope of registered staff.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"This goal explicitly focuses on quality of care delivery, evidence-based practices, and addressing the needs of diverse populations including Francophones and Indigenous People.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lady Dunn Health Centre,686
686,Lady Dunn Health Centre,Strategic Goal #2 Create And Sustain Organizational Resilience,"Strategic Goal #2 Create And Sustain Organizational Resilience. By increasing resilience, we increase our effectiveness and help to ensure our sustainability.. • Continue to support staff members in creating a harmonious, safe and healthy work environment.: • Develop project management and change management methodologies to use consistently.: • Increase the capacity and engagement of organization leaders in developing, monitoring, and managing their budgets.: • Strengthen processes relating to recruitment, retention and succession planning.: • Expand on successes in clinical training to provide comprehensive training opportunities for all staff.: • Integrate technology in how we work in all areas.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This goal focuses on supporting staff, developing leaders, strengthening processes for recruitment/retention, and providing training, all contributing to workforce sustainability and organizational resilience.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lady Dunn Health Centre,686
686,Lady Dunn Health Centre,Strategic Goal #3 Integrate And Partner With Others To Better Serve Our Communities,"Strategic Goal #3 Integrate And Partner With Others To Better Serve Our Communities. Through partnerships and collaboration, we lead and participate in the development of a high performing health care system locally, regionally and province wide.. • Continue to develop our local campus of care and Ontario Health Team partnership.: • Seek out and participate in initiatives that will develop or enhance services to meet community needs.: • Partner with others in support of the mental health of our community.: • Communicate effectively with all stakeholders to ensure awareness of THE_HOSPITAL’s services, issues and shared opportunities.: • Showcase different staff roles.: • Explore opportunities for shared resources and roles.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The goal focuses on partnerships, collaboration, and integration within the healthcare system and community, specifically mentioning the Ontario Health Team and mental health initiatives.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lady Dunn Health Centre,686
686,Lady Dunn Health Centre,Strategic Goal #4 Seek And Optimize Financial Resources,"Strategic Goal #4 Seek And Optimize Financial Resources. Through partnerships and collaboration we will lead and participate in the development of a high-performing health care system locally, regionally and province wide.. • Capitalize on funded regional and Ministry opportunities as they arise (e.g. outpatient laboratory services, Meditech 6.1, Home and Community Care, LTC home expansion).: • Use performance indicators to support the allocation of resources.: • Identify and explore new revenue streams.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The goal focuses on optimizing financial resources through partnerships, capitalizing on opportunities, and exploring new revenue streams.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lady Dunn Health Centre,686
695,Providence Care,Quality More Participation.,"Quality More Participation.. the hospital enhances the quality of life for the people we serve, demonstrating that:. > Our people foster meaningful partnerships with the people we serve to achieve the best possible outcomes and experiences.: > Our teams strive to exceed standards of excellence through a commitment to equity and accountability.: > We embrace quality improvement, driven by collaboration and a shared vision for better care and services.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on improving outcomes and experiences for patients through excellence, equity, accountability, and a commitment to quality improvement, while also emphasizing partnerships and a shared vision which speaks to organizational culture.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Providence Care,695
695,Providence Care,Research & Innovation More Imagination.,"Research & Innovation More Imagination.. the hospital drives meaningful improvement through innovation, guided by research and learning, demonstrating that:. > A culture of curiosity and transformation is nurtured.: > Our teams actively seek, generate, and apply best practices to deliver equitable, person-centered care.: > Research is advanced by fostering discovery and encouraging diverse perspectives.: > We share our knowledge openly to inspire progress and benefit the broader community.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text explicitly mentions research, discovery, learning, and knowledge sharing, indicating a focus on research and academic activities, while also highlighting a culture of curiosity and transformation.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Providence Care,695
695,Providence Care,Sustainability More Opportunity.,"Sustainability More Opportunity.. the hospital manages our resources thoughtfully and sustainably, demonstrating that:. > Our resources are maximized to meet the diverse needs of our people and the communities we serve.: > Our services are strategically integrated to create lasting value and equitable access.: > Our investments prioritize improvements that enhance the well-being of individuals, care of the earth, and long-term community health.: > A culture of generosity, collaboration and shared responsibility thrives.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text emphasizes resource maximization, strategic integration for equitable access, and investments prioritizing community well-being, aligning with financial sustainability and health equity.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Providence Care,695
695,Providence Care,Access More Connections.,"Access More Connections.. the hospital partners across the continuum of care to improve equitable access for all, demonstrating that:. > Our services are widely recognized and adapt to emerging needs.: > Our services are inclusive, trusted, and accessible to individuals of all identities, abilities, and backgrounds - free from discrimination and system inequities.: > Our services support reconciliation and respect for Indigenous identities, histories, and cultures.: > Our teams build respectful partnerships to optimize transitions in care and enhance the experience of those we serve.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on improving equitable access, addressing discrimination and system inequities, supporting reconciliation with Indigenous communities, and building partnerships for transitions in care.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Providence Care,695
695,Providence Care,Inclusive & Healthy Workplace More Belonging.,"Inclusive & Healthy Workplace More Belonging.. the hospital fosters the health, well-being, and belonging of everyone who works, learns, or volunteers with us, demonstrating that:. > Our workplaces are inclusive, safe and promote overall well-being free from discrimination and systemic inequities.: > Our people are encouraged to pursue lifelong learning, continuous growth, and development.: > Our people feel valued and appreciated through recognition of their contributions and perspectives.: > Our communication is dynamic and effective.: > Our leaders are visible and accessible.: > Our people are accountable and supported in their roles.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on employee well-being, inclusivity, and leadership support within the workplace.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,Providence Care,695
704,Erie Shores HealthCare,Chosen Workplace,"Chosen Workplace. Recruit and retain the best talent to have an inclusive, high performing organization.. • Develop and implement a framework for embedding diversity, equity, and inclusive approaches at all levels of the organization.: • Incorporate continuous quality improvement into organizational processes to ensure effective operations, resource management (human, financial and physical), and adaptation to change.: • Advance internal communications efforts to improve employee knowledge and transparency of organizational goals, objectives, and priorities.: • Support regular and meaningful employee engagement and recognition to acknowledge the value of internal expertise and input, and to celebrate successes.: • Collaborate with academic and professional entities to create learning and research opportunities for those within the organization and those who may join the organization in the future.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on attracting and retaining talent, embedding DEI, and improving employee engagement and recognition, which all contribute to workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Erie Shores HealthCare,704
704,Erie Shores HealthCare,Smart Growth,"Smart Growth. Innovate and scale for effective, responsible, and sustainable stewardship.. • Achieve financial health and increase capacity to respond to emerging needs and reinvest in people, equipment, and systems.: • Explore all opportunities to secure funding tailored to the unique needs of the community.: • Increase community awareness, engagement and organization visibility across all catchment areas and priority populations.: • Accelerate patient outcomes through compelling technology and ingenious infrastructure.: • Implement innovative and collaborative staffing structures that strengthen human capacity within the hospital and across the regional health system.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text emphasizes financial health, funding opportunities, technology, and innovative staffing structures, aligning with financial sustainability and digital innovation.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Erie Shores HealthCare,704
704,Erie Shores HealthCare,Care Excellence,"Care Excellence. Provide high quality inclusive care one patient at a time to be their chosen hospital.. • Advance diversity, equity, and inclusion efforts to improve patient outcomes and genuine care experiences.: • Formalize an action plan to address Truth & Reconciliation and support Indigenous peoples care within the hospital.: • Increase the consistency of quality outcomes and standards of care across clinical units and core services.: • Develop a comprehensive strategy to address the unique and diverse needs of patients and the broader community.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on providing high-quality, inclusive care, improving patient outcomes, and addressing diversity, equity, and inclusion, alongside supporting Indigenous peoples' care.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Erie Shores HealthCare,704
704,Erie Shores HealthCare,Connected Partner,"Connected Partner. Be a leader, collaborator, and advocate within the regional health system.. • Collaborate with Indigenous communities to develop a relationship agreement framework.: • Establish strategic partnerships that advance access and health outcomes for the local population and evolving community needs.: • Develop partnerships with primary care to enhance the care continuum and patient experience.: • Foster relationships across health system and community services organizations to address the mental health and substance use needs of the community.: • Empower patients as partners in their own health and integrate their voices in care design, delivery, and transitions.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on collaboration within the regional health system, with Indigenous communities, and with primary care to improve access and health outcomes, highlighting both integration and health equity.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Erie Shores HealthCare,704
681,Hôpital Notre-Dame Hospital (Hearst),Our Patients,Our Patients. Providing exceptional and safe care. • Involving patients and their families with the care team: • Smooth navigation through the care continuum: • Providing safe and appropriate care: • Patient-centered care in all its dimensions.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,None,"The text focuses on providing exceptional, safe, and patient-centered care, directly aligning with patient care excellence.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Hôpital Notre-Dame Hospital (Hearst),681
681,Hôpital Notre-Dame Hospital (Hearst),Our People,Our People. Creating a healthy and safe work environment focused on well-being. • Attract new talents: • Communication and teamwork: • Culture of professional development and mentoring: • Employee retention: • Reduction of adverse events.,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text emphasizes a healthy work environment, attracting talent, employee retention, and reducing adverse events which are all essential components of workforce sustainability and contribute to patient safety.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Hôpital Notre-Dame Hospital (Hearst),681
