681,Hôpital Notre-Dame Hospital (Hearst),Our Growth,Our Growth. Grow sustainably and creatively to meet future needs. • Awareness of the changing needs of our communities: • Encourage innovation: • Promotion of an eco-responsible culture.,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text focuses on sustainable growth and meeting future needs, indicating financial considerations, while also mentioning an eco-responsible culture, which relates to the environment.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Hôpital Notre-Dame Hospital (Hearst),681
696,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,System Integration,"System Integration. THE_HOSPITAL believes that each organization has strength and capacity to provide excellent services and by working together, actively removing barriers, we can respond to people's holistic needs timely, we can prevent people needing help falling through the cracks, and we can uphold a world-class healthcare system for all.. • Policies, processes, procurement, equipment, supplies are reviewed and streamlined for both sites.: • Appropriate committees are formed and sustained to support standardization (eg. product evaluation, signage).: • Forum that gets partners together (eg. Health huddle) are supported / co-established.: • Common platforms such as policies, Meditech Expanse, bulk purchasing, bulk subscriptions are explored with partners.: • Explore ways to collaborate meaningfully, creating seamless pathways in providing care.: • Team members are actively supported in representing THE_HOSPITAL at regional committees and leading the creation of such committees if not existing (eg. environmental, maintenance).: • An up to date resource map that can support recruitment and retention is made available.: • Representation at meetings and events are active and consistent.: • TAOHT / CDOHT maturation is fully supported through sharing of THE_HOSPITAL resources.: • Opportunities toward service integration that can better serve our communities are actively pursued.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on system integration through collaboration and removing barriers, with a secondary focus on streamlining processes and bulk purchasing to improve financial sustainability.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,NA,TRUE,1,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,696
696,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,People Centered-Care,"People Centered-Care. THE_HOSPITAL believes that the system should work for the people and not the people trying to figure out how to navigate the complex system. We see individuals as a whole person, with worth and dignity, and are deserving of the best care possible at the right place, the right time, the right provider, and as close to home as possible.. • Assessment for baseline SWOT is completed and an EDI work plan is established.: • EDI training made accessible to all staff and physicians.: • Strengthened services for Francophone, Indigenous citizens, and other marginalized groups.: • Integrated principles in THE_HOSPITAL culture.: • Baseline data and comprehensive indicators are collected and utilized for QI.: • Improved access and wait time, data regularly monitored to gauge strategies that effectively advance targets.: • Incidents and feedback are used to make improvements: • Patient safety is prioritized by tracking data and creating system improvements to eliminate risks involving medication, falls, hospital acquired infections, and other preventable safety incidents.: • A system of innovation is established where everyone has a chance to share ideas, participate, learn, and lead innovative practices / programs.: • Strategic Planning with PEP conducted to identify strategies that fully incorporate patients and families' voices in THE_HOSPITAL processes.: • Patients' and families' voices are integrated in THE_HOSPITAL processes and feedback is actively solicited.: • Committees / Groups / Meetings are streamlined across the organization for efficiency and strategic use of time towards accomplishing organizational goals: • Improved access to Mental Health, spiritual and cultural support including language services: • Improved access to follow-up care post-discharge and systems navigation for: • Relentless pursuit of best practices and out of the box thinking to improve care and access.: • Embed partnership-based culture when determining support for individuals and families: • Gaps are identified and programs evaluated for continuous effectiveness: • Implement quality improvement systems such as mapping out patients' journeys to identify barriers, quality case reviews, and creating comprehensive scorecards.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on providing the best possible care, improving patient safety, integrating patient voices, and addressing the needs of marginalized groups.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,NA,TRUE,1,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,696
696,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,Infrastructure,"Infrastructure. In order to provide the best care possible, THE_HOSPITAL believes in having the right infrastructure to support the work that we do - physical, technological, data, equipment, and processes. We believe in proactive maintenance and advocacy to maintain the resources that are needed to provide the best care possible. Continuous quality improvement is embedded in everything that we do.. • Average satisfaction rating or higher from staff and physician regarding their transition to Expanse experience.: • Staff supported 24/7 during Go Live date and at least 6 months post Go Live.: • Workflow optimization post Go-Live: • Electronic Scheduling system implemented in 2025: • Other opportunities to automate are explored, existing systems merged and optimized: • ED/ICU: Ministry-funded application submitted, project completed up to pre-tender stage.: • Fund-Raising expertise leveraged and fund-raising plan implemented.: • Projects are prioritized and advanced through for Ministry and public support: • Strengthened Foundation support and optimization: • Policies / frameworks are created: communication, partner engagement, decision-making, capital project approval, procurement.: • Regular operations review, data access: • CNIB Guidelines incorporated in all documents and electronic sites.: • Accessibility Framework reviewed and approved.: • Accessibility assessment completed and projects based on risks and resources are prioritized.: • Accessibility committee established with strong patient and frontline participation.: • Ongoing assessments to measure progress and ensure responsiveness to people's needs.: • Evidence in people culture, resource management, adaptive processes, strong leadership and partnership.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,The text focuses on physical and technological infrastructure improvements and maintenance within the hospital.,Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,NA,TRUE,1,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,696
696,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,Health And Human Resources,"Health And Human Resources. The backbone of our services is our people. Our employees, our leaders, our physicians, our partners, our volunteers. Our people's welfare is our priority. THE_HOSPITAL believes in fair and equitable treatment, in providing a safe and welcoming work environment where people thrive and pursue continuous growth, and where people are valued.. • HR Strategy launched and reviewed annually or as needed. The strategy includes recruitment and retention strategies, talent management, succession,: • A formal Professional Development Program including promotion of leadership competencies and mentorship, and regular performance appraisals are developed and sustained: • Scopes of practice are optimized: • Robust recognition system for contributions and stellar value-based attributes is implemented: • Employee and physician mental health are supported timely.: • Wellness initiatives and safety are prioritized.: • Critical Incident Stress Debriefing available 24/7: • Ergonomics assessment and equipment are available to all staff: • Incidents and near misses are addressed with risks identified mitigated and safety groups / committees established.: • Policies and expectations are established and clearly communicated.: • Fair procedural processes are adhered to as per collective agreements and organizational policies: • Volunteer Program is created / implemented with clearly outlined contributions and recognitions: • Physicians / NPs have access to tools and training that enhance clinical leadership, excellent people-centered care, and ground-breaking initiatives specifically responding to the needs in the North.: • Standard processes are established that support consistency, fairness, and equitability: • Recognition and incentive programs are implemented.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The primary focus is on employee welfare, recruitment, retention, and a safe work environment, while also encompassing the goal of providing excellent people-centered care through well-supported physicians and NPs.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,NA,TRUE,1,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,696
696,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,Communication,"Communication. The heart of what we do is dependent on the quality of our communication, THE_HOSPITAL believes in timely, responsive, transparent, and clear communication as the vehicle to get our work done and to serve effectively. THE_HOSPITAL is committed to ongoing improvement and to ensuring that our people, our community members, our partners, are well-informed and proactively engaged with our organization.. • The communication framework established include principles, strategies, processes, and THE_HOSPITAL tools that are being utilized to communicate: • Multiple ways of communicating internally are utilized (Town halls, newsletters, mass messaging for emergency and non-emergency announcements, huddle boards, feedback boards, emails): • Intranet and a document management system are set-up and well-utilized: • Effective communication is gauged based on feedback, surveys, and interpersonal connections: • Accomplishments / milestones are celebrated: • An operational “macro agenda” calendar is created and shared: • TAOHT and CDOHT are fully supported to maturity: • Regular participation in forums with partners that promote dialogue, focusing on improving the health of the communities we serve: • A variety of media is used to communicate and reach out to the general public (radio, newsprints, social media): • Regular community updates are shared: • Feedback / incident management policies and processes are re-established: • Employees, physicians, partners have a well-established system where they can provide ideas / feedback and are recognized for their contributions: • Patient / family communications are established for clear service navigation, expectations before, during, and after receiving services, understanding of resources available and opportunities for advocacy.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The focus on timely, responsive, and transparent communication throughout the organization, with partners (OHTs), and the community aligns with organizational culture and governance, and the integration aspect stems from supporting OHTs and participating in forums with partners.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,NA,TRUE,1,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,696
696,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,Fiscal Accountability,"Fiscal Accountability. THE_HOSPITAL believes in managing our resources effectively so we can continue to provide excellent services, we can continue to think outside the box, and we can continue to invest in the future of healthcare in our communities.. • Revenue generation streams are regularly identified and fully optimized (OH, federal, municipal, for profit): • Regular reconciliation of staffing / budget / resources / changes: • Contracts are actively managed and updated to ensure THE_HOSPITAL receives market value or better deals: • Revive fiscal advisory committee with representation as per legislation / by-laws, focusing on budget processes, transparent processes: • Product evaluation, Process committee, space committee, and other groups that can promote transparency, efficiency, and active staff participation are established: • Scorecard enhanced and shared appropriately: • Staff, physician, partners have opportunities to contribute to processes towards quality and efficiency: • Clear processes with clear accountabilities are established (requesting capital equipment, renovations, changes): • Clear reporting structures and accountabilities are adhered to.: • Processes that create bottlenecks are identified and actively eliminated: • Close partnerships between the governance and foundation boards are supported towards common gaols: • Streamline foundation goals and strategies with the organization's: • THE_HOSPITAL Foundation's presence in the community is reinforced: • Stronger connection with external sources of support (mines, private citizens, factories, rails) are nurtured: • THE_HOSPITAL has a balanced budget by 2029: • THE_HOSPITAL has a healthy capital reserve and funding application processes that allow for active maintenance and preservation of buildings and resources: • THE_HOSPITAL healthy cash flow ensures timely payments and ability to cover operational needs.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on managing resources effectively, optimizing revenue streams, and establishing clear processes for financial accountability and transparency within the organization.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,NA,TRUE,1,BLANCHE RIVER HEALTH SANTÉ RIVIÈRE BLANCHE,696
701,Mackenzie Health,Patient Care Excellence,"Patient Care Excellence. the hospital aspires to deliver exemplary, person-centred care that is safe, reliable and high-quality with timely access to critical services close to home — creating a world-class health experience.. - Demonstrating a strong commitment to caring and safety through empathetic communication in every interaction.: - Leveraging digital solutions and intelligent systems to advance data-driven decision-making, high reliability, service delivery models and person-centred care.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The focus is on delivering high-quality, safe, and person-centered care, supported by digital solutions for improved decision-making and service delivery.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Mackenzie Health,701
701,Mackenzie Health,People Are Our Strength,"People Are Our Strength. the hospital aspires to continue cultivating an exemplary organizational culture that fosters learning, belonging and engagement where everyone feels valued, empowered and inspired to deliver a world-class experience.. - Modernizing corporate services and workflows to enhance meaningful work, staff experience and real-time data analytics.: - Building structured learning and career pathways that enable growth and development.: - Investing in leadership development to grow future staff and physician leaders and empower teams.: - Cultivating a strong sense of belonging, wellness and safety by fostering a culture where everyone feels valued.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on improving organizational culture through learning, belonging, and engagement, while also addressing staff development and wellness.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Mackenzie Health,701
701,Mackenzie Health,Growing With Our Communities,Growing With Our Communities. the hospital will grow responsibly and sustainably to meet the evolving health needs of our communities — bringing care closer to home.. - Expanding capacity to meet health care needs by managing core services and corresponding access to specialized care.: - Continuing to plan for long-term growth through proactive land strategies and site planning.,ACCESS & CAPACITY,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The text focuses on expanding capacity to meet healthcare needs and bringing care closer to home, indicating improved access and a focus on community health needs.",Access & Capacity,Access & Capacity,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Mackenzie Health,701
701,Mackenzie Health,Integrated Care,"Integrated Care. the hospital aspires to deliver exemplary integrated care within and beyond our facilities, delivering seamless, co-ordinated and connected care across the health care system, creating a world-class health experience for the western York Region community.. - Advancing the future of primary care in our region by expanding access and integration with our primary care partners.: - Bridging hospital and community services to facilitate smooth transitions across the health care system.: - Providing education to support capacity building for our primary care and community partners.: - Leveraging digital solutions to strengthen care co-ordination, information exchange and collaboration.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text emphasizes seamless, co-ordinated care across the health system, integrating hospital and community services, and leveraging digital solutions for care coordination.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Mackenzie Health,701
701,Mackenzie Health,Education And Research,"Education And Research. Education: Enhance and expand medical and other health discipline learning experiences at the hospital to train the next generation of health professionals, shape the future of primary care, respond to growing demand for health services and enhance patient care outcomes.<br>Research: Improve access to leading treatments and enhance quality of care close to home by expanding research activity.. - Expanding and enhancing educational opportunities for learners, with a focus on providing hands-on clinical experience, mentorship and access to innovative learning resources.: - Creating an integrated training and education network to equip primary care providers with the skills, knowledge and resources needed to meet growing community health needs.: - Connecting learners to jobs at the hospital and in western York Region.: - Establishing a self-sustaining research program focusing on clinical research, including expanding access to clinical trials through academic and industry partnerships.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on expanding educational experiences and establishing a self-sustaining research program, while also connecting learners to jobs, addressing workforce needs.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Mackenzie Health,701
707,Ross Memorial Hospital,Providing The Best Possible Patient Experience,"Providing The Best Possible Patient Experience. NF. Pursuing the journey of becoming a High-Reliability Organization.: Advancing our master program and plan, working closely with our Foundation and partners.: Continually improving and building pride in the overall experience of our hospital.: Leveraging current and emerging technology to deliver more efficient and effective patient and family-centric care.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,The text focuses on improving the patient experience and leveraging technology to enhance care delivery.,Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Ross Memorial Hospital,707
707,Ross Memorial Hospital,Continually Building A Passionate Team,"Continually Building A Passionate Team. NF. • Continually leveraging creative strategies and emphasizing what makes the hospital special to support, recruit, and retain our people.: • Purposefully nurturing and reinforcing our THE_HOSPITAL Memorial culture.: • Supporting our physicians and their work life.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on recruiting and retaining staff, nurturing the hospital's culture and supporting physicians.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Ross Memorial Hospital,707
707,Ross Memorial Hospital,Anticipating And Responding To The Needs Of Our Community,"Anticipating And Responding To The Needs Of Our Community. NF. • Collaborating and partnering with our Ontario Health Team (OHT) and community partners to identify and address community needs.: • Optimizing our service offerings to best meet the continually changing needs of the community.: • Ensuring our services are equitable, inclusive, and respectful of everyone in our community.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text emphasizes collaboration with the OHT and community partners to address community needs, while also highlighting the importance of equitable and inclusive services.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Ross Memorial Hospital,707
707,Ross Memorial Hospital,Championing System Improvements,Championing System Improvements. NF. • Working within the Ontario health system to best position THE_HOSPITAL in the post-pandemic reality.: • Identifying new and different approaches to funding and resourcing to deliver on our strategic directions.: • Working with others to improve the efficiency of our local system through creative partnerships.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on working within the Ontario health system, improving efficiency through partnerships, and identifying new approaches to funding.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Ross Memorial Hospital,707
709,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,Services,"Services. Transform and grow our services to meet the needs of the community and greater catchment area.. 1. Fully utilize the existing resource capacity in the OR and Diagnostics by:: a) Increase OR utilization hours by 20% by March 31, 2026. Target = 88 hours/month THE_HOSPITAL; 28 hours / month THE_HOSPITAL: b) Increase Diagnostic Imaging annual volumes by 15%, by March 31, 2026. Baseline = 38,001: 2. Update the Master Services Plan, identifying the Centers of Excellence for a) our sites and b)in relation to the broader region by March 2027.",ACCESS & CAPACITY,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on increasing resource capacity in OR and Diagnostics, as well as updating the Master Services Plan in relation to the broader region.",Access & Capacity,Access & Capacity,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,709
709,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,Quality (&Risk),"Quality (&Risk). Provide Quality Care that is patient centered, timely, efficient, effective, equitable and safe. 3. To achieve accreditation in the November 2025 process.: 4. Implement the HIROC RAC program by 2027 by completing the risk assessment component by March 31, 2026 .: 5. To achieve full electronic documentation.: • Physician documentation in the ED, Oncology and In-patient unit by December 2025: • All program documentation in the ED, Oncology and in-patient programs by March 2026: • All program documentation in the, surgical services and THE_HOSPITAL Physician lead Ambulatory/Outpatient Clinics by December 2026.: 6. To implement the OHA patient satisfaction survey for the emergency department and inpatient unit, utilizing the Qualtrics platform, to identify an area of opportunity by March 31st 2026.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The focus on providing quality, safe, and patient-centered care aligns with patient care excellence, while the implementation of electronic documentation and Qualtrics platform falls under digital health.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,709
709,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,Human Resources,"Human Resources. A Workplace that nurtures accountability, individual and collective potential and a culture of kindness and inclusion.. 6. To achieve 85% of regular active staff, patient partners, and board members, completing the unconscious bias training and inclusive language modules by March 31, 2026. Baseline = 0: 8. Improve staff engagement by decreasing the leaders scores on the following Accreditation Canada Staff Engagement Survey questions by March 31, 2027: a) Decrease by 30%, leaders who report their days as being quite or extremely stressful. Baseline = 60%.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The focus on staff engagement, reducing leader stress, and promoting kindness and inclusion in the workplace directly addresses workforce sustainability, while unconscious bias training aligns with health equity and social accountability.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,709
709,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,Finance (& Resources),"Finance (& Resources). A sustainable and resilient Health Organization that is here for future generations.. 9. To achieve a balanced budget within 2% of revenues in 2025/26 and a balanced within 1% in 2026/27. Baseline= revenues for 2025/26 and 2026/27: 10. To achieve 10% supply chain reductions by March 31,2027. Baseline= THE_HOSPITAL = $5,934,085 & savings target of $225,000 THE_HOSPITAL - $5,207,927 & savings target of $225,000.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,None,"The text focuses on achieving a balanced budget and supply chain reductions, directly relating to financial efficiency and cost management.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,709
709,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,Stewardship & Partnerships,"Stewardship & Partnerships. Harness Innovation and Partnerships to deliver a quality, expanded, integrated network of sustainable regional care, demonstrating responsible use of public funds.. 10. Increase access to primary care through the recruitment of primary care providers and exploration of alternative care models to better meet the primary and acute care needs of the community by December 2026.: Targets:: ✓ Recruit 2 physicians with focused practices as outlined in the recruitment targets.: ✓ Recruit 2 physician specialists as outlined in the recruitment targets.: ✓ Explore one alternative care model in partnership.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text emphasizes partnerships and integration for regional care, while also addressing access to primary care through recruitment.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,2,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,709
736,Southlake Health,Clinical Excellence,Clinical Excellence. Maintain a relentless focus on clinical excellence by consistently providing evidence-informed care that patients deserve and can trust.. • Improve access to the right care in the right place at the right time: • Implement additional integrated care pathways within and beyond our walls to continuously improve outcomes for patients.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text focuses on providing high-quality, evidence-based care and improving access through integrated care pathways, which extends beyond the hospital's walls and points to partnerships.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Southlake Health,736
736,Southlake Health,Quality And Safety,"Quality And Safety. Consistently provide high-quality and safe care to everyone who relies on us, while building trust and accountability to inspire people to deliver their best.. • Adopt a rigorous approach to quality improvement to achieve Quintuple Aim advances: • Cultivate a just culture that prioritizes safety and transparency, empowers people to take ownership for safety and continuously learn and improve.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on providing high-quality and safe care, while also emphasizing a just culture and accountability within the organization.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Southlake Health,736
736,Southlake Health,Experience,"Experience. Enable a positive experience for everyone who comes through our doors and make THE_HOSPITAL the best place to work.. • Improve the patient's experience, with a special focus on transitions of care: • Support the unique needs of our diverse communities and team members: • Grow education, learning, development and engagement for everyone at THE_HOSPITAL.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on improving patient experience and fostering a positive work environment through education, learning, and engagement.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Southlake Health,736
736,Southlake Health,New Models Of Care,"New Models Of Care. Distribute services closer to home to improve the Quintuple Aim.. • Collaborate with partners to connect services and help build one integrated care system for patients: • Pursue population health management and value-based care approaches: • Focus on prevention, wellness and early intervention with the community to help preserve acute care capacity for those who require care that only a hospital can provide.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The focus is on collaborating with partners for integrated care and pursuing population health management, with an emphasis on prevention and wellness.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Southlake Health,736
736,Southlake Health,"Partnerships, Research And Academics","Partnerships, Research And Academics. Foster knowledge development and exchange for the benefit of patients and strengthen our partnerships.. • Embrace the Learning Health System approach with our partners to accelerate impact: • Inspire community investment partnerships with an emphasis on transformative philanthropy: • Advance research and expand our academic mission.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",The text explicitly mentions partnerships and fostering knowledge development through research and academics.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Southlake Health,736
736,Southlake Health,People,"People. Our people are the most important part of THE_HOSPITAL.. • Boost team member health and wellness, recognition and professional development: • Retain, recruit and co-design the future of work with our team members.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text emphasizes the importance of team member health, wellness, recognition, and professional development, directly relating to workforce sustainability, and mentions co-designing the future of work, reflecting organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Southlake Health,736
736,Southlake Health,Sustainability,"Sustainability. Ensuring we are good stewards of taxpayer dollars without loosing focus on the environmental impact of what we do is of paramount importance.. • Maximize value and efficiency, and secure additional funding to support our continued growth: • Implement additional sustainable practices to minimize our environmental footprint: • Pursue alternative revenue opportunities and market our expertise.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text focuses on maximizing value and efficiency with taxpayer dollars, alongside implementing sustainable practices to minimize environmental impact.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Southlake Health,736
736,Southlake Health,Infrastructure,"Infrastructure. We need to care for the buildings and spaces from which our people care for patients.. • Advance planning for our Master Plan to build for a new hospital, redevelop and improve our Davis Drive campus, and develop new community-based facilities: • Invest in upgraded equipment and new technologies for our teams.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on maintaining and improving buildings and spaces, including planning for a new hospital and investing in equipment, which necessitates financial considerations.",Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Southlake Health,736
736,Southlake Health,Data And Analytics,"Data And Analytics. After our people, data is the most important strategic asset we have.. • Grow our Leading-Edge Analytics Platform by integrating additional data from across and outside THE_HOSPITAL: • Build a strong organizational foundation for Population Health Management and predictive analytics.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,The text explicitly mentions growing an analytics platform and building a foundation for population health management using data.,Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Southlake Health,736
736,Southlake Health,Digital Health,"Digital Health. Digital health is health. People expect healthcare to be convenient and connected, like how they live the rest of their lives.. • Build a future-focused healthcare delivery ecosystem where technology enables improvement in each element of the Quintuple Aim.: • Harness technology to optimize workflows and new models of care: • Enhance interoperability of systems and devices to improve quality, safety and patient experience.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on leveraging technology to improve healthcare delivery, workflows, and system interoperability to enhance patient experience, safety, and quality.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Southlake Health,736
714,ST JOSEPH'S HEALTH CARE LONDON,Excellence In Care: Powered By Discovery,"Excellence In Care: Powered By Discovery. We will continue to work closely with community partners and use the best information available to shape the future of health care at St. Joseph’s. With research, education and innovation—supported by Lawson Research Institute—we are proud of our role in caring for our community members and will continue to evolve to meet their changing needs—in body, mind and spirit.. • Incorporate knowledge from our diverse communities and Indigenous ways of knowing to respond to the holistic needs of our community and improve care for the most vulnerable.: • Accelerate and elevate clinical care and health system impact through research.: • Leverage data analytics and artificial intelligence to support the redesign of care.: • Predict, optimize and enhance our services and models of care.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS","The text emphasizes excellence in care driven by research and innovation, with a focus on meeting community needs and leveraging data analytics and AI.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,ST JOSEPH'S HEALTH CARE LONDON,714
714,ST JOSEPH'S HEALTH CARE LONDON,A Vibrant Workforce,"A Vibrant Workforce. Making our workforce one of our three main priorities demonstrates an ongoing commitment to being an exceptional place to work.. • Cultivate a culture of inquiry among all staff, clinicians and learners to ensure a dynamic and engaging learning environment.: • Foster a work environment that promotes comprehensive well-being for all staff, clinicians, learners and volunteers.: • Advance our organizational commitment to equity, diversity, inclusion and belonging.: • Develop the leaders of tomorrow.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on prioritizing the workforce, promoting well-being, and cultivating a positive and inclusive work environment, indicating workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,ST JOSEPH'S HEALTH CARE LONDON,714
714,ST JOSEPH'S HEALTH CARE LONDON,Partnering For Impact,"Partnering For Impact. Over the next five years, we will focus on forming new and nurturing existing collaborations and partnerships with those who share our vision for innovative, connected health care.. • Enable a more seamless patient experience by working with our care delivery partners across the health care continuum.: • Lead planning efforts in partnership across the health, community and social care sectors to build system capacity.: • Develop new and expanded partnerships in research, academia, education and philanthropy to amplify impact.: • Elevate the voice of patients, residents and caregivers as partners in all we do.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The primary focus is on forming collaborations and partnerships for connected healthcare and system capacity, with a secondary emphasis on patient experience.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,ST JOSEPH'S HEALTH CARE LONDON,714
724,"HÔPITAL DE Mattawa HOSPITAL, MAISON DES AÎNÉS Algonquin NURSING HOME",Quality Of Care & Patient/Resident Safety,"Quality Of Care & Patient/Resident Safety. We will provide bilingual, high-quality, safe and timely patient and resident care to ensure the best outcomes and high level of satisfaction for the people we serve.. Collaboration with district, RFP to ministry (time resources): Local access to CT: Continue to follow direction of ONE HITS go live April 2024: QIP Annual Work Plans: Patient Satisfaction Surveys: Patient Safety Audits: Accreditation Surveys: Ethics Integration.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on providing high-quality, safe, and timely patient care to ensure the best outcomes and satisfaction, with mentions of ethics integration, indicating a focus on organizational values and governance.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,"HÔPITAL DE Mattawa HOSPITAL, MAISON DES AÎNÉS Algonquin NURSING HOME",724
724,"HÔPITAL DE Mattawa HOSPITAL, MAISON DES AÎNÉS Algonquin NURSING HOME",Our People & Our Mission,"Our People & Our Mission. We will be a ""workplace of choice"" in our area and focus on our physicians and our staff.. Health Human Resources Recruitment: Succession Planning: Quality of Work Life Committee: Work Life Pulse Surveys: Staff Recognition Weeks: Attendance and Long Service Awards: Elizabeth Bruyère Award.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The focus on being a ""workplace of choice"", staff recognition, and HR recruitment initiatives all relate to workforce sustainability, with the underlying mission representing org culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,"HÔPITAL DE Mattawa HOSPITAL, MAISON DES AÎNÉS Algonquin NURSING HOME",724
724,"HÔPITAL DE Mattawa HOSPITAL, MAISON DES AÎNÉS Algonquin NURSING HOME",Our Community: Working Together For Better Integration,"Our Community: Working Together For Better Integration. We will work collaboratively and creatively with other health care providers and stakeholders in order to deliver innovative, effective, integrated quality care.. Promote utilization of the Indigenous Healing space: Maintain GEM: Fundraising: Maintain Safe Bed and RAAM Clinic: Explore Virtual Care Opportunities.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on collaborative work with healthcare providers for integrated care, as well as Indigenous healing space and safe beds.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,"HÔPITAL DE Mattawa HOSPITAL, MAISON DES AÎNÉS Algonquin NURSING HOME",724
724,"HÔPITAL DE Mattawa HOSPITAL, MAISON DES AÎNÉS Algonquin NURSING HOME","Financial Responsibility, Accountability & Transparency","Financial Responsibility, Accountability & Transparency. We will plan for and maintain financial stability in order to deliver and sustain quality patient and resident care services.. Annual Balanced Budgets: Small Hospital Transforma-tion Fund: Health Care Heartbeat and Pulse: Website Updates.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text explicitly mentions financial stability, responsibility, and accountability, pointing to both financial sustainability and organizational governance regarding budget management.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,"HÔPITAL DE Mattawa HOSPITAL, MAISON DES AÎNÉS Algonquin NURSING HOME",724
