745,Soldiers' MEMORIAL HOSPITAL Orillia,We Are Connected,"We Are Connected. NF. - The integration of care: - Enhancing access to palliative care services at home.: - Additional populations (e.g. children and youth, mental health & addictions) will continue to be developed for as future priority populations: - Virtual care advances associated with the COVID-19 response will be formalized and expanded.: - Information access to integrated care plans will be expanded to more agencies, providers and patients: - Organizations within the Couchiching OHT will continue to develop a shared strategy including shared purpose, principles of decision-making and priorities. THE_HOSPITAL will continue to co-create this work, ensuring tactics and performance measures with our partners. A Collaborative Decision-Making Agreement will be created, that will enhance existing OHT relationships and enable community and regional participation.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text focuses on the integration of care services, particularly palliative care, and the development of a shared strategy within the Couchiching OHT, while also mentioning enhancing access to these services.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Soldiers' MEMORIAL HOSPITAL Orillia,745
745,Soldiers' MEMORIAL HOSPITAL Orillia,We Are Soldiers',"We Are THE_HOSPITAL'. NF. - Commit to listen and act upon the needs of our people in a timely and transparent manner.: - Create regular opportunities for all team members to contribute to making THE_HOSPITAL even better.: - Provide diverse opportunities for staff to enhance their clinical and leadership skills.: - Provide targeted training opportunities to support staff retention based on the needs of the organization.: - Provide staff with access to facilities that offer physical, mental and emotional health services and programming such as access to physical fitness facilities, meditation and yoga. Modernization of staff scheduling processes Active recruitment and retention initiatives.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on staff needs, training, wellness, recruitment, and retention, indicating workforce sustainability and organizational culture improvements.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Soldiers' MEMORIAL HOSPITAL Orillia,745
745,Soldiers' MEMORIAL HOSPITAL Orillia,We Adapt And Advance,"We Adapt And Advance. NF. - Active participation in the planning and implementation of our electronic medical record with our provider (GBIN) clinical road map Create, adapt and adopt an innovation agenda based on leading practices to support rapid quality improvements, patient convenience and implement effective safety measures.: - Develop a Financial Health Strategy which enables sustainable operating and capital plans that advance our strategic goals: - Continued work with our Couchiching OHT partners to identify leading edge, technology-enabled, integrated care which will instruct future infrastructure investments: - Pursue further Ministry of Health commitment for our capital redevelopment Future Hospital Project (e.g., Stage 1 grant, Stage 1 review).",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text discusses electronic medical records, innovation agenda, integrated care with OHT partners, and infrastructure investments informed by technology.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Soldiers' MEMORIAL HOSPITAL Orillia,745
718,JOSEPH BRANT HOSPITAL,Achieve Excellence In Quality Patient Care,Achieve Excellence In Quality Patient Care. NF. • Drive excellence through continuous implementation of evidence-based quality and patient safety standards.: • Engage our people and key stakeholders in organizational initiatives and processes to drive a culture of continuous improvement.: • Execute our Digital Health Strategy.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The focus is on quality patient care and patient safety standards, with a secondary emphasis on implementing the Digital Health Strategy.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,JOSEPH BRANT HOSPITAL,718
718,JOSEPH BRANT HOSPITAL,Nurture And Support Our People,"Nurture And Support Our People. NF. • Champion a workplace environment that supports the well-being and safety of our staff, physicians and volunteers.: • Be recognized as a workplace of choice.: • Embed a culture of Diversity, Equity and Inclusion into all we do at THE_HOSPITAL.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"This focuses on supporting staff well-being, safety, and being a workplace of choice, with DEI embedded in the culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,JOSEPH BRANT HOSPITAL,718
718,JOSEPH BRANT HOSPITAL,Re-Imagine How We Deliver Care,Re-Imagine How We Deliver Care. NF. • Support implementation of the Burlington Ontario Health Team's 3-year plan.: • Advance complementary relationships with our people and our partners to improve the health of our communities.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,The text mentions the Ontario Health Team's plan and improving the health of communities through partnerships.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,JOSEPH BRANT HOSPITAL,718
718,JOSEPH BRANT HOSPITAL,Collaborate To Deliver Outstanding Care Experience,Collaborate To Deliver Outstanding Care Experience. NF. • Relentless pursuit of operational excellence while ensuring the effective and efficient use of resources.: • Foster an environment that stimulates creativity and new ideas.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,The text focuses on delivering outstanding care experience through operational excellence and fostering a creative environment.,Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,JOSEPH BRANT HOSPITAL,718
726,GEORGIAN BAY General Hospital,Continual Excellence,"Continual Excellence. NF. • Commit to meeting or exceeding safety and quality standards.: • Continually provide person-centered and person-driven care.: • Continue to pursue strategies for providing consistent and dependable care for all.: • Reinforce coordination and collaboration with our health partners to develop a more integrated care journey for our community.: • Engage in evidence-informed leadership and decision-making.: • Continually improve systems, processes, procedures, policies, and accountabilities to enable our people to perform at their best.: • Ensure our patients feel comfortable and safe in coming to us with their health needs.: • Continually collaborate with and engage our Patient & Family Advisory Council (PFAC) to ensure patient experiences are incorporated into decision-making.: • Deliver optimal outcomes and experiences for our patients through seamless transitions in care, enhanced collaboration with partners (internal and external), and continual process improvement.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text emphasizes safety, quality, person-centered care, collaboration with partners, and improving patient experiences, aligning with patient care excellence and integration themes.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,GEORGIAN BAY General Hospital,726
726,GEORGIAN BAY General Hospital,Trust And Belonging,"Trust And Belonging. NF. • Strive to build a deeper sense of belonging and community amongst our people, patients, and partners.: • Partner to address health gaps and inequities in our community.: • Proactively engage and deepen relationships with Indigenous peoples and communities, with full commitment to making changes and creating an environment of culturally safe and sensitive care.: • Ensure a focus on Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Belonging through providing services in a safe way for all, as we grow our services.: • Continue to instill confidence in and awareness of our healthcare services.: • Leverage trauma informed care practices to create a culturally safe hospital environment.: • Practice active listening and empathetic approaches to understand individual patient healing goals.: • Serve as a community leader through external communication and partnerships that build trust and reliability.: • Continue to seek engagement and consult: • Recognize our role in delivering care to our Francophone community and acknowledge their specific care needs.: • Develop a deeper understanding of the distinct health needs of Indigenous individuals and other vulnerable groups in our community.: • Actively seek an increased representation of Indigenous voices and other marginalized groups in decision-making and planning conversations.: • Use purposeful language (e.g., Our People) to further ingrain our team culture.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on building trust and belonging, addressing health inequities, engaging with Indigenous communities, and promoting diversity and inclusion, reflecting both health equity and organizational culture.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,GEORGIAN BAY General Hospital,726
726,GEORGIAN BAY General Hospital,Dedicated Team,"Dedicated Team. NF. • Be an engaged, collaborative, and inclusive team.: • Value, grow, invest in, and retain our talent.: • Promote an environment of continuous learning and growth.: • Highlight our strong internal culture, and ingrain our values in all processes and systems.: • Celebrate our successes.: • Support our people to perform at their highest potential.: • Enhance communication channels, create more recognition opportunities, and foster increased staff appreciation to drive retention.: • Invest in learning opportunities for our people.: • Cultivate collaboration and inclusivity amongst our people.: • Actively listen to our people.: • Encourage a culture of positivity and building strong relationships.: • Inspire a growth mindset in our people.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on valuing, growing, and retaining talent, promoting a positive work environment, and enhancing communication and relationships, all of which align with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,GEORGIAN BAY General Hospital,726
726,GEORGIAN BAY General Hospital,Sustainable Growth,"Sustainable Growth. NF. • Be an organization of choice for talented people.: • Grow our services to align with current and anticipated needs of our community.: • Invest in our physical infrastructure and environmental stewardship.: • Leverage technology to improve patient experience, patient outcomes, health equity and team effectiveness.: • Enhance our partnership networks and reshape our processes to support patient needs throughout their health journey.: • Continue to achieve financial sustainability.: • Listen to and engage with our people to build upon our valued culture and remain an organization of choice.: • Address recruitment in a way that accents our positive and supportive culture.: • Enhance advocacy and strategic efforts to grow our services and programming, specifically in the areas of women’s health services, mental health, seniors’ health, surgical services, and diagnostic imaging.: • Identify and secure innovative and relevant technology to support our people in performing their work.: • Seek creative funding and savings opportunities.: • Act in a fiscally responsible way through efficient use of resources.: • Support community driven changes that improve health and healthcare delivery to the residents we serve.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on financial sustainability through efficient resource use and cost savings, while also emphasizing attracting and retaining talented people, aligning with workforce sustainability.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,GEORGIAN BAY General Hospital,726
734,WEST HALDIMAND GENERAL HOSPITAL,Exceptional Patient Care,"Exceptional Patient Care. Every patient we serve will receive personalized, compassionate, and high-quality care. Supporting their healing, well-being and satisfaction throughout their healthcare journey.. * We will provide high-quality, timely, safe and accessible care.: * We will empower, involve and support patients and families in their care.: * We will provide inclusive care that reflects the communities we serve.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The focus on personalized, high-quality care aligns with patient care excellence, while the emphasis on inclusive care reflects health equity and social accountability.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,WEST HALDIMAND GENERAL HOSPITAL,734
734,WEST HALDIMAND GENERAL HOSPITAL,Outstanding Team,"Outstanding Team. We strive to cultivate a skilled, engaged, and empowered workforce, fostering a culture of collaboration, professional development, and excellence to deliver the best possible outcomes for our patients and community.. * We will be a great place to work and an employer of choice.: * We will employ innovative recruitment and retention efforts to attract top talent.: * We will support team health and well-being.: * We will invest in the development of our team and foster a culture of continuous learning.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,The text focuses on cultivating a skilled and engaged workforce and fostering a culture of collaboration and professional development.,Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,WEST HALDIMAND GENERAL HOSPITAL,734
734,WEST HALDIMAND GENERAL HOSPITAL,Operational Excellence,"Operational Excellence. Our aim is to optimize efficiency, effectiveness, and safety in all aspects of our operations. Leveraging best practices, technology, and continuous improvement initiatives to achieve the highest standards of service delivery and resource management.. * We will grow and improve our infrastructure and services to reflect the needs of the communities we serve and elevate patient care.: * We will ensure the responsible financial management and stewardship of our resources.: * We will ensure our facilities are safe for all those entering our doors.: * We will continuously improve, informed by measurement, benchmarking and monitoring.: * We will strengthen the link between WHGH and THE_HOSPITAL through integrated governance.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"Focus on efficiency, resource management, safety, and integrated governance points to financial and patient care excellence as key themes.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,WEST HALDIMAND GENERAL HOSPITAL,734
734,WEST HALDIMAND GENERAL HOSPITAL,Community Partnerships And Connection,"Community Partnerships And Connection. We are committed to building strong partnerships and meaningful connections with our community stakeholders, collaborating to address local health needs, promote wellness, and enhance access to care through outreach, education, and advocacy.. * We will engage with our communities and health and social care partners to improve care and advance the implementation of Ontario Health Teams.: * We will support our foundation in fundraising to improve our infrastructure and services to meet the needs of our community.: * We will increase community engagement and communication to ensure an understanding of our services and new developments at the hospital.: * We will prioritize public health and bolster partnerships to address community health concerns and enhance overall well-being.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The text emphasizes building strong partnerships with community stakeholders, addressing local health needs, and improving care through collaboration with health and social care partners, indicating integration and community health initiatives.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,WEST HALDIMAND GENERAL HOSPITAL,734
734,WEST HALDIMAND GENERAL HOSPITAL,Innovation And Digital Enablement,"Innovation And Digital Enablement. Embracing innovation and leveraging digital technologies, we seek to drive transformative change in healthcare delivery, enhancing accessibility, efficiency, and quality of care through the adoption of cutting-edge solutions and data-driven approaches.. * We will implement a new electronic medical record system to streamline healthcare processes and enhance patient care and records management.: * We will leverage innovation, digital technologies and data analytics to improve care quality, efficiency and patient-centredness.: * We will advance and strengthen a culture of innovation and continuous improvement.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on using digital technologies to transform healthcare delivery, improve efficiency, and enhance care quality.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,WEST HALDIMAND GENERAL HOSPITAL,734
751,CHEO,Excellent Care,"Excellent Care. We are the trusted leader in excellent, safe and compassionate pediatric care and expertise and always strive to know, do and be even better.. * Deepen our strong safety culture and practices to eliminate all preventable harm.: * Innovate, adapt and grow programs and teams to better respond to the increasing needs of children and youth.: * Expand education for providers, parents, children and youth to bring the hospital's knowledge to the world.: * Develop a framework to screen every child and youth for the full range of developmental, wellness and social needs.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS","Focuses on safe and compassionate care, innovation in programs, and expansion of education initiatives, all contributing to patient well-being and hospital knowledge.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,CHEO,751
751,CHEO,Everyone Belongs,"Everyone Belongs. We respond to every unique need, going above and beyond to ensure safe and supportive spaces for Indigenous and diverse communities.. * Develop training and tools that improve awareness, knowledge and competency to ensure that all forms of discrimination and bias are eliminated at the hospital.: * Continue in our commitment to advance reconciliation by building respectful and reciprocal relationships with First Nations, Inuit and Métis people in all regions we serve, including host nations and the Ottawa urban Indigenous communities, to improve health access and outcomes.: * Work with partners to understand and address the developmental health, wellness and social needs of each child and youth.: * Leverage data and analysis to measure the progress and impact of I-IDEAS initiatives.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on addressing the unique needs of Indigenous and diverse communities, promoting inclusivity, and eliminating discrimination, aligning with health equity and organizational culture.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,CHEO,751
751,CHEO,Strong Team,"Strong Team. We branch out to attract, support and teach the very best people and empower everyone at the hospital to make big, bold and meaningful contributions.. * Build and support strong teams through ongoing opportunities to learn, grow and strive, led by empowered and authentic leaders.: * Strengthen engagement and recognition to create a team of the hospital ambassadors.: * Attract and retain the best talent through workforce planning, innovative recruitment, robust onboarding and ongoing mentoring.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on attracting, supporting, and empowering employees, building strong teams, and strengthening engagement and recognition, all related to workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,CHEO,751
751,CHEO,Bright Future,"Bright Future. We all develop and leverage clinical expertise, research and innovation to create a stronger, healthier tomorrow – for kids here and around the world.. * Create strong links between the hospital and the hospital Research Institute to optimize research, innovation and quality improvement advancement.: * Improve research study recruitment and participation by making it easier to collect and use data, collaborate with partners and leverage the research to make meaningful change.: * Grow our efforts and initiatives that contribute to a greener, more sustainable the hospital.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text focuses on leveraging clinical expertise, research, and innovation, with a specific emphasis on improving research study recruitment and promoting sustainability efforts.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,CHEO,751
751,CHEO,Connected Care,"Connected Care. We work, educate, collaborate and advocate with others to grow capacity, build expertise and bring care closer to home.. * Expand our network of partners to ensure every child's developmental, health and social needs are met where they live.: * Deepen the hospital's academic teaching role for future health professionals, aligned to our many academic partners.: * Increase access to holistic navigation support and build a network that facilitates an integrated approach to services across the communities we serve.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS","The text focuses on expanding partnerships, deepening academic teaching roles, and increasing access to integrated community services, which aligns with integration and education.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,CHEO,751
763,Pembroke Regional Hospital,Care For Our People,"Care For Our People. We will provide the best care for our patients and support to their families by:. 1. Including patients and families in designing their care: 2. Providing learning and growth opportunities for our staff, physicians and learners: 3. Fostering a stimulating, motivating and safe work environment: 4. Embracing and integrating equity, diversity and inclusion for our patients and our THE_HOSPITAL team: 5. Continuing to foster innovative models of team-based care.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text emphasizes providing the best care for patients and families, along with supporting staff and fostering a safe and equitable work environment.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Pembroke Regional Hospital,763
763,Pembroke Regional Hospital,Care For Our Community,"Care For Our Community. We will continually improve the care we provide by:. 1. Assessing needs, addressing gaps and seeking opportunities to improve care, especially for our vulnerable populations: 2. Embracing and implementing leading practices across the hospital: 3. Optimizing how patients and families navigate their care: 4. Assisting with and supporting the health of our community.",POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on improving care, addressing gaps for vulnerable populations, and supporting the health of the community, aligning with population health and health equity.",Population & Community Health,Population & Community Health,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Pembroke Regional Hospital,763
763,Pembroke Regional Hospital,Care With Our Partners,"Care With Our Partners. We will improve the care and support for our community by:. Leading in our work with our local partners (such as primary care, community and long-term care) to improve care for all, including those with highest unmet needs:: 1. Mental health and addictions.: 2. Frail elderly: 3. Unattached patients: Leading in our work with our regional hospital partners to optimize access to specialized care close to home:: 1. Develop communities of clinical practices with our local hospital partners: 2. Build regional specialized networks of care.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The text focuses on collaborating with local and regional partners to improve care for the community, particularly those with mental health issues, frail elderly, and unattached patients, and building specialized networks.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Pembroke Regional Hospital,763
763,Pembroke Regional Hospital,An Authentic And Inclusive Culture,"An Authentic And Inclusive Culture. We cultivate a genuine, positive and inclusive organizational culture that is characterized by a welcoming and safe environment. We champion our shared values every day and establish initiatives that promote innovation, inclusivity, teamwork, and a sense of purpose where everyone feels empowered to contribute to high-quality care for our patients and each other.. NF.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on fostering a positive and inclusive organizational culture, which directly impacts the work environment and employee well-being, and aims to empower employees.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Pembroke Regional Hospital,763
763,Pembroke Regional Hospital,Robust Data And Digital Health Capabilities,"Robust Data And Digital Health Capabilities. We enable data and digital health technologies to facilitate efficient decision-making, personalized and improved patient care, and streamlined operational workflow. We emphasize data safety and privacy.. NF.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,The focus is on leveraging data and digital technologies to enhance patient care and streamline operations.,Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Pembroke Regional Hospital,763
763,Pembroke Regional Hospital,Open Communication,"Open Communication. We engage in clear, comprehensive and transparent communication to ensure that all stakeholders, including staff, physicians, learners, patients and families, the community, and external partners are informed, consulted, and engaged.. NF.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The focus is on transparent communication with all stakeholders, indicating a commitment to organizational culture and engagement with external partners.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Pembroke Regional Hospital,763
763,Pembroke Regional Hospital,Financial And Environmental Stewardship,Financial And Environmental Stewardship. We strive to be a resilient and high-functioning hospital through championing responsible and efficient use of resources and environmentally responsible practices. This includes a focus on continuously assessing our environmental impact and promoting eco-friendly initiatives.. NF.,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text focuses on efficient resource use, environmental responsibility, and eco-friendly initiatives, aligning with financial sustainability and infrastructure & environment.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Pembroke Regional Hospital,763
753,Montfort,Serve A Growing And Aging Population,"Serve A Growing And Aging Population. To meet the growing and complex needs of a diverse population, we will take a proactive, multidisciplinary approach with our partners to serve 210,000 more patients in Ottawa and Eastern Ontario within the next 10 years, including 80,000 persons aged 65 and over.. 1. Optimized the Aline-Chrétien Health Hub, namely by adding a clinic for patients without a family doctor;: 2. Developed a network of primary care providers with privileges at the hospital, who will receive personalized support in eliminating current irritants;: 3. Secured ministry approvals for phase 1 of the hospital's redevelopment, which includes adding beds, eliminating rooms for more than two patients, renovating neonatal intensive care, enhancing teaching and critical care spaces and reducing our environmental footprint;: 4. Enhanced the service offering of our medical departments by expanding access to certain specialties and 24/7 coverage based on operational needs.",POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text focuses on serving a growing and aging population with proactive approaches, specifically addressing the needs of a large segment of the community.",Population & Community Health,Population & Community Health,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Montfort,753
753,Montfort,Expand French-Language Services,"Expand French-Language Services. We will increase access to services in French to better serve our communities, knowing that receiving health care in one's mother tongue is beneficial for health. Through close and active collaboration with other health care institutions, we will create partnerships that reinforce the services provided in French and transform the patient experience across the entire health sector.. 5. Enhanced our delivery of health care in specific specialities, in French, to meet the needs of patients in predetermined regions of Ontario;: 6. Opened primary care services in French in Ottawa's west-end, in partnership with primary care providers;: 7. Planned the opening of additional Francophone long-term care beds in Ottawa.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"This project focuses on improving access to healthcare services for Francophone communities, directly addressing health equity and involving partnerships for service delivery.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Montfort,753
753,Montfort,Strengthen Our Social Accountability,"Strengthen Our Social Accountability. In recognizing our social accountability toward the wide-range of communities that we serve, we will offer services suited to the needs of vulnerable populations to create a more equitable and inclusive healthcare system while reducing health disparities.. 8. Improved the patient experience by introducing culturally appropriate practices, geared toward reconciliation with Indigenous communities and inclusive of the various populations we serve;: 9. Ensured greater representation and diversity within our boards of directors and our leadership;: 10. Opened a interdisciplinary addiction service.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on serving vulnerable populations, promoting equity and inclusion, and addressing health disparities, while also mentioning improved patient experience through culturally appropriate practices.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Montfort,753
753,Montfort,Enhance The Impact Of Education And Research,"Enhance The Impact Of Education And Research. We will cultivate next-generation knowledge for future-oriented care with an emphasis on multidisciplinary activity and knowledge transfers across different sectors of clinical activity. We will capitalize on the hospital's status as one of Ontario's largest hospitals in terms of obstetrical and mental health beds, with recognized programs in family medicine and orthopedic surgery, among others.. 11. Increased the number of Francophone learners in the health sector through enhanced collaboration with our partner postsecondary institutions;: 12. Increased the volume and quality of our research activities with the aim of disseminating new knowledge to improve care.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The focus is on education, research activities, and knowledge dissemination to improve care, along with collaboration with partner institutions.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Montfort,753
753,Montfort,Innovate To Remain A Sought-After Environment,"Innovate To Remain A Sought-After Environment. In the context of a health care labour shortage, we will cultivate a positive environment with priority placed on employee well-being. By supporting our teams in a stimulating, caring environment, we will retain our talent while delivering quality care with empathy and professionalism.. 13. Implemented greater workplace flexibility and professional development initiatives;: 14. Implemented the Epic electronic health record system to improve our clinician and patient experience;: 15. Lightened the administrative load on staff and optimized our service offering by integrating artificial intelligence tools;: 16. Achieved recognition as one the few Canadian hospitals to have achieved the highest distinction under the Choosing Wisely initiative, which promotes the efficient use of resources and climate action;: 17. Created partnerships with businesses to encourage innovation and meet the needs of our communities.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text focuses on employee well-being, workplace flexibility, and professional development to retain talent, along with implementing Epic and AI tools.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,Montfort,753
768,ST. FRANCIS MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,Quality Of Care,"Quality Of Care. We will improve patient and family experience. • Successfully complete the Emergency Redevelopment project: • Meet the targeted objectives on all patient services and patient safety: • Integrate patient and family experience into planning and decision making: • Emphasize performance measurement and reporting; while focusing on patient safety, timeliness, quality and transparency: • Provide access to care without barriers.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text focuses on improving patient and family experience, patient safety, and access to care, all of which align with patient care excellence and reducing barriers to access.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,ST. FRANCIS MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,768
768,ST. FRANCIS MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,System Integration,"System Integration. We will improve our partnerships to increase effective, seamless patient centred care. • Demonstrate Ontario Health Team leadership: • Ensure a patient centered approach: • Invest in Technological systems to further our Vision.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The focus is on improving partnerships and system integration, with an investment in technology to support the vision.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,ST. FRANCIS MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,768
768,ST. FRANCIS MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,Financial Performance,Financial Performance. We will maintain sustainable financial stability. • Leading as a resource-conscious health provider: • Seeking improvement through efficiency and sustainability.,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on financial stability, efficiency, and resource consciousness, aligning with financial sustainability and hints at organizational priorities.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,ST. FRANCIS MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,768
768,ST. FRANCIS MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,Strength In People,"Strength In People. We will recruit, develop and retain qualified staff. • Improve our recruitment plan ensuring inclusivity: • Ensure a healthy and safe workplace: • Demonstrate and support Just culture, innovation, learning and Continuous Quality Improvement: • Improve staff engagement.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on recruitment, retention, and creating a healthy/safe workplace, with elements of a just culture, innovation, and staff engagement which aligns with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,ST. FRANCIS MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,768
771,Peterborough Regional Health Centre,Provide Timely And Excellent Care,Provide Timely And Excellent Care. NF. Partner with patients and families as we deliver care and develop programs: Improve the quality of patient care using a systematic approach: Make it easier for patients to access care using virtual and rapid-access models: Increase safety and efficiency of care through a Command Centre model: Investigate implementing a reactivation care centre to help patients recover faster.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text focuses on improving the quality, safety, and accessibility of patient care, with specific mention of virtual access and rapid-access models.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Peterborough Regional Health Centre,771
771,Peterborough Regional Health Centre,Be A Workplace Where People Can Thrive,"Be A Workplace Where People Can Thrive. NF. Implement a workplace well-being strategy: Create development opportunities for our people: Build a comprehensive workforce plan for today and tomorrow, for all staff and physician groups: Promote inclusion, welcoming perspectives to inform decision-making, service delivery, leadership and partnerships: Strengthen our focus on environmental stewardship.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on employee well-being, development, and inclusion, which are core elements of workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Peterborough Regional Health Centre,771
771,Peterborough Regional Health Centre,Expand Tertiary Services To Support Our Region,Expand Tertiary Services To Support Our Region. NF. Implement an integrated care mental health & addictions model with our partners: Enhance regional maternal and pediatric care: Bring new cardiovascular care services to the region: Expand our seniors' centre of excellence: Continue to expand cancer care services.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The text emphasizes integrated care with partners and expanding services related to mental health, seniors' care, and cancer care, indicating both integration and a focus on population health needs.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Peterborough Regional Health Centre,771
771,Peterborough Regional Health Centre,"Transform Data, Analytics And Technology To Support People Today And Into The Future","Transform Data, Analytics And Technology To Support People Today And Into The Future. NF. Use data and analytics to improve quality of care: Use technology to advance care: Embed data and analytics into all operational decision-making: Make data, analytics and technology user-friendly.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The focus is on using data, analytics, and technology to improve care and operational decision-making, and making these tools user-friendly, which directly relates to digital health and innovation while also aiming to improve quality of care.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Peterborough Regional Health Centre,771
