809,SMOOTH ROCK FALLS HOSPITAL,Technology,Technology. REMAINING CURRENT WITH TECHNOLOGICAL UPGRADES TO IMPROVE SAFETY AND CARE. NF.,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on technological upgrades with the explicit goal of improving safety and care, linking digital innovation with patient outcomes.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,SMOOTH ROCK FALLS HOSPITAL,809
813,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,People,"People. engaging with passion. • Advance Social Accountability: Focus health priorities on marginalized or underserved populations.: • Drive Exceptional Experiences: Deliver timely, equitable, culturally safe, and collaborative person-centered care.: • Foster Proactive Engagement: Engage patients, caregivers, staff, partners, and communities in health promotion, illness prevention, and service design.: • Kindness First: Empathy and kindness will guide our actions in a culture that values equity, inclusion, diversity, and anti-racism.: • Values-Based: Compassion, Accountability, and Integrity will be evident in all that we do.: • Listening Intently: Feedback from patients, families, caregivers, volunteers, staff, partners, and community members will drive continuous improvement.: • Developing All: Staff and volunteers will be supported through ongoing learning and development.: • Communicate Clearly: We will promote transparency and ensure all voices help shape the organization’s direction and tone.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text emphasizes addressing marginalized populations, delivering equitable and culturally safe care, and fostering a culture of equity, inclusion, and anti-racism, alongside patient engagement and compassionate care.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,813
813,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,Partnership,"Partnership. collaborating with purpose. • Foster Collaborative Relationships: Build trusted partnerships grounded in mutual respect and shared accountability.: • Advance Integrated Care: Improve coordination across the care continuum to enhance access, quality, and experience.: • Drive System Transformation: Serve as a catalyst for innovation and alignment across the healthcare system.: • Population Health-Centered Decisions: Focus on improving community health outcomes.: • Inclusive Governance: Engage all stakeholders in decisions that impact them.: • Shared Capability: Contribute THE_HOSPITAL’s knowledge and expertise to build system-wide capacity.: • Barrier Reduction: Identify and eliminate obstacles to accessing high-quality care.: • System Alignment: Align goals, processes, and protocols with partners to enable seamless care.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"The text focuses on building partnerships, improving integrated care, and aligning goals to enhance community health outcomes.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,813
813,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,Performance,"Performance. exceeding expectations. • Foster Responsible Resource Management: Use human, financial, physical, and technological resources ethically, efficiently, and effectively.: • Advance Digital Innovation: Use technology to enhance care delivery and system performance.: • Drive Exceptional Quality Care: Provide care that is person-centered, safe, timely, equitable, and continuously improved.: • Clear, Transparent Priorities: Align resource allocation with organizational and system goals.: • Aligned Performance Indicators: Set annual goals that support strategic objectives.: • Timely Access: Place priority on investments that improve access to appropriate care.: • Leading Practices: Apply evidence-based standards and best practices.: • Exceptional Performance: Equip staff with tools and information to meet high standards.",FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text emphasizes responsible resource management and aligning resource allocation with goals, as well as advancing digital innovation, all pointing to financial sustainability and digital solutions.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,HURON PERTH HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE,813
826,Lake of the Woods District Hospital,Authentic Partnerships,"Authentic Partnerships. NF. We will partner purposefully to advance health system integration, innovation, research and education.. We will partner with patients and families in decision-making for care.. We will acknowledge, respect and collaborate with our Indigenous partners and communities to learn and grow together.. We will collaborate with our Foundation, advancing a culture of philanthropy.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text emphasizes partnerships for system integration, collaboration with Indigenous partners, and engagement with the Foundation.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lake of the Woods District Hospital,826
826,Lake of the Woods District Hospital,Patient Safety And Clinical Excellence,Patient Safety And Clinical Excellence. NF. We will improve patient safety through quality improvement and best practice clinical service delivery.. We will accelerate the introduction and adoption of enterprise-wide data and information systems.. We will invest in continuous learning and development opportunities to support hospital and professional staff in achieving clinical excellence.. We will establish specialty centres of excellence to support health care delivery.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The text focuses on improving patient safety through quality improvement and best practices, and also mentions investing in continuous learning for staff to achieve clinical excellence.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lake of the Woods District Hospital,826
826,Lake of the Woods District Hospital,Effective Stewardship,Effective Stewardship. NF. We will contribute to a healthier planet by reducing our environmental footprint.. We will secure funding tailored to the unique health needs of our region.. We will diversify revenue streams and foster entrepreneurial thinking.. We will optimize efficiency and use of resources.,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"This text focuses on reducing environmental impact and securing funding, diversifying revenue, and optimizing resource use, which aligns with financial sustainability and environmental responsibility.",Financial Sustainability,Financial Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lake of the Woods District Hospital,826
826,Lake of the Woods District Hospital,Engaged Workforce,"Engaged Workforce. NF. We will continually enhance a responsive Human Resources strategy and action plan.. We will engage staff and seek ideas for improving work-life and hospital culture.. We will champion inclusion, diversity, equity and accessibility.. We will advance internal communications efforts to improve organizational transparency and increase employee engagement.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on enhancing HR strategies, improving work-life and culture, and promoting inclusion and engagement within the workforce.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lake of the Woods District Hospital,826
826,Lake of the Woods District Hospital,Campus Of Care,Campus Of Care. NF. We will grow our services to align with current and evolving needs of our region.. We will address issues of rural health inequities through advanced advocacy and strategic efforts.. We will foster unique and innovative solutions to support an integrated health system.. We will work with our partners and key influencers to advance the All Nations Hospital Project.,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"Focuses on addressing rural health inequities and supporting an integrated health system with partners, aligning with both themes.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Lake of the Woods District Hospital,826
837,SickKids,Elevate Quality And The Care Experience,"Elevate Quality And The Care Experience. Care isn't just what we do-it's who we are. To achieve a next-generation experience, we will reimagine care to ensure that every child and family feels seen, heard, and supported. By championing equity and addressing the whole child and family-mind, body, spirit, and social context-we will create a seamless, safe, and inclusive the hospital. On the strength of partnership, we will connect health journeys that not only respond to diverse needs, but also enhance access, proactively eliminate harm, and improve outcomes for all.. • Design inclusive services that respond to patient and family needs: • Advance health equity and action on social determinants of health: • Embed proactive safety and prediction to eliminate harm: • Expand access and partner to create seamless health journeys: • Harmonize physical, mental, and behavioural health.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on improving the care experience by addressing equity, social determinants of health, safety, and seamless health journeys.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,SickKids,837
837,SickKids,Create An Exceptional Employee Experience,"Create An Exceptional Employee Experience. We know that patient, family, and employee experience are inextricably linked; so, when it comes to experience, we will strive to make every day exceptional.<br><br>Together, we will redesign the employee experience from recruitment to retirement, prioritizing training, professional development, competitive compensation, strong benefits and pensions, and recognition in all its forms. Sustaining a focus on employee health and psychological safety, we will create a safer, future-proofed the hospital team. And we will take the pebbles from the shoes of our staff, eliminating unnecessary bureaucracy, automating redundant tasks, and leveraging Al to unleash the talent of our people.. • Develop and reward diverse talent: • Cultivate employee health, well-being, and psychological safety: • Strive for balanced, streamlined, smarter work.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The focus is on improving the employee experience through recruitment, retention, training, compensation, and well-being, aligning with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,SickKids,837
837,SickKids,Advance The Era Of Precision Child Health,"Advance The Era Of Precision Child Health. The Precision Child Health movement has already made significant strides; however, our journey is far from over and our determination to realize individualized care for every child remains unwavering.<br><br>Unifying our people, culture, data, and processes, we will foster a learning network that encourages the free flow of ideas and expertise. Supported by deep engagement of patients and families in all that we do, representation of the diverse population we serve in our research, and revitalization of clinical research services, we will leave the one-size-fits-all era of health care in the rear-view mirror.. • Unify data, culture, and ways of working to lead the shift to individualized care: • Ensure patients and families can inform, participate in, and benefit from discovery research, translation, and clinical care: • Strengthen clinical research to drive scientific and clinical excellence.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The focus is on advancing precision child health through research, individualized care, and patient/family engagement in research and clinical care.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,SickKids,837
837,SickKids,Accelerate Foundations For Innovation,"Accelerate Foundations For Innovation. Project Horizon, our ambitious redevelopment journey, will not only reimagine our campus but also fundamentally change the ways we work. Calibrating campus redevelopment to cutting-edge models of clinical care, research, and education, we will transform 100-year-old buildings into engines of innovation.<br><br>Progress will be fueled by the hospital Al, a trailblazing program that will revolutionize paediatric health services through responsible Al. In the space of Al and beyond, an intensifying focus on research will accelerate discovery and translation to real-world applications, moving the needle where it matters most—at the point of impact for children, youth, and families.. • Leverage campus redevelopment to evolve integrated models of clinical care, research, and education: • Scale responsible Al to optimize outcomes and operations: • Increase research intensity to fuel discovery and translational impact.",INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text discusses campus redevelopment and the integration of AI in healthcare, indicating a focus on both infrastructure and digital innovation.",Infrastructure & Environment,Infrastructure & Environment,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,SickKids,837
850,RUNNYMEDE HEALTHCARE CENTRE,Expansion & Integration,"Expansion & Integration. NF. GROW FOOTPRINT & SERVICES: Improve health outcomes for our diverse community through new development and responsive programs and services.: CONNECTED HEALTHCARE: Enhance access, coordination and support for patients as they move through their healthcare journey.: STRATEGIC PARTNERSHIPS: Expand partnerships to streamline care delivery and enhance organizational effectiveness.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ACCESS & CAPACITY,The text focuses on expanding partnerships and improving access to healthcare services for patients.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,RUNNYMEDE HEALTHCARE CENTRE,850
850,RUNNYMEDE HEALTHCARE CENTRE,Centre Of Excellence,Centre Of Excellence. NF. KNOWLEDGE EXCHANGE: Create opportunities to advance care through information exchange and partnerships.: RESEARCH & INNOVATION: Enable continuous improvement through vision and thought leadership.: EDUCATION: Establish and promote a holistic model of care for aging and wellness.,"RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"The text emphasizes knowledge exchange and partnerships, enabling improvement through thought leadership and establishing a model of care for aging and wellness.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,RUNNYMEDE HEALTHCARE CENTRE,850
850,RUNNYMEDE HEALTHCARE CENTRE,"Quality, Safety, & Accountability","Quality, Safety, & Accountability. NF. CULTURE OF QUALITY: Foster an organization-wide commitment to excellence.: SUSTAINABILITY: Reinforce culture of environmental and financial responsibility.: TECHNOLOGY AND INFRASTRUCTURE: Invest in technology to improve safety, services, and access to information.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The primary focus is on quality and safety, with organizational culture supporting this and sustainability representing a secondary consideration.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,RUNNYMEDE HEALTHCARE CENTRE,850
850,RUNNYMEDE HEALTHCARE CENTRE,Exceptional Experience,"Exceptional Experience. NF. PEOPLE PLAN: Recruit and cultivate top talent to elevate our brand and support organizational excellence.: CUSTOMER SERVICE MINDSET: Adopt a service-driven approach to enhance patient experience.: COMMUNITY CARE: Design care responsive to community, patient and caregiver needs.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,"The focus is on improving patient experience through customer service and community-responsive care, supported by recruiting and cultivating top talent.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Chronic/Rehab Hospital,FALSE,1,RUNNYMEDE HEALTHCARE CENTRE,850
