854,Toronto Grace Hospital,Strategic Direction #1: Invest In Our People And Culture,"Strategic Direction #1: Invest In Our People And Culture. NF. Attract and retain staff who embrace our values and are committed to advancing THE_HOSPITAL's Vision and Mission: Celebrate and promote a diverse, equitable, and inclusive culture: Ensure a safe environment where staff feel heard, and feedback is recognized and actioned by leadership: Invest in learning, wellness and professional development.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The focus is on attracting/retaining staff, promoting DEI, ensuring a safe environment, and investing in learning and wellness, all relating to workforce and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Toronto Grace Hospital,854
854,Toronto Grace Hospital,Strategic Direction #2: Communicate Our Purpose,"Strategic Direction #2: Communicate Our Purpose. NF. Strengthen our understanding of how patients, families, staff, and partners see us: Develop strong communication channels and feedback mechanisms for patients, families, staff, and partners: Openly share the Toronto Grace story with patients, families, staff, partners, and other relevant stakeholders.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,"This strategic direction focuses on strengthening understanding and communication with patients, staff, and partners, which aligns with organizational culture and governance while also touching on integration with external partners.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Toronto Grace Hospital,854
854,Toronto Grace Hospital,Strategic Direction #3: Strengthen Partnerships And Collaboration,Strategic Direction #3: Strengthen Partnerships And Collaboration. NF. Strengthen and expand strategic partnerships to meet future service demands and focus on common goals: Identify opportunities for integrated care to optimally serve our patients and community: Intentionally connect with other networks: Advocate for the needs of those we serve within the health system and the government.,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text emphasizes strengthening partnerships and collaboration, while also aiming to improve service delivery and meet future demands, implying a focus on system integration and access.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Toronto Grace Hospital,854
854,Toronto Grace Hospital,Strategic Direction #4: Drive Innovation And Transformation,Strategic Direction #4: Drive Innovation And Transformation. NF. Enhance our infrastructure and technology: Incorporate new models of care to solve system challenges: Develop new innovations to support seamless transitions back to the community: Ensure operational efficiency and financial sustainability: Provide care and services to help facilitate patient flow and promote recovery through the health care system.,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,"The direction focuses on infrastructure, technology, innovation in care models, and efficiency, pointing towards digital health and financial sustainability.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Toronto Grace Hospital,854
854,Toronto Grace Hospital,Strategic Direction #5: Provide People-Centred Care,Strategic Direction #5: Provide People-Centred Care. NF. Deliver excellent care experiences supporting people and family centered care: Focus on quality and safety and continuous quality improvement: Provide those we serve with timely access to care.,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The strategic direction focuses on delivering excellent, people and family-centered care, with an emphasis on quality, safety, and timely access.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Toronto Grace Hospital,854
858,MICHAEL GARRON HOSPITAL TORONTO EAST HEALTH NETWORK,Deliver High-Quality And Compassionate Care,"Deliver High-Quality And Compassionate Care. While we continue to navigate a rapidly changing landscape, our goal remains to provide the highest quality care to our growing and diverse communities. Embedded in our approach is a commitment to health equity and inclusive care, continuing our journey to remove barriers and recognizing that everyone brings with them a unique set of needs. We remain dedicated to driving quality improvement, and providing an exceptional patient experience where patients feel confident that their care is our highest priority.. * Build quality into everything we do, as part of being one of the safest hospitals in the country;: * Expand quality improvement capacity to ensure the best patient outcomes and experiences;: * Actively plan to expand our existing and established clinical services for the growing population and changing needs of our diverse communities; and: * Adopt a population health approach, with a focus on underserved populations.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text emphasizes high-quality, compassionate care, with a focus on health equity, inclusive care, and removing barriers for diverse communities, aligning with both patient care excellence and social accountability.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,MICHAEL GARRON HOSPITAL TORONTO EAST HEALTH NETWORK,858
858,MICHAEL GARRON HOSPITAL TORONTO EAST HEALTH NETWORK,Value And Inspire Our People,"Value And Inspire Our People. Our ability to achieve excellent care is made possible by the extraordinary dedication of our people who, in the face of challenges, have consistently risen to the occasion. Our people are the driving force behind our ability to achieve our vision and purpose. We will ensure that we build on our culture and strengthen our ability to attract and retain highly talented health professionals who share our organizational values. Going forward, we will continue to recognize the invaluable contributions of our people, providing an environment that promotes ongoing professional growth and development, making Micheal Garron Hospital a sought after place to work and provide care.. * Promote a safe, inclusive and supportive environment, enabling our people to continue delivering high-quality care;: * Build a positive culture that attracts and retains exceptional talent, supporting our health human resource requirements;: * Develop a thriving workforce by advancing professional practice and education to maximize potential; and: * Collaborate with our teams to improve care, listening to their perspectives and recognizing their contributions.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on attracting, retaining, and supporting the workforce, while also building a positive and inclusive organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,MICHAEL GARRON HOSPITAL TORONTO EAST HEALTH NETWORK,858
858,MICHAEL GARRON HOSPITAL TORONTO EAST HEALTH NETWORK,Invest Now For Our Future,"Invest Now For Our Future. To deliver transformative care, we must move quickly to modernize, invest in emerging technologies, update our facilities, and ensure our people have access to the tools they need. The future of technology offers us an unprecedented opportunity to embrace innovation to enhance how we deliver care, while maintaining a commitment to environmental sustainability. To support these efforts, we will continue to work with our partners in government and our Foundation to secure the resources needed to deliver on the promise of excellence.. * Create a digital infrastructure that informs decision-making and reporting through reliable and accurate data in real time;: * Revitalize and modernize the hospital's physical infrastructure, ensuring a positive experience and high-quality care;: * Adopt innovative systems and tools that support our people to better serve patients; and: * Improve the hospital's impact on environmental sustainability.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text focuses on modernizing and investing in emerging technologies and digital infrastructure, as well as revitalizing physical infrastructure and improving environmental sustainability.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,MICHAEL GARRON HOSPITAL TORONTO EAST HEALTH NETWORK,858
858,MICHAEL GARRON HOSPITAL TORONTO EAST HEALTH NETWORK,Advance A High-Impact Academic Mandate,"Advance A High-Impact Academic Mandate. Learning and discovery are the cornerstones of advancing healthcare, and they drive us to innovate, adapt and challenge the status quo. We are well-positioned to continue building on our legacy of excellence in medical and health professional education through a unique research agenda and educational experience that is inspired by a longstanding commitment to care and partnership. We are at a pivotal time in our educational leadership role and will focus on providing our learners with the modern skills and tools required to deliver evidence-based, high-quality care in healthcare settings today and in the future.. * Establish a nationally recognized, community-focused research program;: * Implement an academic roadmap that advances evidence-based patient-centered care;: * Embed research in our clinical programs, and promote our research findings to enhance the quality of care in our community and beyond; and: * Expand innovative models of learning that prepare the next generation of healthcare professionals to deliver high-quality care.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on advancing learning, research, and education to improve healthcare delivery and patient-centered care.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,MICHAEL GARRON HOSPITAL TORONTO EAST HEALTH NETWORK,858
858,MICHAEL GARRON HOSPITAL TORONTO EAST HEALTH NETWORK,Lead Integrated Care,"Lead Integrated Care. The future of integrated care will require a system-wide commitment to transforming the care experience for patients and their families. As a well-established leader in partnering with community health and social service organizations, we have been at the forefront in working with others to support patients in advancing more connected care. With this foundation in place, we will strive to build a model of integrated care that embraces the full continuum of care, including primary and community care and will serve as an example for others across the province.. * Work with our community partners to advance a model of integrated care, serving as a leading example for the province;: * Develop a campus of care that expands services to support patients at every stage of their health journey;: * Solidify strategic partnerships that advance research, education and access to care; and: * Strengthen relationships with the communities we serve to provide culturally safe, equitable, and patient-centred care that addresses the unique needs of patients and families.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"This focuses on partnering with community organizations to create a more integrated care model and addresses culturally safe and equitable care, thus covering integration and health equity.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,MICHAEL GARRON HOSPITAL TORONTO EAST HEALTH NETWORK,858
862,WOMEN'S COLLEGE HOSPITAL,Lead The New Era Of Sex And Gender In Health,"Lead The New Era Of Sex And Gender In Health. Closing gender gaps and supporting well-being across the life span.. * Establish Canada's first Centre for Sex and Gender in Health to address sex and gender bias and gaps in healthcare and research that lead to poorer health outcomes, evidence gaps and inefficient health spending for women, trans and gender diverse people.: * Drive precision healthcare – focused on individual needs of patients and families – for those living with complex health conditions influenced by sex and gender.: * Promote healthy aging by addressing the unique health and wellbeing needs of women and gender diverse people across the lifespan.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,"This initiative directly addresses sex and gender biases in healthcare, aiming to improve health outcomes for women, trans, and gender diverse people, while also promoting healthy aging and well-being across the lifespan.",Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,WOMEN'S COLLEGE HOSPITAL,862
862,WOMEN'S COLLEGE HOSPITAL,Move The Needle On Health Equity,"Move The Needle On Health Equity. Creating a just and equitable health system with better health outcomes.. * Partner with First Nations, Inuit and Métis peoples to improve health and wellbeing and elevate community health priorities.: * Relentlessly work to achieve health equity in partnership with communities.: * Build trusted, just, inclusive environments across care, learning and discovery.",HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,The primary focus is on achieving health equity through partnerships with Indigenous communities and building inclusive environments.,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Health Equity & Social Accountability,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,WOMEN'S COLLEGE HOSPITAL,862
862,WOMEN'S COLLEGE HOSPITAL,Reimagine The Health System With And For Patients,"Reimagine The Health System With And For Patients. Creating a better integrated system of care and better patient experience across the care continuum.. * Lead and inform innovative outpatient and primary care models that prioritize access and coordinated care across hospital, home and community settings and realize system efficiencies.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on system integration and patient experience across the care continuum, aiming for better coordinated care.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Teaching Hospital,FALSE,1,WOMEN'S COLLEGE HOSPITAL,862
882,Winchester District Memorial Hospital,Quality/ Services,"Quality/ Services. We will provide high-quality services to achieve the best possible patient experience and outcomes.. • Partner with patients to improve their care: • Serve as a collaboration hub to address community needs throughout all stages of life: • Enhance patient access and interaction, including new digital opportunities: • Conduct rural health research and apply evidence to support quality improvement: • Ensure public awareness and understanding of patient services.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,The focus is on providing high-quality services for best patient outcomes and addressing community needs.,Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Winchester District Memorial Hospital,882
882,Winchester District Memorial Hospital,Our People,"Our People. We value our staff, physicians, volunteers and learners, and will foster a workplace where everyone is empowered to work to their full potential.. • Live our Commitment Statement: • Provide opportunities for growth and learning: • Communicate effectively: • Strengthen health, safety and wellness in our workplace: • Be a workplace-of-choice for new applicants and our current team: • Continue to foster engagement in THE_HOSPITAL decisions and activities.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on valuing staff, providing opportunities, and fostering a positive workplace, all of which contribute to workforce sustainability and a positive organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Winchester District Memorial Hospital,882
882,Winchester District Memorial Hospital,Partnerships/ Integration,"Partnerships/ Integration. We will collaborate to improve our patients’ transitions.. • Share resources, including knowledge, information, education, technology, programs and advocacy efforts: • Explore new opportunities, including those involving virtual services: • Partner with physician organizations to address community needs: • Partner with educational organizations to facilitate the transfer of knowledge and skills.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,The text focuses on collaborative partnerships to improve patient transitions and address community needs.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Winchester District Memorial Hospital,882
882,Winchester District Memorial Hospital,Accountability,"Accountability. We will demonstrate accountability in all relationships and ensure responsible stewardship of all resources.. • Make decisions ethically, consistently and transparently: • Actively engage in change involving the broader health system: • Nurture a strong community relationship that encourages continuous investment in THE_HOSPITAL: • Strategically invest in infrastructure, equipment and technology: • Practice environmental responsibility.",ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,"The focus is on ethical decision-making, stewardship of resources, and investment in the hospital's future, aligning with organizational values and responsible resource management.",Org Culture & Governance,Org Culture & Governance,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Winchester District Memorial Hospital,882
888,L'Hôpital Temiskaming,Personnes,"Personnes. équipe résiliente, organisation durable.. • La rétention du meilleur personnel: • Le renforcement du processus d'embauche: • La citoyenneté environnementale intégrée: • L'amélioration de la santé et la stabilité financières.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY,"This text focuses on retaining personnel, improving hiring processes, environmental citizenship, and improving financial health.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,L'Hôpital Temiskaming,888
888,L'Hôpital Temiskaming,Partenaires,"Partenaires. Relations valorisées, communautés fortes. • Revendiquer de façon significative: • Uniformiser les soins grâce aux partenariats: • Faciliter l'accès efficace aux services de santé: • Développer la mise en œuvre de l'équipe Santé Ontario.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text emphasizes partnerships and equitable access to healthcare services, particularly through the development of Ontario Health Teams.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,L'Hôpital Temiskaming,888
888,L'Hôpital Temiskaming,Patients,"Patients. expérience cohérente, résultats positifs.. • Assurer une expérience cohérente chez le patient: • Étendre nos services spécialisés: • Optimiser et coordonner l'utilisation des lieux: • Concevoir l'accès aux soins adapté à la culture et accessible.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ACCESS & CAPACITY,The text focuses on ensuring a consistent patient experience and optimizing access to care.,Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,L'Hôpital Temiskaming,888
888,L'Hôpital Temiskaming,Processus,"Processus. capacité numérique, connexion améliorée. • Mettre en œuvre l'initiative ONE *: • Investir dans les systèmes et processus: • Améliorer la communication et le partage d'information: • Augmenter l'accessibilité.",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The text discusses digital capacity, improved connection, systems and processes, communication, and increased accessibility, indicating a focus on digital solutions and their impact on access.",Digital Health & Innovation,Digital Health & Innovation,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,L'Hôpital Temiskaming,888
889,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,Human Resources,"Human Resources. A Workplace that nurtures accountability, individual and collective potential and a culture of kindness and inclusion.. 6. To achieve 85% of regular active staff, patient partners, and board members, completing the unconscious bias training and inclusive language modules by March 31, 2026. Baseline = 0: 8. Improve staff engagement by decreasing the leaders scores on the following Accreditation Canada Staff Engagement Survey questions by March 31, 2027:: a) Decrease by 30%, leaders who report their days as being quite or extremely stressful. Baseline = 60%.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"This initiative focuses on staff engagement, reducing stress, and promoting inclusion through unconscious bias training, all contributing to workforce sustainability and equity.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Small Hospital,FALSE,1,Listowel Wingham HOSPITALS ALLIANCE,889
890,WOODSTOCK HOSPITAL,Caring,"Caring. Demonstrating empathy, respect, and compassion in everything we do, by prioritizing the well-being of patients, families, our hospital team, and the community. Through our hospital culture of kindness and Service Excellence we are committed to providing a sense of belonging for all.. - Ensure a safe and healthy environment for all: - Foster a culture of compassion that aligns with the guiding principles of people-centred care: - Promote equitable access to resources and care.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on empathy, compassion, and well-being of patients, families, and the community, which aligns with patient care excellence, and highlights a culture of kindness and service excellence, pointing to organizational culture.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,WOODSTOCK HOSPITAL,890
890,WOODSTOCK HOSPITAL,Empowering,"Empowering. Fostering a culture of trust, collaboration, and growth, to enable individuals, patients, families, our hospital team, and community members to reach their full potential. Achieved by preparing people with the knowledge, tools, and confidence to make informed decisions.. - Enhance well-being and resilience of our hospital team by investing in staff learning and development: - Provide patients and caregivers with tools for self-management and informed decision-making: - Recruit and retain highly skilled staff.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on fostering a culture of trust and growth, investing in staff learning and development, and recruiting/retaining skilled staff, ultimately enhancing patient care through informed decision-making and self-management.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,WOODSTOCK HOSPITAL,890
890,WOODSTOCK HOSPITAL,Evolving,"Evolving. Evolving as our community grows, to meet its changing healthcare needs. Embracing innovation and cutting-edge technology to ensure we provide the highest quality care. An ongoing commitment to energy conservation and sustainability.. - Grow with our community while adapting to the changing needs and demographics: - Incorporate innovative solutions by embracing technology and adapting to emerging trends: - Commit to energy conservation and sustainable practices, integrating eco-friendly solutions.",POPULATION & COMMUNITY HEALTH,DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"Focuses on community growth and needs, incorporating technology, and sustainability (environmental aspect).",Population & Community Health,Population & Community Health,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,WOODSTOCK HOSPITAL,890
890,WOODSTOCK HOSPITAL,Collaborating,"Collaborating. Cultivating strong partnerships and relationships beyond the hospital walls to better address the diverse needs of those we serve. Internally, we foster a culture of teamwork, encouraging open communication and shared responsibility, to achieve the best outcomes for all.. - Build and strengthen relationships with our community partners: - Strengthen internal, cross departmental collaboration: - Actively involve patients, families, and caregivers in hospital initiatives and decision-making processes.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text emphasizes building relationships with community partners and fostering internal collaboration, aligning with integration and organizational culture themes.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,WOODSTOCK HOSPITAL,890
