905,Oak Valley Health,"Our People, Our Culture","Our People, Our Culture. Integrated care is dependent on people working together. Time and time again, we have heard that what makes the hospital special is our people and our culture. While our mission focuses on providing an extraordinary patient experience, we want our people to enjoy working, practicing, volunteering, and learning at the hospital while supporting and providing care. That’s why it has never been more important to prioritize the people who make our honoured to care culture special and who are instrumental to our success.. by enhancing our approach to focused retention, prioritizing wellbeing, and strengthening our investment in our people.. by employing purposeful recruitment to address our programs and community priorities.. by creating and empowering high-performing teams that advance collaborative health care.. by improving the understanding of our lived experience through radical engagement and creating safe spaces to listen and incorporate ideas to advance equity, diversity, inclusion, and belonging.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,ORG CULTURE & GOVERNANCE,"The text focuses on people, culture, retention, wellbeing, recruitment and empowering teams, all aligning with workforce sustainability and organizational culture.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Oak Valley Health,905
905,Oak Valley Health,System Design And Partnerships,"System Design And Partnerships. Integrated care is dependent on making purposeful connections. One of the hospital's greatest strengths is our ability to address challenges with creative solutions, partnering with all kinds of interested parties, across our organization and throughout the broader health system, to meet the needs of the patients and the communities we serve. We believe prioritizing system design and partnerships is essential for successful integrated care and we work hard to be good partners.. by prioritizing collaboration over competition and demonstrating the benefits of partnering with us.. by enhancing community engagement and reach, and employing co-design and co-delivery models wherever possible.. by strengthening relationships and alliances with primary care, community providers, our Eastern York Region North Durham Ontario Health Team, and system partners to create seamless transitions and address the needs of all our patients including underserved populations.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text emphasizes collaboration with various partners, including the Ontario Health Team and community providers, to improve integrated care and address the needs of underserved populations.",Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Oak Valley Health,905
905,Oak Valley Health,Scholarship And Innovation,"Scholarship And Innovation. Integrated care is dependent on growth. The health care landscape is changing along with our growing community. With innovation in mind, we will grow our programs, services, and space and enhance environmental sustainability along the way. We will prioritize scholarship to provide cutting-edge care close to home and a rich learning experience for our future health care professionals, partners, patients, and families.. by enhancing our academic affiliations, creating an extraordinary learner experience for trainees and staff, and expanding our research program.. by leading the field in responding with agility to the ever-changing health care environment, and empowering our teams to explore new ways of doing things.. by automating legacy processes, evolving technology, and enhancing data-driven decision-making.. by methodically expanding our physical space and purposefully expanding our programs and services to meet the needs of the patients and communities we serve, while mindful of the impact to the environment.","RESEARCH, EDUCATION & ACADEMICS",DIGITAL HEALTH & INNOVATION,"The text emphasizes scholarship, learning experience, research program expansion, and technology evolution for data-driven decision-making.","Research, Education & Academics","Research, Education & Academics",Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Oak Valley Health,905
916,HEADWATERS Health Care Centre,Empower Our People,"Empower Our People. Our team is invaluable. Empowering and investing in the development, well-being, safety, and support of our people is paramount to ensure a high performing and sustainable workplace environment that delivers the best care for our patients and communities.. • Attract, retain, and recognize our people: • Focus on an engaged, inclusive, safe and healthy workplace: • Enable teams to deliver high quality care with tools and resources.",WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,"The text focuses on attracting, retaining, and supporting staff well-being to create a high-performing workplace and deliver high-quality patient care.",Workforce Sustainability,Workforce Sustainability,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,HEADWATERS Health Care Centre,916
916,HEADWATERS Health Care Centre,Get Even Better,"Get Even Better. Continually improving systems, processes and our facility is fundamental to achieving our commitments, delivering a consistent patient experience, and ensuring operational excellence. We have a responsibility to ensure our performance meets the needs of our patients and community.. • Use timely, evidence and data-based analysis to support decision making and enhance equitable access to care: • Advance digital health opportunities: • Continue to build for the future of our facility.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,INFRASTRUCTURE & ENVIRONMENT,"The text focuses on improving systems, processes, and the facility to enhance patient experience and operational excellence, while also mentioning building for the future of the facility.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,HEADWATERS Health Care Centre,916
916,HEADWATERS Health Care Centre,Deliver Patient Centred Quality Care,"Deliver Patient Centred Quality Care. Pursuing continuous quality improvement is fundamental to achieving our commitments and delivering excellent patient care and experiences. Through a relentless focus on quality and safety, we will deliver quality care to be proud of.. • Listen to patients, families and caregivers to support what's most important to them: • Build a safe, quality driven, continuous improvement culture following best practice guidelines: • Ensure population health measures inform our approach to decisions: • Promote health equity, ensuring inclusion and diversity are respected and achieved.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,HEALTH EQUITY & SOCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY,"The text focuses on delivering high-quality, patient-centered care and improving the patient experience, while also emphasizing health equity, inclusion, and diversity.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,HEADWATERS Health Care Centre,916
916,HEADWATERS Health Care Centre,Connect Through Partnerships,"Connect Through Partnerships. Ongoing success and innovation includes collaboration and support from and with system partners. Together, we can achieve more to support delivery of the best care to our communities.. • Lead and pursue meaningful partnerships that extend our capability to support seamless, equitable and timely access to care: • Strengthen our academic partnerships: • Grow opportunities for training and development: • Use technology to enhance efficiency, safety and care.",INTEGRATION & PARTNERSHIPS,WORKFORCE SUSTAINABILITY,The text emphasizes collaboration with system partners and strengthening academic partnerships to improve care delivery and grow training opportunities.,Integration & Partnerships,Integration & Partnerships,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,HEADWATERS Health Care Centre,916
928,Perth and Smiths Falls District Hospital,"Provide An Excellent Experience For The Persons We Serve, Every Time","Provide An Excellent Experience For The Persons We Serve, Every Time. NF. • Deploy best practice to deliver safest possible care: • Remove barriers to care: • Improve care transitions and health system navigation: • Review and remove barriers to Patient Flow: ○ revise Surge Policy: ○ implement 100% of the recommendations from review: • Reduce Injurious Falls: ○ Reduce the number of falls with injury by 25% for each unit: ○ Reduce the number of overall falls by 1.79 per 1000 patient days: • Improve transfer information at care transitions.",PATIENT CARE EXCELLENCE,ACCESS & CAPACITY,"The focus is on improving patient experience and safety, with elements addressing barriers to care and patient flow which fall under access and capacity.",Patient Care Excellence,Patient Care Excellence,Large Community Hospital,FALSE,1,Perth and Smiths Falls District Hospital,928
